29 /*
30 ASN Options:
31  * NO_ASN_TIME: Disables time parts of the ASN code for systems without an RTC
32  or wishing to save space.
33  * IGNORE_NAME_CONSTRAINTS: Skip ASN name checks.
34  * ASN_DUMP_OID: Allows dump of OID information for debugging.
35  * RSA_DECODE_EXTRA: Decodes extra information in RSA public key.
36  * WOLFSSL_CERT_GEN: Cert generation. Saves extra certificate info in GetName.
37  * WOLFSSL_NO_OCSP_OPTIONAL_CERTS: Skip optional OCSP certs (responder issuer
38  must still be trusted)
39  * WOLFSSL_NO_TRUSTED_CERTS_VERIFY: Workaround for situation where entire cert
40  chain is not loaded. This only matches on subject and public key and
41  does not perform a PKI validation, so it is not a secure solution.
42  Only enabled for OCSP.
43  * WOLFSSL_NO_OCSP_ISSUER_CHECK: Can be defined for backwards compatibility to
44  disable checking of OCSP subject hash with issuer hash.
45 */
46

222 /* wolf struct tm and time_t */
223 #if defined(USE_WOLF_TM)
224  struct tm {
225  int tm_sec; /* seconds after the minute [0-60] */
226  int tm_min; /* minutes after the hour [0-59] */
227  int tm_hour; /* hours since midnight [0-23] */
228  int tm_mday; /* day of the month [1-31] */
229  int tm_mon; /* months since January [0-11] */
230  int tm_year; /* years since 1900 */
231  int tm_wday; /* days since Sunday [0-6] */
232  int tm_yday; /* days since January 1 [0-365] */
233  int tm_isdst; /* Daylight Savings Time flag */
234  long tm_gmtoff; /* offset from CUT in seconds */
235  char *tm_zone; /* timezone abbreviation */
236  };
237 #endif /* USE_WOLF_TM */

262 #if defined(_WIN32_WCE)
263 time_t windows_time(time_t* timer)
264 {
265  SYSTEMTIME sysTime;
266  FILETIME fTime;
267  ULARGE_INTEGER intTime;
268  time_t localTime;
269 
270  if (timer == NULL)
271  timer = &localTime;
272 
273  GetSystemTime(&sysTime);
274  SystemTimeToFileTime(&sysTime, &fTime);
275 
276  XMEMCPY(&intTime, &fTime, sizeof(FILETIME));
277  /* subtract EPOCH */
278  intTime.QuadPart -= 0x19db1ded53e8000;
279  /* to secs */
280  intTime.QuadPart /= 10000000;
281  *timer = (time_t)intTime.QuadPart;
282 
283  return *timer;
284 }
285 #endif /* _WIN32_WCE */
286 
287 #if defined(WOLFSSL_GMTIME)
288 struct tm* gmtime(const time_t* timer)
289 {
290  #define YEAR0 1900
291  #define EPOCH_YEAR 1970
292  #define SECS_DAY (24L * 60L * 60L)
293  #define LEAPYEAR(year) (!((year) % 4) && (((year) % 100) || !((year) %400)))
294  #define YEARSIZE(year) (LEAPYEAR(year) ? 366 : 365)
295 
296  static const int _ytab[2][12] =
297  {
298  {31, 28, 31, 30, 31, 30, 31, 31, 30, 31, 30, 31},
299  {31, 29, 31, 30, 31, 30, 31, 31, 30, 31, 30, 31}
300  };
301 
302  static struct tm st_time;
303  struct tm* ret = &st_time;
304  time_t secs = *timer;
305  unsigned long dayclock, dayno;
306  int year = EPOCH_YEAR;
307 
308  dayclock = (unsigned long)secs % SECS_DAY;
309  dayno = (unsigned long)secs / SECS_DAY;
310 
311  ret->tm_sec = (int) dayclock % 60;
312  ret->tm_min = (int)(dayclock % 3600) / 60;
313  ret->tm_hour = (int) dayclock / 3600;
314  ret->tm_wday = (int) (dayno + 4) % 7; /* day 0 a Thursday */
315 
316  while(dayno >= (unsigned long)YEARSIZE(year)) {
317  dayno -= YEARSIZE(year);
318  year++;
319  }
320 
321  ret->tm_year = year - YEAR0;
322  ret->tm_yday = (int)dayno;
323  ret->tm_mon = 0;
324 
325  while(dayno >= (unsigned long)_ytab[LEAPYEAR(year)][ret->tm_mon]) {
326  dayno -= _ytab[LEAPYEAR(year)][ret->tm_mon];
327  ret->tm_mon++;
328  }
329 
330  ret->tm_mday = (int)++dayno;
331  ret->tm_isdst = 0;
332 
333  return ret;
334 }
335 #endif /* WOLFSSL_GMTIME */
336

338 #if defined(HAVE_RTP_SYS)
339 #define YEAR0 1900
340 
341 struct tm* rtpsys_gmtime(const time_t* timer) /* has a gmtime() but hangs */
342 {
343  static struct tm st_time;
344  struct tm* ret = &st_time;
345 
346  DC_RTC_CALENDAR cal;
347  dc_rtc_time_get(&cal, TRUE);
348 
349  ret->tm_year = cal.year - YEAR0; /* gm starts at 1900 */
350  ret->tm_mon = cal.month - 1; /* gm starts at 0 */
351  ret->tm_mday = cal.day;
352  ret->tm_hour = cal.hour;
353  ret->tm_min = cal.minute;
354  ret->tm_sec = cal.second;
355 
356  return ret;
357 }
358 
359 #endif /* HAVE_RTP_SYS */

364 /*
365  * time() is just a stub in Microchip libraries. We need our own
366  * implementation. Use SNTP client to get seconds since epoch.
367  */
368 time_t pic32_time(time_t* timer)
369 {
370 #ifdef MICROCHIP_TCPIP_V5
371  DWORD sec = 0;
372 #else
373  uint32_t sec = 0;
374 #endif
375  time_t localTime;
376 
377  if (timer == NULL)
378  timer = &localTime;
379 
380 #ifdef MICROCHIP_MPLAB_HARMONY
381  sec = TCPIP_SNTP_UTCSecondsGet();
382 #else
383  sec = SNTPGetUTCSeconds();
384 #endif
385  *timer = (time_t) sec;
386 
387  return *timer;
388 }
389 
390 #endif /* MICROCHIP_TCPIP || MICROCHIP_TCPIP_V5 */

446 time_t XTIME(time_t * timer)
447 {
448  time_t sec = 0;
449  XRtcPsu_Config* con;
450  XRtcPsu rtc;
451 
452  con = XRtcPsu_LookupConfig(XPAR_XRTCPSU_0_DEVICE_ID);
453  if (con != NULL) {
454  if (XRtcPsu_CfgInitialize(&rtc, con, con->BaseAddr) == XST_SUCCESS) {
455  sec = (time_t)XRtcPsu_GetCurrentTime(&rtc);
456  }
457  else {
458  WOLFSSL_MSG("Unable to initialize RTC");
459  }
460  }
461 
462  if (timer != NULL)
463  *timer = sec;
464 
465  return sec;
466 }

477 /* two byte date/time, add to value */
478 static INLINE void GetTime(int* value, const byte* date, int* idx)
479 {
480  int i = *idx;
481 
482  *value += btoi(date[i++]) * 10;
483  *value += btoi(date[i++]);
484 
485  *idx = i;
486 }

508 WOLFSSL_LOCAL int GetLength(const byte* input, word32* inOutIdx, int* len,
509  word32 maxIdx)
510 {
511  int length = 0;
512  word32 idx = *inOutIdx;
513  byte b;
514 
515  *len = 0; /* default length */
516 
517  if ((idx + 1) > maxIdx) { /* for first read */
518  WOLFSSL_MSG("GetLength bad index on input");
519  return BUFFER_E;
520  }
521 
522  b = input[idx++];
523  if (b >= ASN_LONG_LENGTH) {
524  word32 bytes = b & 0x7F;
525 
526  if ((idx + bytes) > maxIdx) { /* for reading bytes */
527  WOLFSSL_MSG("GetLength bad long length");
528  return BUFFER_E;
529  }
530 
531  while (bytes--) {
532  b = input[idx++];
533  length = (length << 8) | b;
534  }
535  }
536  else
537  length = b;
538 
539  if ((idx + length) > maxIdx) { /* for user of length */
540  WOLFSSL_MSG("GetLength value exceeds buffer length");
541  return BUFFER_E;
542  }
543 
544  *inOutIdx = idx;
545  if (length > 0)
546  *len = length;
547 
548  return length;
549 }
550 
551 
552 /* Get the DER/BER encoding of an ASN.1 header.
553  *
554  * input Buffer holding DER/BER encoded data.
555  * tag ASN.1 tag value expected in header.
556  * inOutIdx Current index into buffer to parse.
557  * len The number of bytes in the ASN.1 data.
558  * maxIdx Length of data in buffer.
559  * returns BUFFER_E when there is not enough data to parse.
560  * ASN_PARSE_E when the expected tag is not found or length is invalid.
561  * Otherwise, the number of bytes in the ASN.1 data.
562  */
563 static int GetASNHeader(const byte* input, byte tag, word32* inOutIdx, int* len,
564  word32 maxIdx)
565 {
566  word32 idx = *inOutIdx;
567  byte b;
568  int length;
569 
570  if ((idx + 1) > maxIdx)
571  return BUFFER_E;
572 
573  b = input[idx++];
574  if (b != tag)
575  return ASN_PARSE_E;
576 
577  if (GetLength(input, &idx, &length, maxIdx) < 0)
578  return ASN_PARSE_E;
579 
580  *len = length;
581  *inOutIdx = idx;
582  return length;
583 }
584 
585 WOLFSSL_LOCAL int GetSequence(const byte* input, word32* inOutIdx, int* len,
586  word32 maxIdx)
587 {
588  return GetASNHeader(input, ASN_SEQUENCE | ASN_CONSTRUCTED, inOutIdx, len,
589  maxIdx);
590 }
591 
592 
593 WOLFSSL_LOCAL int GetSet(const byte* input, word32* inOutIdx, int* len,
594  word32 maxIdx)
595 {
596  return GetASNHeader(input, ASN_SET | ASN_CONSTRUCTED, inOutIdx, len,
597  maxIdx);
598 }
599 
600 /* Get the DER/BER encoded ASN.1 NULL element.
601  * Ensure that the all fields are as expected and move index past the element.
602  *
603  * input Buffer holding DER/BER encoded data.
604  * inOutIdx Current index into buffer to parse.
605  * maxIdx Length of data in buffer.
606  * returns BUFFER_E when there is not enough data to parse.
607  * ASN_TAG_NULL_E when the NULL tag is not found.
608  * ASN_EXPECT_0_E when the length is not zero.
609  * Otherwise, 0 to indicate success.
610  */
611 static int GetASNNull(const byte* input, word32* inOutIdx, word32 maxIdx)
612 {
613  word32 idx = *inOutIdx;
614  byte b;
615 
616  if ((idx + 2) > maxIdx)
617  return BUFFER_E;
618 
619  b = input[idx++];
620  if (b != ASN_TAG_NULL)
621  return ASN_TAG_NULL_E;
622 
623  if (input[idx++] != 0)
624  return ASN_EXPECT_0_E;
625 
626  *inOutIdx = idx;
627  return 0;
628 }
629 
630 /* Set the DER/BER encoding of the ASN.1 NULL element.
631  *
632  * output Buffer to write into.
633  * returns the number of bytes added to the buffer.
634  */
635 static int SetASNNull(byte* output)
636 {
637  output[0] = ASN_TAG_NULL;
638  output[1] = 0;
639 
640  return 2;
641 }
642 
643 /* Get the DER/BER encoding of an ASN.1 BOOLEAN.
644  *
645  * input Buffer holding DER/BER encoded data.
646  * inOutIdx Current index into buffer to parse.
647  * maxIdx Length of data in buffer.
648  * returns BUFFER_E when there is not enough data to parse.
649  * ASN_PARSE_E when the BOOLEAN tag is not found or length is not 1.
650  * Otherwise, 0 to indicate the value was false and 1 to indicate true.
651  */
652 static int GetBoolean(const byte* input, word32* inOutIdx, word32 maxIdx)
653 {
654  word32 idx = *inOutIdx;
655  byte b;
656 
657  if ((idx + 3) > maxIdx)
658  return BUFFER_E;
659 
660  b = input[idx++];
661  if (b != ASN_BOOLEAN)
662  return ASN_PARSE_E;
663 
664  if (input[idx++] != 1)
665  return ASN_PARSE_E;
666 
667  b = input[idx++] != 0;
668 
669  *inOutIdx = idx;
670  return b;
671 }
672 
673 #ifdef ASN1_SET_BOOLEAN
674 /* Set the DER/BER encoding of the ASN.1 NULL element.
675  * Note: Function not required as yet.
676  *
677  * val Boolean value to encode.
678  * output Buffer to write into.
679  * returns the number of bytes added to the buffer.
680  */
681 static int SetBoolean(int val, byte* output)
682 {
683  output[0] = ASN_BOOLEAN;
684  output[1] = 1;
685  output[2] = val ? -1 : 0;
686 
687  return 3;
688 }
689 #endif
690 
691 /* Get the DER/BER encoding of an ASN.1 OCTET_STRING header.
692  *
693  * input Buffer holding DER/BER encoded data.
694  * inOutIdx Current index into buffer to parse.
695  * len The number of bytes in the ASN.1 data.
696  * maxIdx Length of data in buffer.
697  * returns BUFFER_E when there is not enough data to parse.
698  * ASN_PARSE_E when the OCTET_STRING tag is not found or length is
699  * invalid.
700  * Otherwise, the number of bytes in the ASN.1 data.
701  */
702 static int GetOctetString(const byte* input, word32* inOutIdx, int* len,
703  word32 maxIdx)
704 {
705  return GetASNHeader(input, ASN_OCTET_STRING, inOutIdx, len, maxIdx);
706 }
707 
708 /* Get the DER/BER encoding of an ASN.1 INTEGER header.
709  * Removes the leading zero byte when found.
710  *
711  * input Buffer holding DER/BER encoded data.
712  * inOutIdx Current index into buffer to parse.
713  * len The number of bytes in the ASN.1 data (excluding any leading zero).
714  * maxIdx Length of data in buffer.
715  * returns BUFFER_E when there is not enough data to parse.
716  * ASN_PARSE_E when the INTEGER tag is not found, length is invalid,
717  * or invalid use of or missing leading zero.
718  * Otherwise, 0 to indicate success.
719  */
720 static int GetASNInt(const byte* input, word32* inOutIdx, int* len,
721  word32 maxIdx)
722 {
723  int ret;
724 
725  ret = GetASNHeader(input, ASN_INTEGER, inOutIdx, len, maxIdx);
726  if (ret < 0)
727  return ret;
728 
729  if (*len > 0) {
730  /* remove leading zero, unless there is only one 0x00 byte */
731  if ((input[*inOutIdx] == 0x00) && (*len > 1)) {
732  (*inOutIdx)++;
733  (*len)--;
734 
735  if (*len > 0 && (input[*inOutIdx] & 0x80) == 0)
736  return ASN_PARSE_E;
737  }
738  else if ((input[*inOutIdx] & 0x80) == 0x80)
739  return ASN_PARSE_E;
740  }
741 
742  return 0;
743 }
744 
745 /* Get the DER/BER encoding of an ASN.1 INTEGER that has a value of no more than
746  * 7 bits.
747  *
748  * input Buffer holding DER/BER encoded data.
749  * inOutIdx Current index into buffer to parse.
750  * maxIdx Length of data in buffer.
751  * returns BUFFER_E when there is not enough data to parse.
752  * ASN_PARSE_E when the INTEGER tag is not found or length is invalid.
753  * Otherwise, the 7-bit value.
754  */
755 static int GetInteger7Bit(const byte* input, word32* inOutIdx, word32 maxIdx)
756 {
757  word32 idx = *inOutIdx;
758  byte b;
759 
760  if ((idx + 3) > maxIdx)
761  return BUFFER_E;
762 
763  if (input[idx++] != ASN_INTEGER)
764  return ASN_PARSE_E;
765  if (input[idx++] != 1)
766  return ASN_PARSE_E;
767  b = input[idx++];
768 
769  *inOutIdx = idx;
770  return b;
771 }
772 
773 #if !defined(NO_DSA) || defined(HAVE_ECC) || (!defined(NO_RSA) && (defined(WOLFSSL_CERT_GEN) || (defined(WOLFSSL_KEY_GEN) && !defined(HAVE_USER_RSA))))
774 /* Set the DER/BER encoding of the ASN.1 INTEGER header.
775  *
776  * len Length of data to encode.
777  * firstByte First byte of data, most significant byte of integer, to encode.
778  * output Buffer to write into.
779  * returns the number of bytes added to the buffer.
780  */
781 static int SetASNInt(int len, byte firstByte, byte* output)
782 {
783  word32 idx = 0;
784 
785  output[idx++] = ASN_INTEGER;
786  if (firstByte & 0x80)
787  len++;
788  idx += SetLength(len, output + idx);
789  if (firstByte & 0x80)
790  output[idx++] = 0x00;
791 
792  return idx;
793 }
794 #endif
795 
796 #if !defined(NO_DSA) || defined(HAVE_ECC) || defined(WOLFSSL_CERT_GEN) || (defined(WOLFSSL_KEY_GEN) && !defined(NO_RSA) && !defined(HAVE_USER_RSA))
797 /* Set the DER/BER encoding of the ASN.1 INTEGER element with an mp_int.
798  * The number is assumed to be positive.
799  *
800  * n Multi-precision integer to encode.
801  * maxSz Maximum size of the encoded integer.
802  * A negative value indicates no check of length requested.
803  * output Buffer to write into.
804  * returns BUFFER_E when the data is too long for the buffer.
805  * MP_TO_E when encoding the integer fails.
806  * Otherwise, the number of bytes added to the buffer.
807  */
808 static int SetASNIntMP(mp_int* n, int maxSz, byte* output)
809 {
810  int idx = 0;
811  int leadingBit;
812  int length;
813  int err;
814 
815  leadingBit = mp_leading_bit(n);
816  length = mp_unsigned_bin_size(n);
817  idx = SetASNInt(length, leadingBit ? 0x80 : 0x00, output);
818  if (maxSz >= 0 && (idx + length) > maxSz)
819  return BUFFER_E;
820 
821  err = mp_to_unsigned_bin(n, output + idx);
822  if (err != MP_OKAY)
823  return MP_TO_E;
824  idx += length;
825 
826  return idx;
827 }
828 #endif
829 
830 #if !defined(NO_RSA) && defined(HAVE_USER_RSA) && defined(WOLFSSL_CERT_GEN)
831 /* Set the DER/BER encoding of the ASN.1 INTEGER element with an mp_int from
832  * an RSA key.
833  * The number is assumed to be positive.
834  *
835  * n Multi-precision integer to encode.
836  * output Buffer to write into.
837  * returns BUFFER_E when the data is too long for the buffer.
838  * MP_TO_E when encoding the integer fails.
839  * Otherwise, the number of bytes added to the buffer.
840  */
841 static int SetASNIntRSA(mp_int* n, byte* output)
842 {
843  int idx = 0;
844  int leadingBit;
845  int length;
846  int err;
847 
848  leadingBit = wc_Rsa_leading_bit(n);
849  length = wc_Rsa_unsigned_bin_size(n);
850  idx = SetASNInt(length, leadingBit ? 0x80 : 0x00, output);
851  if ((idx + length) > MAX_RSA_INT_SZ)
852  return BUFFER_E;
853 
854  err = wc_Rsa_to_unsigned_bin(n, output + idx, length);
855  if (err != MP_OKAY)
856  return MP_TO_E;
857  idx += length;
858 
859  return idx;
860 }
861 #endif /* !NO_RSA && (WOLFSSL_CERT_GEN || (WOLFSSL_KEY_GEN &&
862  !HAVE_USER_RSA))) */
863 
864 /* Windows header clash for WinCE using GetVersion */
865 WOLFSSL_LOCAL int GetMyVersion(const byte* input, word32* inOutIdx,
866  int* version, word32 maxIdx)
867 {
868  word32 idx = *inOutIdx;
869 
870  if ((idx + MIN_VERSION_SZ) > maxIdx)
871  return ASN_PARSE_E;
872 
873  if (input[idx++] != ASN_INTEGER)
874  return ASN_PARSE_E;
875 
876  if (input[idx++] != 0x01)
877  return ASN_VERSION_E;
878 
879  *version = input[idx++];
880  *inOutIdx = idx;
881 
882  return *version;
883 }
884 
885 
886 #ifndef NO_PWDBASED
887 /* Get small count integer, 32 bits or less */
888 int GetShortInt(const byte* input, word32* inOutIdx, int* number, word32 maxIdx)
889 {
890  word32 idx = *inOutIdx;
891  word32 len;
892 
893  *number = 0;
894 
895  /* check for type and length bytes */
896  if ((idx + 2) > maxIdx)
897  return BUFFER_E;
898 
899  if (input[idx++] != ASN_INTEGER)
900  return ASN_PARSE_E;
901 
902  len = input[idx++];
903  if (len > 4)
904  return ASN_PARSE_E;
905 
906  if (len + idx > maxIdx)
907  return ASN_PARSE_E;
908 
909  while (len--) {
910  *number = *number << 8 | input[idx++];
911  }
912 
913  *inOutIdx = idx;
914 
915  return *number;
916 }
917 #endif /* !NO_PWDBASED */
918 
919 /* May not have one, not an error */
920 static int GetExplicitVersion(const byte* input, word32* inOutIdx, int* version,
921  word32 maxIdx)
922 {
923  word32 idx = *inOutIdx;
924 
925  WOLFSSL_ENTER("GetExplicitVersion");
926 
927  if ((idx + 1) > maxIdx)
928  return BUFFER_E;
929 
930  if (input[idx++] == (ASN_CONTEXT_SPECIFIC | ASN_CONSTRUCTED)) {
931  *inOutIdx = ++idx; /* skip header */
932  return GetMyVersion(input, inOutIdx, version, maxIdx);
933  }
934 
935  /* go back as is */
936  *version = 0;
937 
938  return 0;
939 }
940 
941 int GetInt(mp_int* mpi, const byte* input, word32* inOutIdx, word32 maxIdx)
942 {
943  word32 idx = *inOutIdx;
944  int ret;
945  int length;
946 
947  ret = GetASNInt(input, &idx, &length, maxIdx);
948  if (ret != 0)
949  return ret;
950 
951  if (mp_init(mpi) != MP_OKAY)
952  return MP_INIT_E;
953 
954  if (mp_read_unsigned_bin(mpi, (byte*)input + idx, length) != 0) {
955  mp_clear(mpi);
956  return ASN_GETINT_E;
957  }
958 
959 #ifdef HAVE_WOLF_BIGINT
960  if (wc_bigint_from_unsigned_bin(&mpi->raw, input + idx, length) != 0) {
961  mp_clear(mpi);
962  return ASN_GETINT_E;
963  }
964 #endif /* HAVE_WOLF_BIGINT */
965 
966  *inOutIdx = idx + length;
967 
968  return 0;
969 }
970 
971 static int CheckBitString(const byte* input, word32* inOutIdx, int* len,
972  word32 maxIdx, int zeroBits, byte* unusedBits)
973 {
974  word32 idx = *inOutIdx;
975  int length;
976  byte b;
977 
978  if ((idx + 1) > maxIdx)
979  return BUFFER_E;
980 
981  if (input[idx++] != ASN_BIT_STRING)
982  return ASN_BITSTR_E;
983 
984  if (GetLength(input, &idx, &length, maxIdx) < 0)
985  return ASN_PARSE_E;
986 
987  /* extra sanity check that length is greater than 0 */
988  if (length <= 0) {
989  WOLFSSL_MSG("Error length was 0 in CheckBitString");
990  return BUFFER_E;
991  }
992 
993  if (idx + 1 > maxIdx) {
994  WOLFSSL_MSG("Attempted buffer read larger than input buffer");
995  return BUFFER_E;
996  }
997 
998  b = input[idx];
999  if (zeroBits && b != 0x00)
1000  return ASN_EXPECT_0_E;
1001  if (b >= 0x08)
1002  return ASN_PARSE_E;
1003  if (b != 0) {
1004  if ((byte)(input[idx + length - 1] << (8 - b)) != 0)
1005  return ASN_PARSE_E;
1006  }
1007  idx++;
1008  length--; /* length has been checked for greater than 0 */
1009 
1010  *inOutIdx = idx;
1011  if (len != NULL)
1012  *len = length;
1013  if (unusedBits != NULL)
1014  *unusedBits = b;
1015 
1016  return 0;
1017 }
1018 
1019 #if (!defined(NO_RSA) && (defined(WOLFSSL_CERT_GEN) || \
1020  (defined(WOLFSSL_KEY_GEN) && \
1021  !defined(HAVE_USER_RSA)))) || \
1022  (defined(HAVE_ECC) && (defined(WOLFSSL_CERT_GEN) || \
1023  defined(WOLFSSL_KEY_GEN)))
1024 /* Set the DER/BER encoding of the ASN.1 BIT_STRING header.
1025  *
1026  * len Length of data to encode.
1027  * unusedBits The number of unused bits in the last byte of data.
1028  * That is, the number of least significant zero bits before a one.
1029  * The last byte is the most-significant non-zero byte of a number.
1030  * output Buffer to write into.
1031  * returns the number of bytes added to the buffer.
1032  */
1033 static word32 SetBitString(word32 len, byte unusedBits, byte* output)
1034 {
1035  word32 idx = 0;
1036 
1037  output[idx++] = ASN_BIT_STRING;
1038  idx += SetLength(len + 1, output + idx);
1039  output[idx++] = unusedBits;
1040 
1041  return idx;
1042 }
1043 
1044 #ifdef WOLFSSL_CERT_EXT
1045 /* Set the DER/BER encoding of the ASN.1 BIT_STRING with a 16-bit value.
1046  *
1047  * val 16-bit value to encode.
1048  * output Buffer to write into.
1049  * returns the number of bytes added to the buffer.
1050  */
1051 static word32 SetBitString16Bit(word16 val, byte* output)
1052 {
1053  word32 idx;
1054  int len;
1055  byte lastByte;
1056  byte unusedBits = 0;
1057 
1058  if ((val >> 8) != 0) {
1059  len = 2;
1060  lastByte = (byte)(val >> 8);
1061  }
1062  else {
1063  len = 1;
1064  lastByte = (byte)val;
1065  }
1066 
1067  while (((lastByte >> unusedBits) & 0x01) == 0x00)
1068  unusedBits++;
1069 
1070  idx = SetBitString(len, unusedBits, output);
1071  output[idx++] = (byte)val;
1072  output[idx++] = (byte)(val >> 8);
1073 
1074  return idx;
1075 }
1076 #endif /* WOLFSSL_CERT_EXT */
1077 #endif /* !NO_RSA && (WOLFSSL_CERT_GEN || (WOLFSSL_KEY_GEN &&
1078  !HAVE_USER_RSA)) */

1195 static const byte* OidFromId(word32 id, word32 type, word32* oidSz)
1196 {
1197  const byte* oid = NULL;
1198 
1199  *oidSz = 0;
1200 
1201  switch (type) {
1202 
1203  case oidHashType:
1204  switch (id) {
1205  case MD2h:
1206  oid = hashMd2hOid;
1207  *oidSz = sizeof(hashMd2hOid);
1208  break;
1209  case MD5h:
1210  oid = hashMd5hOid;
1211  *oidSz = sizeof(hashMd5hOid);
1212  break;
1213  case SHAh:
1214  oid = hashSha1hOid;
1215  *oidSz = sizeof(hashSha1hOid);
1216  break;
1217  case SHA224h:
1218  oid = hashSha224hOid;
1219  *oidSz = sizeof(hashSha224hOid);
1220  break;
1221  case SHA256h:
1222  oid = hashSha256hOid;
1223  *oidSz = sizeof(hashSha256hOid);
1224  break;
1225  case SHA384h:
1226  oid = hashSha384hOid;
1227  *oidSz = sizeof(hashSha384hOid);
1228  break;
1229  case SHA512h:
1230  oid = hashSha512hOid;
1231  *oidSz = sizeof(hashSha512hOid);
1232  break;
1233  }
1234  break;
1235 
1236  case oidSigType:
1237  switch (id) {
1238  #ifndef NO_DSA
1239  case CTC_SHAwDSA:
1240  oid = sigSha1wDsaOid;
1241  *oidSz = sizeof(sigSha1wDsaOid);
1242  break;
1243  #endif /* NO_DSA */
1244  #ifndef NO_RSA
1245  case CTC_MD2wRSA:
1246  oid = sigMd2wRsaOid;
1247  *oidSz = sizeof(sigMd2wRsaOid);
1248  break;
1249  case CTC_MD5wRSA:
1250  oid = sigMd5wRsaOid;
1251  *oidSz = sizeof(sigMd5wRsaOid);
1252  break;
1253  case CTC_SHAwRSA:
1254  oid = sigSha1wRsaOid;
1255  *oidSz = sizeof(sigSha1wRsaOid);
1256  break;
1257  case CTC_SHA224wRSA:
1258  oid = sigSha224wRsaOid;
1259  *oidSz = sizeof(sigSha224wRsaOid);
1260  break;
1261  case CTC_SHA256wRSA:
1262  oid = sigSha256wRsaOid;
1263  *oidSz = sizeof(sigSha256wRsaOid);
1264  break;
1265  case CTC_SHA384wRSA:
1266  oid = sigSha384wRsaOid;
1267  *oidSz = sizeof(sigSha384wRsaOid);
1268  break;
1269  case CTC_SHA512wRSA:
1270  oid = sigSha512wRsaOid;
1271  *oidSz = sizeof(sigSha512wRsaOid);
1272  break;
1273  #endif /* NO_RSA */
1274  #ifdef HAVE_ECC
1275  case CTC_SHAwECDSA:

1552 #ifdef HAVE_OID_ENCODING
1553 int EncodeObjectId(const word16* in, word32 inSz, byte* out, word32* outSz)
1554 {
1555  int i, x, len;
1556  word32 d, t;
1557 
1558  /* check args */
1559  if (in == NULL || outSz == NULL) {
1560  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
1561  }
1562 
1563  /* compute length of encoded OID */
1564  d = (in[0] * 40) + in[1];
1565  len = 0;
1566  for (i = 1; i < (int)inSz; i++) {
1567  x = 0;
1568  t = d;
1569  while (t) {
1570  x++;
1571  t >>= 1;
1572  }
1573  len += (x / 7) + ((x % 7) ? 1 : 0) + (d == 0 ? 1 : 0);
1574 
1575  if (i < (int)inSz - 1) {
1576  d = in[i + 1];
1577  }
1578  }
1579 
1580  if (out) {
1581  /* verify length */
1582  if ((int)*outSz < len) {
1583  return BUFFER_E; /* buffer provided is not large enough */
1584  }
1585 
1586  /* calc first byte */
1587  d = (in[0] * 40) + in[1];
1588 
1589  /* encode bytes */
1590  x = 0;
1591  for (i = 1; i < (int)inSz; i++) {
1592  if (d) {
1593  int y = x, z;
1594  byte mask = 0;
1595  while (d) {
1596  out[x++] = (byte)((d & 0x7F) | mask);
1597  d >>= 7;
1598  mask |= 0x80; /* upper bit is set on all but the last byte */
1599  }
1600  /* now swap bytes y...x-1 */
1601  z = x - 1;
1602  while (y < z) {
1603  mask = out[y];
1604  out[y] = out[z];
1605  out[z] = mask;
1606  ++y;
1607  --z;
1608  }
1609  }
1610  else {
1611  out[x++] = 0x00; /* zero value */
1612  }
1613 
1614  /* next word */
1615  if (i < (int)inSz - 1) {
1616  d = in[i + 1];
1617  }
1618  }
1619  }
1620 
1621  /* return length */
1622  *outSz = len;
1623 
1624  return 0;
1625 }
1626 #endif /* HAVE_OID_ENCODING */
1627 
1628 #ifdef HAVE_OID_DECODING
1629 int DecodeObjectId(const byte* in, word32 inSz, word16* out, word32* outSz)
1630 {
1631  int x = 0, y = 0;
1632  word32 t = 0;
1633 
1634  /* check args */
1635  if (in == NULL || outSz == NULL) {
1636  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
1637  }
1638 
1639  /* decode bytes */
1640  while (inSz--) {
1641  t = (t << 7) | (in[x] & 0x7F);
1642  if (!(in[x] & 0x80)) {
1643  if (y >= (int)*outSz) {
1644  return BUFFER_E;
1645  }
1646  if (y == 0) {
1647  out[0] = (t / 40);
1648  out[1] = (t % 40);
1649  y = 2;
1650  }
1651  else {
1652  out[y++] = t;
1653  }
1654  t = 0; /* reset tmp */
1655  }
1656  x++;
1657  }
1658 
1659  /* return length */
1660  *outSz = y;
1661 
1662  return 0;
1663 }
1664 #endif /* HAVE_OID_DECODING */
1665 
1666 /* Get the DER/BER encoding of an ASN.1 OBJECT_ID header.
1667  *
1668  * input Buffer holding DER/BER encoded data.
1669  * inOutIdx Current index into buffer to parse.
1670  * len The number of bytes in the ASN.1 data.
1671  * maxIdx Length of data in buffer.
1672  * returns BUFFER_E when there is not enough data to parse.
1673  * ASN_OBJECt_ID_E when the OBJECT_ID tag is not found.
1674  * ASN_PARSE_E when length is invalid.
1675  * Otherwise, 0 to indicate success.
1676  */
1677 static int GetASNObjectId(const byte* input, word32* inOutIdx, int* len,
1678  word32 maxIdx)
1679 {
1680  word32 idx = *inOutIdx;
1681  byte b;
1682  int length;
1683 
1684  if ((idx + 1) > maxIdx)
1685  return BUFFER_E;
1686 
1687  b = input[idx++];
1688  if (b != ASN_OBJECT_ID)
1689  return ASN_OBJECT_ID_E;
1690 
1691  if (GetLength(input, &idx, &length, maxIdx) < 0)
1692  return ASN_PARSE_E;
1693 
1694  *len = length;
1695  *inOutIdx = idx;
1696  return 0;
1697 }
1698 
1699 /* Set the DER/BER encoding of the ASN.1 OBJECT_ID header.
1700  *
1701  * len Length of the OBJECT_ID data.
1702  * output Buffer to write into.
1703  * returns the number of bytes added to the buffer.
1704  */
1705 static int SetObjectId(int len, byte* output)
1706 {
1707  int idx = 0;
1708 
1709  output[idx++] = ASN_OBJECT_ID;
1710  idx += SetLength(len, output + idx);
1711 
1712  return idx;
1713 }
1714 
1715 int GetObjectId(const byte* input, word32* inOutIdx, word32* oid,
1716  word32 oidType, word32 maxIdx)
1717 {
1718  int ret = 0, length;
1719  word32 idx = *inOutIdx;
1720 #ifndef NO_VERIFY_OID
1721  word32 actualOidSz = 0;
1722  const byte* actualOid;
1723 #endif /* NO_VERIFY_OID */
1724 
1725  (void)oidType;
1726  WOLFSSL_ENTER("GetObjectId()");
1727  *oid = 0;
1728 
1729  ret = GetASNObjectId(input, &idx, &length, maxIdx);
1730  if (ret != 0)
1731  return ret;
1732 
1733 #ifndef NO_VERIFY_OID
1734  actualOid = &input[idx];
1735  if (length > 0)
1736  actualOidSz = (word32)length;
1737 #endif /* NO_VERIFY_OID */
1738 
1739  while (length--) {
1740  /* odd HC08 compiler behavior here when input[idx++] */
1741  *oid += (word32)input[idx];
1742  idx++;
1743  }
1744  /* just sum it up for now */
1745 
1746  *inOutIdx = idx;
1747 
1748 #ifndef NO_VERIFY_OID
1749  {
1750  const byte* checkOid = NULL;
1751  word32 checkOidSz;
1752  #ifdef ASN_DUMP_OID
1753  int i;
1754  #endif
1755 
1756  if (oidType != oidIgnoreType) {
1757  checkOid = OidFromId(*oid, oidType, &checkOidSz);
1758 
1759  #ifdef ASN_DUMP_OID
1760  /* support for dumping OID information */
1761  printf("OID (Type %d, Sz %d, Sum %d): ", oidType, actualOidSz, *oid);
1762  for (i=0; i<actualOidSz; i++) {
1763  printf("%d, ", actualOid[i]);
1764  }
1765  printf("\n");
1766  #ifdef HAVE_OID_DECODING
1767  {
1768  word16 decOid[16];
1769  word32 decOidSz = sizeof(decOid);
1770  ret = DecodeObjectId(actualOid, actualOidSz, decOid, &decOidSz);
1771  if (ret == 0) {
1772  printf(" Decoded (Sz %d): ", decOidSz);
1773  for (i=0; i<decOidSz; i++) {
1774  printf("%d.", decOid[i]);
1775  }
1776  printf("\n");
1777  }
1778  else {
1779  printf("DecodeObjectId failed: %d\n", ret);
1780  }
1781  }
1782  #endif /* HAVE_OID_DECODING */
1783  #endif /* ASN_DUMP_OID */
1784 
1785  if (checkOid != NULL &&
1786  (checkOidSz != actualOidSz ||
1787  XMEMCMP(actualOid, checkOid, checkOidSz) != 0)) {
1788  WOLFSSL_MSG("OID Check Failed");
1789  return ASN_UNKNOWN_OID_E;
1790  }
1791  }
1792  }
1793 #endif /* NO_VERIFY_OID */
1794 
1795  return ret;
1796 }
1797 
1798 static int SkipObjectId(const byte* input, word32* inOutIdx, word32 maxIdx)
1799 {
1800  word32 idx = *inOutIdx;
1801  int length;
1802  int ret;
1803 
1804  ret = GetASNObjectId(input, &idx, &length, maxIdx);
1805  if (ret != 0)
1806  return ret;
1807 
1808  idx += length;
1809  *inOutIdx = idx;
1810 
1811  return 0;
1812 }

1814 WOLFSSL_LOCAL int GetAlgoId(const byte* input, word32* inOutIdx, word32* oid,
1815  word32 oidType, word32 maxIdx)
1816 {
1817  int length;
1818  word32 idx = *inOutIdx;
1819  int ret;
1820  *oid = 0;
1821 
1822  WOLFSSL_ENTER("GetAlgoId");
1823 
1824  if (GetSequence(input, &idx, &length, maxIdx) < 0)
1825  return ASN_PARSE_E;
1826 
1827  if (GetObjectId(input, &idx, oid, oidType, maxIdx) < 0)
1828  return ASN_OBJECT_ID_E;
1829 
1830  /* could have NULL tag and 0 terminator, but may not */
1831  if (input[idx] == ASN_TAG_NULL) {
1832  ret = GetASNNull(input, &idx, maxIdx);
1833  if (ret != 0)
1834  return ret;
1835  }
1836 
1837  *inOutIdx = idx;
1838 
1839  return 0;
1840 }

1842 #ifndef NO_RSA
1843 
1844 #ifndef HAVE_USER_RSA
1845 int wc_RsaPrivateKeyDecode(const byte* input, word32* inOutIdx, RsaKey* key,
1846  word32 inSz)
1847 {
1848  int version, length;
1849 
1850  if (inOutIdx == NULL) {
1851  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
1852  }
1853  if (GetSequence(input, inOutIdx, &length, inSz) < 0)
1854  return ASN_PARSE_E;
1855 
1856  if (GetMyVersion(input, inOutIdx, &version, inSz) < 0)
1857  return ASN_PARSE_E;
1858 
1859  key->type = RSA_PRIVATE;
1860 
1861  if (GetInt(&key->n, input, inOutIdx, inSz) < 0 ||
1862  GetInt(&key->e, input, inOutIdx, inSz) < 0 ||
1863  GetInt(&key->d, input, inOutIdx, inSz) < 0 ||
1864  GetInt(&key->p, input, inOutIdx, inSz) < 0 ||
1865  GetInt(&key->q, input, inOutIdx, inSz) < 0 ||
1866  GetInt(&key->dP, input, inOutIdx, inSz) < 0 ||
1867  GetInt(&key->dQ, input, inOutIdx, inSz) < 0 ||
1868  GetInt(&key->u, input, inOutIdx, inSz) < 0 ) return ASN_RSA_KEY_E;
1869 
1870 #ifdef WOLFSSL_XILINX_CRYPT
1871  if (wc_InitRsaHw(key) != 0) {
1872  return BAD_STATE_E;
1873  }
1874 #endif
1875 
1876  return 0;
1877 }
1878 #endif /* HAVE_USER_RSA */
1879 #endif /* NO_RSA */

1881 /* Remove PKCS8 header, place inOutIdx at beginning of traditional,
1882  * return traditional length on success, negative on error */
1883 int ToTraditionalInline(const byte* input, word32* inOutIdx, word32 sz)
1884 {
1885  word32 idx, oid;
1886  int version, length;
1887  int ret;
1888 
1889  if (input == NULL || inOutIdx == NULL)
1890  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
1891 
1892  idx = *inOutIdx;
1893 
1894  if (GetSequence(input, &idx, &length, sz) < 0)
1895  return ASN_PARSE_E;
1896 
1897  if (GetMyVersion(input, &idx, &version, sz) < 0)
1898  return ASN_PARSE_E;
1899 
1900  if (GetAlgoId(input, &idx, &oid, oidKeyType, sz) < 0)
1901  return ASN_PARSE_E;
1902 
1903  if (input[idx] == ASN_OBJECT_ID) {
1904  if (SkipObjectId(input, &idx, sz) < 0)
1905  return ASN_PARSE_E;
1906  }
1907 
1908  ret = GetOctetString(input, &idx, &length, sz);
1909  if (ret < 0)
1910  return ret;
1911 
1912  *inOutIdx = idx;
1913 
1914  return length;
1915 }
1916 
1917 /* Remove PKCS8 header, move beginning of traditional to beginning of input */
1918 int ToTraditional(byte* input, word32 sz)
1919 {
1920  word32 inOutIdx = 0;
1921  int length;
1922 
1923  if (input == NULL)
1924  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
1925 
1926  length = ToTraditionalInline(input, &inOutIdx, sz);
1927  if (length < 0)
1928  return length;
1929 
1930  XMEMMOVE(input, input + inOutIdx, length);
1931 
1932  return length;
1933 }

1936 /* find beginning of traditional key inside PKCS#8 unencrypted buffer
1937  * return traditional length on success, with inOutIdx at beginning of
1938  * traditional
1939  * return negative on failure/error */
1940 int wc_GetPkcs8TraditionalOffset(byte* input, word32* inOutIdx, word32 sz)
1941 {
1942  int length;
1943 
1944  if (input == NULL || inOutIdx == NULL || (*inOutIdx > sz))
1945  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
1946 
1947  length = ToTraditionalInline(input, inOutIdx, sz);
1948 
1949  return length;
1950 }

1953 /* PKCS#8 from RFC 5208
1954  * This function takes in a DER key and converts it to PKCS#8 format. Used
1955  * in creating PKCS#12 shrouded key bags.
1956  * Reverse of ToTraditional
1957  *
1958  * PrivateKeyInfo ::= SEQUENCE {
1959  * version Version,
1960  * privateKeyAlgorithm PrivateKeyAlgorithmIdentifier,
1961  * privateKey PrivateKey,
1962  * attributes optional
1963  * }
1964  * Version ::= INTEGER
1965  * PrivateKeyAlgorithmIdentifier ::= AlgorithmIdentifier
1966  * PrivateKey ::= OCTET STRING
1967  *
1968  * out buffer to place result in
1969  * outSz size of out buffer
1970  * key buffer with DER key
1971  * keySz size of key buffer
1972  * algoID algorithm ID i.e. RSAk
1973  * curveOID ECC curve oid if used. Should be NULL for RSA keys.
1974  * oidSz size of curve oid. Is set to 0 if curveOID is NULL.
1975  *
1976  * Returns the size of PKCS#8 placed into out. In error cases returns negative
1977  * values.
1978  */
1979 int wc_CreatePKCS8Key(byte* out, word32* outSz, byte* key, word32 keySz,
1980  int algoID, const byte* curveOID, word32 oidSz)
1981 {
1982  word32 keyIdx = 0;
1983  word32 tmpSz = 0;
1984  word32 sz;
1985 
1986 
1987  /* If out is NULL then return the max size needed
1988  * + 2 for ASN_OBJECT_ID and ASN_OCTET_STRING tags */
1989  if (out == NULL && outSz != NULL) {
1990  *outSz = keySz + MAX_SEQ_SZ + MAX_VERSION_SZ + MAX_ALGO_SZ
1991  + MAX_LENGTH_SZ + MAX_LENGTH_SZ + 2;
1992 
1993  if (curveOID != NULL)
1994  *outSz += oidSz + MAX_LENGTH_SZ + 1;
1995 
1996  WOLFSSL_MSG("Checking size of PKCS8");
1997 
1998  return LENGTH_ONLY_E;
1999  }
2000 
2001  WOLFSSL_ENTER("wc_CreatePKCS8Key()");
2002 
2003  if (key == NULL || out == NULL || outSz == NULL) {
2004  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
2005  }
2006 
2007  /* check the buffer has enough room for largest possible size */
2008  if (curveOID != NULL) {
2009  if (*outSz < (keySz + MAX_SEQ_SZ + MAX_VERSION_SZ + MAX_ALGO_SZ
2010  + MAX_LENGTH_SZ + MAX_LENGTH_SZ + 3 + oidSz + MAX_LENGTH_SZ))
2011  return BUFFER_E;
2012  }
2013  else {
2014  oidSz = 0; /* with no curveOID oid size must be 0 */
2015  if (*outSz < (keySz + MAX_SEQ_SZ + MAX_VERSION_SZ + MAX_ALGO_SZ
2016  + MAX_LENGTH_SZ + MAX_LENGTH_SZ + 2))
2017  return BUFFER_E;
2018  }
2019 
2020  /* PrivateKeyInfo ::= SEQUENCE */
2021  keyIdx += MAX_SEQ_SZ; /* save room for sequence */
2022 
2023  /* version Version
2024  * no header information just INTEGER */
2025  sz = SetMyVersion(PKCS8v0, out + keyIdx, 0);
2026  tmpSz += sz; keyIdx += sz;
2027 
2028  /* privateKeyAlgorithm PrivateKeyAlgorithmIdentifier */
2029  sz = 0; /* set sz to 0 and get privateKey oid buffer size needed */
2030  if (curveOID != NULL && oidSz > 0) {
2031  byte buf[MAX_LENGTH_SZ];
2032  sz = SetLength(oidSz, buf);
2033  sz += 1; /* plus one for ASN object id */
2034  }
2035  sz = SetAlgoID(algoID, out + keyIdx, oidKeyType, oidSz + sz);
2036  tmpSz += sz; keyIdx += sz;
2037 
2038  /* privateKey PrivateKey *
2039  * pkcs8 ecc uses slightly different format. Places curve oid in
2040  * buffer */
2041  if (curveOID != NULL && oidSz > 0) {
2042  sz = SetObjectId(oidSz, out + keyIdx);
2043  keyIdx += sz; tmpSz += sz;
2044  XMEMCPY(out + keyIdx, curveOID, oidSz);
2045  keyIdx += oidSz; tmpSz += oidSz;
2046  }
2047 
2048  sz = SetOctetString(keySz, out + keyIdx);
2049  keyIdx += sz; tmpSz += sz;
2050  XMEMCPY(out + keyIdx, key, keySz);
2051  tmpSz += keySz;
2052 
2053  /* attributes optional
2054  * No attributes currently added */
2055 
2056  /* rewind and add sequence */
2057  sz = SetSequence(tmpSz, out);
2058  XMEMMOVE(out + sz, out + MAX_SEQ_SZ, tmpSz);
2059 
2060  return tmpSz + sz;
2061 }
2062 
2063 
2064 /* check that the private key is a pair for the public key in certificate
2065  * return 1 (true) on match
2066  * return 0 or negative value on failure/error
2067  *
2068  * key : buffer holding DER fromat key
2069  * keySz : size of key buffer
2070  * der : a initialized and parsed DecodedCert holding a certificate */
2071 int wc_CheckPrivateKey(byte* key, word32 keySz, DecodedCert* der)
2072 {
2073  int ret;
2074 
2075  if (key == NULL || der == NULL) {
2076  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
2077  }
2078 
2079  #if !defined(NO_RSA)
2080  /* test if RSA key */
2081  if (der->keyOID == RSAk) {
2082  RsaKey a, b;
2083  word32 keyIdx = 0;
2084 
2085  if ((ret = wc_InitRsaKey(&a, NULL)) < 0)
2086  return ret;
2087  if ((ret = wc_InitRsaKey(&b, NULL)) < 0) {
2088  wc_FreeRsaKey(&a);
2089  return ret;
2090  }
2091  if ((ret = wc_RsaPrivateKeyDecode(key, &keyIdx, &a, keySz)) == 0) {
2092  WOLFSSL_MSG("Checking RSA key pair");
2093  keyIdx = 0; /* reset to 0 for parsing public key */
2094 
2095  if ((ret = wc_RsaPublicKeyDecode(der->publicKey, &keyIdx, &b,
2096  der->pubKeySize)) == 0) {
2097  /* limit for user RSA crypto because of RsaKey
2098  * dereference. */
2099  #if defined(HAVE_USER_RSA)
2100  WOLFSSL_MSG("Cannot verify RSA pair with user RSA");
2101  ret = 1; /* return first RSA cert as match */
2102  #else
2103  /* both keys extracted successfully now check n and e
2104  * values are the same. This is dereferencing RsaKey */
2105  if (mp_cmp(&(a.n), &(b.n)) != MP_EQ ||
2106  mp_cmp(&(a.e), &(b.e)) != MP_EQ) {
2107  ret = MP_CMP_E;
2108  }
2109  else
2110  ret = 1;
2111  #endif
2112  }
2113  }
2114  wc_FreeRsaKey(&b);
2115  wc_FreeRsaKey(&a);
2116  }
2117  else
2118  #endif /* NO_RSA */
2119 
2120  #ifdef HAVE_ECC
2121  if (der->keyOID == ECDSAk) {
2122  word32 keyIdx = 0;
2123  ecc_key key_pair;
2124 
2125  if ((ret = wc_ecc_init(&key_pair)) < 0)
2126  return ret;
2127  if ((ret = wc_EccPrivateKeyDecode(key, &keyIdx, &key_pair,
2128  keySz)) == 0) {
2129  WOLFSSL_MSG("Checking ECC key pair");
2130  keyIdx = 0;
2131  if ((ret = wc_ecc_import_x963(der->publicKey, der->pubKeySize,
2132  &key_pair)) == 0) {
2133  /* public and private extracted successfuly no check if is
2134  * a pair and also do sanity checks on key. wc_ecc_check_key
2135  * checks that private * base generator equals pubkey */
2136  if ((ret = wc_ecc_check_key(&key_pair)) == 0)
2137  ret = 1;
2138  }
2139  }
2140  wc_ecc_free(&key_pair);
2141  }
2142  else
2143  #endif /* HAVE_ECC */
2144 
2145  #ifdef HAVE_ED25519
2146  if (der->keyOID == ED25519k) {
2147  word32 keyIdx = 0;
2148  ed25519_key key_pair;
2149 
2150  if ((ret = wc_ed25519_init(&key_pair)) < 0)
2151  return ret;
2152  if ((ret = wc_Ed25519PrivateKeyDecode(key, &keyIdx, &key_pair,
2153  keySz)) == 0) {
2154  WOLFSSL_MSG("Checking ED25519 key pair");
2155  keyIdx = 0;
2156  if ((ret = wc_ed25519_import_public(der->publicKey, der->pubKeySize,
2157  &key_pair)) == 0) {
2158  /* public and private extracted successfuly no check if is
2159  * a pair and also do sanity checks on key. wc_ecc_check_key
2160  * checks that private * base generator equals pubkey */
2161  if ((ret = wc_ed25519_check_key(&key_pair)) == 0)
2162  ret = 1;
2163  }
2164  }
2165  wc_ed25519_free(&key_pair);
2166  }
2167  else
2168  #endif
2169  {
2170  ret = 0;
2171  }
2172 
2173  return ret;
2174 }
2175 
2176 #ifndef NO_PWDBASED
2177 
2178 /* Check To see if PKCS version algo is supported, set id if it is return 0
2179  < 0 on error */
2180 static int CheckAlgo(int first, int second, int* id, int* version)
2181 {
2182  *id = ALGO_ID_E;
2183  *version = PKCS5; /* default */
2184 
2185  if (first == 1) {
2186  switch (second) {
2187  case 1:
2188  *id = PBE_SHA1_RC4_128;
2189  *version = PKCS12v1;
2190  return 0;
2191  case 3:
2192  *id = PBE_SHA1_DES3;
2193  *version = PKCS12v1;
2194  return 0;
2195  default:
2196  return ALGO_ID_E;
2197  }
2198  }
2199 
2200  if (first != PKCS5)
2201  return ASN_INPUT_E; /* VERSION ERROR */
2202 
2203  if (second == PBES2) {
2204  *version = PKCS5v2;
2205  return 0;
2206  }
2207 
2208  switch (second) {
2209  case 3: /* see RFC 2898 for ids */
2210  *id = PBE_MD5_DES;
2211  return 0;
2212  case 10:
2213  *id = PBE_SHA1_DES;
2214  return 0;
2215  default:
2216  return ALGO_ID_E;
2217 
2218  }
2219 }
2220 
2221 
2222 /* Check To see if PKCS v2 algo is supported, set id if it is return 0
2223  < 0 on error */
2224 static int CheckAlgoV2(int oid, int* id)
2225 {
2226  switch (oid) {
2227  case 69:
2228  *id = PBE_SHA1_DES;
2229  return 0;
2230  case 652:
2231  *id = PBE_SHA1_DES3;
2232  return 0;
2233  default:
2234  return ALGO_ID_E;
2235 
2236  }
2237 }

2239 
2240 /* Decrypt input in place from parameters based on id */
2241 static int DecryptKey(const char* password, int passwordSz, byte* salt,
2242  int saltSz, int iterations, int id, byte* input,
2243  int length, int version, byte* cbcIv)
2244 {
2245  int typeH;
2246  int derivedLen;
2247  int decryptionType;
2248  int ret = 0;
2249 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
2250  byte* key;
2251 #else
2252  byte key[MAX_KEY_SIZE];
2253 #endif
2254 
2255  (void)input;
2256  (void)length;
2257 
2258  switch (id) {
2259  case PBE_MD5_DES:
2260  typeH = MD5;
2261  derivedLen = 16; /* may need iv for v1.5 */
2262  decryptionType = DES_TYPE;
2263  break;
2264 
2265  case PBE_SHA1_DES:
2266  typeH = SHA;
2267  derivedLen = 16; /* may need iv for v1.5 */
2268  decryptionType = DES_TYPE;
2269  break;
2270 
2271  case PBE_SHA1_DES3:
2272  typeH = SHA;
2273  derivedLen = 32; /* may need iv for v1.5 */
2274  decryptionType = DES3_TYPE;
2275  break;
2276 
2277  case PBE_SHA1_RC4_128:
2278  typeH = SHA;
2279  derivedLen = 16;
2280  decryptionType = RC4_TYPE;
2281  break;
2282 
2283  default:
2284  return ALGO_ID_E;
2285  }
2286 
2287 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
2288  key = (byte*)XMALLOC(MAX_KEY_SIZE, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
2289  if (key == NULL)
2290  return MEMORY_E;
2291 #endif
2292 
2293  if (version == PKCS5v2)
2294  ret = wc_PBKDF2(key, (byte*)password, passwordSz,
2295  salt, saltSz, iterations, derivedLen, typeH);
2296 #ifndef NO_SHA
2297  else if (version == PKCS5)
2298  ret = wc_PBKDF1(key, (byte*)password, passwordSz,
2299  salt, saltSz, iterations, derivedLen, typeH);
2300 #endif
2301  else if (version == PKCS12v1) {
2302  int i, idx = 0;
2303  byte unicodePasswd[MAX_UNICODE_SZ];
2304 
2305  if ( (passwordSz * 2 + 2) > (int)sizeof(unicodePasswd)) {
2306 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
2307  XFREE(key, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
2308 #endif
2309  return UNICODE_SIZE_E;
2310  }
2311 
2312  for (i = 0; i < passwordSz; i++) {
2313  unicodePasswd[idx++] = 0x00;
2314  unicodePasswd[idx++] = (byte)password[i];
2315  }
2316  /* add trailing NULL */
2317  unicodePasswd[idx++] = 0x00;
2318  unicodePasswd[idx++] = 0x00;
2319 
2320  ret = wc_PKCS12_PBKDF(key, unicodePasswd, idx, salt, saltSz,
2321  iterations, derivedLen, typeH, 1);
2322  if (decryptionType != RC4_TYPE)
2323  ret += wc_PKCS12_PBKDF(cbcIv, unicodePasswd, idx, salt, saltSz,
2324  iterations, 8, typeH, 2);
2325  }
2326  else {
2327 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
2328  XFREE(key, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
2329 #endif
2330  return ALGO_ID_E;
2331  }
2332 
2333  if (ret != 0) {
2334 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
2335  XFREE(key, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
2336 #endif
2337  return ret;
2338  }
2339 
2340  switch (decryptionType) {
2341 #ifndef NO_DES3
2342  case DES_TYPE:
2343  {
2344  Des dec;
2345  byte* desIv = key + 8;
2346 
2347  if (version == PKCS5v2 || version == PKCS12v1)
2348  desIv = cbcIv;
2349 
2350  ret = wc_Des_SetKey(&dec, key, desIv, DES_DECRYPTION);
2351  if (ret != 0) {
2352 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
2353  XFREE(key, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
2354 #endif
2355  return ret;
2356  }
2357 
2358  wc_Des_CbcDecrypt(&dec, input, input, length);
2359  break;
2360  }
2361 
2362  case DES3_TYPE:
2363  {
2364  Des3 dec;
2365  byte* desIv = key + 24;
2366 
2367  if (version == PKCS5v2 || version == PKCS12v1)
2368  desIv = cbcIv;
2369 
2370  ret = wc_Des3Init(&dec, NULL, INVALID_DEVID);
2371  if (ret != 0) {
2372 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
2373  XFREE(key, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
2374 #endif
2375  return ret;
2376  }
2377  ret = wc_Des3_SetKey(&dec, key, desIv, DES_DECRYPTION);
2378  if (ret != 0) {
2379 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
2380  XFREE(key, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
2381 #endif
2382  return ret;
2383  }
2384  ret = wc_Des3_CbcDecrypt(&dec, input, input, length);
2385  if (ret != 0) {
2386 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
2387  XFREE(key, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
2388 #endif
2389  return ret;
2390  }
2391  break;
2392  }
2393 #endif
2394 #ifndef NO_RC4
2395  case RC4_TYPE:
2396  {
2397  Arc4 dec;
2398 
2399  wc_Arc4SetKey(&dec, key, derivedLen);
2400  wc_Arc4Process(&dec, input, input, length);
2401  break;
2402  }
2403 #endif
2404 
2405  default:
2406 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
2407  XFREE(key, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
2408 #endif
2409  return ALGO_ID_E;
2410  }
2411 
2412 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
2413  XFREE(key, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
2414 #endif
2415 
2416  return 0;
2417 }
2418 
2419 
2420 int wc_GetKeyOID(byte* key, word32 keySz, const byte** curveOID, word32* oidSz,
2421  int* algoID, void* heap)
2422 {
2423  word32 tmpIdx = 0;
2424 #ifdef HAVE_ECC
2425  ecc_key ecc;
2426 #endif
2427 #ifndef NO_RSA
2428  RsaKey rsa;
2429 #endif
2430 #ifdef HAVE_ED25519
2431  ed25519_key ed25519;
2432 #endif
2433 
2434  if (algoID == NULL) {
2435  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
2436  }
2437  *algoID = 0;
2438 
2439 #ifndef NO_RSA
2440  if (wc_InitRsaKey(&rsa, heap) == 0) {
2441  if (wc_RsaPrivateKeyDecode(key, &tmpIdx, &rsa, keySz) == 0) {
2442  *algoID = RSAk;
2443  }
2444  else {
2445  WOLFSSL_MSG("Not RSA DER key");
2446  }
2447  wc_FreeRsaKey(&rsa);
2448  }
2449  else {
2450  WOLFSSL_MSG("GetKeyOID wc_InitRsaKey failed");
2451  }
2452 #endif /* NO_RSA */
2453 #ifdef HAVE_ECC
2454  if (*algoID != RSAk) {
2455  tmpIdx = 0;
2456  if (wc_ecc_init_ex(&ecc, heap, INVALID_DEVID) == 0) {
2457  if (wc_EccPrivateKeyDecode(key, &tmpIdx, &ecc, keySz) == 0) {
2458  *algoID = ECDSAk;
2459 
2460  /* sanity check on arguments */
2461  if (curveOID == NULL || oidSz == NULL) {
2462  WOLFSSL_MSG("Error getting ECC curve OID");
2463  wc_ecc_free(&ecc);
2464  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
2465  }
2466 
2467  /* now find oid */
2468  if (wc_ecc_get_oid(ecc.dp->oidSum, curveOID, oidSz) < 0) {
2469  WOLFSSL_MSG("Error getting ECC curve OID");
2470  wc_ecc_free(&ecc);
2471  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
2472  }
2473  }
2474  else {
2475  WOLFSSL_MSG("Not ECC DER key either");
2476  }
2477  wc_ecc_free(&ecc);
2478  }
2479  else {
2480  WOLFSSL_MSG("GetKeyOID wc_ecc_init_ex failed");
2481  }
2482  }
2483 #endif /* HAVE_ECC */
2484 #ifdef HAVE_ED25519
2485  if (*algoID != RSAk && *algoID != ECDSAk) {
2486  if (wc_ed25519_init(&ed25519) == 0) {
2487  if (wc_Ed25519PrivateKeyDecode(key, &tmpIdx, &ed25519, keySz)
2488  == 0) {
2489  *algoID = ED25519k;
2490  }
2491  else {
2492  WOLFSSL_MSG("Not ED25519 DER key");
2493  }
2494  wc_ed25519_free(&ed25519);
2495  }
2496  else {
2497  WOLFSSL_MSG("GetKeyOID wc_ed25519_init failed");
2498  }
2499  }
2500 #endif
2501 
2502  /* if flag is not set then is neither RSA or ECC key that could be
2503  * found */
2504  if (*algoID == 0) {
2505  WOLFSSL_MSG("Bad key DER or compile options");
2506  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
2507  }
2508 
2509  (void)curveOID;
2510  (void)oidSz;
2511 
2512  return 1;
2513 }

2516 /* Remove Encrypted PKCS8 header, move beginning of traditional to beginning
2517  of input */
2518 int ToTraditionalEnc(byte* input, word32 sz,const char* password,int passwordSz)
2519 {
2520  word32 inOutIdx = 0, oid;
2521  int ret = 0, first, second, length = 0, version, saltSz, id;
2522  int iterations = 0;
2523 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
2524  byte* salt = NULL;
2525  byte* cbcIv = NULL;
2526 #else
2527  byte salt[MAX_SALT_SIZE];
2528  byte cbcIv[MAX_IV_SIZE];
2529 #endif
2530 
2531  if (GetSequence(input, &inOutIdx, &length, sz) < 0) {
2532  ERROR_OUT(ASN_PARSE_E, exit_tte);
2533  }
2534 
2535  if (GetAlgoId(input, &inOutIdx, &oid, oidSigType, sz) < 0) {
2536  ERROR_OUT(ASN_PARSE_E, exit_tte);
2537  }
2538 
2539  first = input[inOutIdx - 2]; /* PKCS version always 2nd to last byte */
2540  second = input[inOutIdx - 1]; /* version.algo, algo id last byte */
2541 
2542  if (CheckAlgo(first, second, &id, &version) < 0) {
2543  ERROR_OUT(ASN_INPUT_E, exit_tte); /* Algo ID error */
2544  }
2545 
2546  if (version == PKCS5v2) {
2547  if (GetSequence(input, &inOutIdx, &length, sz) < 0) {
2548  ERROR_OUT(ASN_PARSE_E, exit_tte);
2549  }
2550 
2551  if (GetAlgoId(input, &inOutIdx, &oid, oidKdfType, sz) < 0) {
2552  ERROR_OUT(ASN_PARSE_E, exit_tte);
2553  }
2554 
2555  if (oid != PBKDF2_OID) {
2556  ERROR_OUT(ASN_PARSE_E, exit_tte);
2557  }
2558  }
2559 
2560  if (GetSequence(input, &inOutIdx, &length, sz) <= 0) {
2561  ERROR_OUT(ASN_PARSE_E, exit_tte);
2562  }
2563 
2564  ret = GetOctetString(input, &inOutIdx, &saltSz, sz);
2565  if (ret < 0)
2566  goto exit_tte;
2567 
2568  if (saltSz > MAX_SALT_SIZE) {
2569  ERROR_OUT(ASN_PARSE_E, exit_tte);
2570  }
2571 
2572 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
2573  salt = (byte*)XMALLOC(MAX_SALT_SIZE, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
2574  if (salt == NULL) {
2575  ERROR_OUT(MEMORY_E, exit_tte);
2576  }
2577 #endif
2578 
2579  XMEMCPY(salt, &input[inOutIdx], saltSz);
2580  inOutIdx += saltSz;
2581 
2582  if (GetShortInt(input, &inOutIdx, &iterations, sz) < 0) {
2583  ERROR_OUT(ASN_PARSE_E, exit_tte);
2584  }
2585 
2586 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
2587  cbcIv = (byte*)XMALLOC(MAX_IV_SIZE, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
2588  if (cbcIv == NULL) {
2589  ERROR_OUT(MEMORY_E, exit_tte);
2590  }
2591 #endif
2592 
2593  if (version == PKCS5v2) {
2594  /* get encryption algo */
2595  /* JOHN: New type. Need a little more research. */
2596  if (GetAlgoId(input, &inOutIdx, &oid, oidBlkType, sz) < 0) {
2597  ERROR_OUT(ASN_PARSE_E, exit_tte);
2598  }
2599 
2600  if (CheckAlgoV2(oid, &id) < 0) {
2601  ERROR_OUT(ASN_PARSE_E, exit_tte); /* PKCS v2 algo id error */
2602  }
2603 
2604  ret = GetOctetString(input, &inOutIdx, &length, sz);
2605  if (ret < 0)
2606  goto exit_tte;
2607 
2608  if (length > MAX_IV_SIZE) {
2609  ERROR_OUT(ASN_PARSE_E, exit_tte);
2610  }
2611 
2612  XMEMCPY(cbcIv, &input[inOutIdx], length);
2613  inOutIdx += length;
2614  }
2615 
2616  ret = GetOctetString(input, &inOutIdx, &length, sz);
2617  if (ret < 0)
2618  goto exit_tte;
2619 
2620  ret = DecryptKey(password, passwordSz, salt, saltSz, iterations, id,
2621  input + inOutIdx, length, version, cbcIv);
2622 
2623 exit_tte:
2624 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
2625  XFREE(salt, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
2626  XFREE(cbcIv, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
2627 #endif
2628 
2629  if (ret == 0) {
2630  XMEMMOVE(input, input + inOutIdx, length);
2631  ret = ToTraditional(input, length);
2632  }
2633 
2634  return ret;
2635 }
2636 
2637 /* decrypt PKCS */
2638 int DecryptContent(byte* input, word32 sz,const char* password,int passwordSz)
2639 {
2640  word32 inOutIdx = 0, oid;
2641  int ret = 0;
2642  int first, second, length = 0, version, saltSz, id;
2643  int iterations = 0;
2644 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
2645  byte* salt = NULL;
2646  byte* cbcIv = NULL;
2647 #else
2648  byte salt[MAX_SALT_SIZE];
2649  byte cbcIv[MAX_IV_SIZE];
2650 #endif
2651 
2652  if (GetAlgoId(input, &inOutIdx, &oid, oidSigType, sz) < 0) {
2653  ERROR_OUT(ASN_PARSE_E, exit_dc);
2654  }
2655 
2656  first = input[inOutIdx - 2]; /* PKCS version always 2nd to last byte */
2657  second = input[inOutIdx - 1]; /* version.algo, algo id last byte */
2658 
2659  if (CheckAlgo(first, second, &id, &version) < 0) {
2660  ERROR_OUT(ASN_INPUT_E, exit_dc); /* Algo ID error */
2661  }
2662 
2663  if (version == PKCS5v2) {
2664  if (GetSequence(input, &inOutIdx, &length, sz) < 0) {
2665  ERROR_OUT(ASN_PARSE_E, exit_dc);
2666  }
2667 
2668  if (GetAlgoId(input, &inOutIdx, &oid, oidKdfType, sz) < 0) {
2669  ERROR_OUT(ASN_PARSE_E, exit_dc);
2670  }
2671 
2672  if (oid != PBKDF2_OID) {
2673  ERROR_OUT(ASN_PARSE_E, exit_dc);
2674  }
2675  }
2676 
2677  if (GetSequence(input, &inOutIdx, &length, sz) <= 0) {
2678  ERROR_OUT(ASN_PARSE_E, exit_dc);
2679  }
2680 
2681  ret = GetOctetString(input, &inOutIdx, &saltSz, sz);
2682  if (ret < 0)
2683  goto exit_dc;
2684 
2685  if (saltSz > MAX_SALT_SIZE) {
2686  ERROR_OUT(ASN_PARSE_E, exit_dc);
2687  }
2688 
2689 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
2690  salt = (byte*)XMALLOC(MAX_SALT_SIZE, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
2691  if (salt == NULL) {
2692  ERROR_OUT(MEMORY_E, exit_dc);
2693  }
2694 #endif
2695 
2696  XMEMCPY(salt, &input[inOutIdx], saltSz);
2697  inOutIdx += saltSz;
2698 
2699  if (GetShortInt(input, &inOutIdx, &iterations, sz) < 0) {
2700  ERROR_OUT(ASN_PARSE_E, exit_dc);
2701  }
2702 
2703 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
2704  cbcIv = (byte*)XMALLOC(MAX_IV_SIZE, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
2705  if (cbcIv == NULL) {
2706  ERROR_OUT(MEMORY_E, exit_dc);
2707  }
2708 #endif
2709 
2710  if (version == PKCS5v2) {
2711  /* get encryption algo */
2712  /* JOHN: New type. Need a little more research. */
2713  if (GetAlgoId(input, &inOutIdx, &oid, oidBlkType, sz) < 0) {
2714  ERROR_OUT(ASN_PARSE_E, exit_dc);
2715  }
2716 
2717  if (CheckAlgoV2(oid, &id) < 0) {
2718  ERROR_OUT(ASN_PARSE_E, exit_dc); /* PKCS v2 algo id error */
2719  }
2720 
2721  ret = GetOctetString(input, &inOutIdx, &length, sz);
2722  if (ret < 0)
2723  goto exit_dc;
2724 
2725  XMEMCPY(cbcIv, &input[inOutIdx], length);
2726  inOutIdx += length;
2727  }
2728 
2729  if (input[inOutIdx++] != (ASN_CONTEXT_SPECIFIC | 0)) {
2730  ERROR_OUT(ASN_PARSE_E, exit_dc);
2731  }
2732 
2733  if (GetLength(input, &inOutIdx, &length, sz) < 0) {
2734  ERROR_OUT(ASN_PARSE_E, exit_dc);
2735  }
2736 
2737  ret = DecryptKey(password, passwordSz, salt, saltSz, iterations, id,
2738  input + inOutIdx, length, version, cbcIv);
2739 
2740 exit_dc:
2741 
2742 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
2743  XFREE(salt, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
2744  XFREE(cbcIv, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
2745 #endif
2746 
2747  if (ret == 0) {
2748  XMEMMOVE(input, input + inOutIdx, length);
2749  ret = length;
2750  }
2751 
2752  return ret;
2753 }
2754 #endif /* NO_PWDBASED */

2756 #ifndef NO_RSA
2757 
2758 #ifndef HAVE_USER_RSA
2759 int wc_RsaPublicKeyDecode(const byte* input, word32* inOutIdx, RsaKey* key,
2760  word32 inSz)
2761 {
2762  int length;
2763 #if defined(OPENSSL_EXTRA) || defined(RSA_DECODE_EXTRA)
2764  byte b;
2765 #endif
2766  int ret;
2767 
2768  if (input == NULL || inOutIdx == NULL || key == NULL)
2769  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
2770 
2771  if (GetSequence(input, inOutIdx, &length, inSz) < 0)
2772  return ASN_PARSE_E;
2773 
2774  key->type = RSA_PUBLIC;
2775 
2776 #if defined(OPENSSL_EXTRA) || defined(RSA_DECODE_EXTRA)
2777  if ((*inOutIdx + 1) > inSz)
2778  return BUFFER_E;
2779 
2780  b = input[*inOutIdx];
2781  if (b != ASN_INTEGER) {
2782  /* not from decoded cert, will have algo id, skip past */
2783  if (GetSequence(input, inOutIdx, &length, inSz) < 0)
2784  return ASN_PARSE_E;
2785 
2786  if (SkipObjectId(input, inOutIdx, inSz) < 0)
2787  return ASN_PARSE_E;
2788 
2789  /* Option NULL ASN.1 tag */
2790  if (input[*inOutIdx] == ASN_TAG_NULL) {
2791  ret = GetASNNull(input, inOutIdx, inSz);
2792  if (ret != 0)
2793  return ret;
2794  }
2795 
2796  /* should have bit tag length and seq next */
2797  ret = CheckBitString(input, inOutIdx, NULL, inSz, 1, NULL);
2798  if (ret != 0)
2799  return ret;
2800 
2801  if (GetSequence(input, inOutIdx, &length, inSz) < 0)
2802  return ASN_PARSE_E;
2803  }
2804 #endif /* OPENSSL_EXTRA */
2805 
2806  if (GetInt(&key->n, input, inOutIdx, inSz) < 0)
2807  return ASN_RSA_KEY_E;
2808  if (GetInt(&key->e, input, inOutIdx, inSz) < 0) {
2809  mp_clear(&key->n);
2810  return ASN_RSA_KEY_E;
2811  }
2812 
2813  return 0;
2814 }

2816 /* import RSA public key elements (n, e) into RsaKey structure (key) */
2817 int wc_RsaPublicKeyDecodeRaw(const byte* n, word32 nSz, const byte* e,
2818  word32 eSz, RsaKey* key)
2819 {
2820  if (n == NULL || e == NULL || key == NULL)
2821  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
2822 
2823  key->type = RSA_PUBLIC;
2824 
2825  if (mp_init(&key->n) != MP_OKAY)
2826  return MP_INIT_E;
2827 
2828  if (mp_read_unsigned_bin(&key->n, n, nSz) != 0) {
2829  mp_clear(&key->n);
2830  return ASN_GETINT_E;
2831  }
2832 
2833  if (mp_init(&key->e) != MP_OKAY) {
2834  mp_clear(&key->n);
2835  return MP_INIT_E;
2836  }
2837 
2838  if (mp_read_unsigned_bin(&key->e, e, eSz) != 0) {
2839  mp_clear(&key->n);
2840  mp_clear(&key->e);
2841  return ASN_GETINT_E;
2842  }
2843 
2844  return 0;
2845 }

2960 static mp_int* GetDsaInt(DsaKey* key, int idx)
2961 {
2962  if (idx == 0)
2963  return &key->p;
2964  if (idx == 1)
2965  return &key->q;
2966  if (idx == 2)
2967  return &key->g;
2968  if (idx == 3)
2969  return &key->y;
2970  if (idx == 4)
2971  return &key->x;
2972 
2973  return NULL;

2987 /* Convert DsaKey key to DER format, write to output (inLen), return bytes
2988  written */
2989 int wc_DsaKeyToDer(DsaKey* key, byte* output, word32 inLen)
2990 {
2991  word32 seqSz, verSz, rawLen, intTotalLen = 0;
2992  word32 sizes[DSA_INTS];
2993  int i, j, outLen, ret = 0, mpSz;
2994 
2995  byte seq[MAX_SEQ_SZ];
2996  byte ver[MAX_VERSION_SZ];
2997  byte* tmps[DSA_INTS];
2998 
2999  if (!key || !output)
3000  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
3001 
3002  if (key->type != DSA_PRIVATE)
3003  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
3004 
3005  for (i = 0; i < DSA_INTS; i++)
3006  tmps[i] = NULL;
3007 
3008  /* write all big ints from key to DER tmps */
3009  for (i = 0; i < DSA_INTS; i++) {
3010  mp_int* keyInt = GetDsaInt(key, i);
3011 
3012  rawLen = mp_unsigned_bin_size(keyInt) + 1;
3013  tmps[i] = (byte*)XMALLOC(rawLen + MAX_SEQ_SZ, key->heap,
3014  DYNAMIC_TYPE_DSA);
3015  if (tmps[i] == NULL) {
3016  ret = MEMORY_E;
3017  break;
3018  }
3019 
3020  mpSz = SetASNIntMP(keyInt, -1, tmps[i]);
3021  if (mpSz < 0) {
3022  ret = mpSz;
3023  break;
3024  }
3025  intTotalLen += (sizes[i] = mpSz);
3026  }
3027 
3028  if (ret != 0) {
3029  FreeTmpDsas(tmps, key->heap);
3030  return ret;
3031  }
3032 
3033  /* make headers */
3034  verSz = SetMyVersion(0, ver, FALSE);
3035  seqSz = SetSequence(verSz + intTotalLen, seq);
3036 
3037  outLen = seqSz + verSz + intTotalLen;
3038  if (outLen > (int)inLen)
3039  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
3040 
3041  /* write to output */
3042  XMEMCPY(output, seq, seqSz);
3043  j = seqSz;
3044  XMEMCPY(output + j, ver, verSz);
3045  j += verSz;
3046 
3047  for (i = 0; i < DSA_INTS; i++) {
3048  XMEMCPY(output + j, tmps[i], sizes[i]);
3049  j += sizes[i];
3050  }
3051  FreeTmpDsas(tmps, key->heap);
3052 
3053  return outLen;
3054 }
3055 
3056 #endif /* NO_DSA */

3144 static int GetCertHeader(DecodedCert* cert)
3145 {
3146  int ret = 0, len;
3147 
3148  if (GetSequence(cert->source, &cert->srcIdx, &len, cert->maxIdx) < 0)
3149  return ASN_PARSE_E;
3150 
3151  cert->certBegin = cert->srcIdx;
3152 
3153  if (GetSequence(cert->source, &cert->srcIdx, &len, cert->maxIdx) < 0)
3154  return ASN_PARSE_E;
3155  cert->sigIndex = len + cert->srcIdx;
3156 
3157  if (GetExplicitVersion(cert->source, &cert->srcIdx, &cert->version,
3158  cert->maxIdx) < 0)
3159  return ASN_PARSE_E;
3160 
3161  if (GetSerialNumber(cert->source, &cert->srcIdx, cert->serial,
3162  &cert->serialSz, cert->maxIdx) < 0)
3163  return ASN_PARSE_E;
3164 
3165  return ret;
3166 }

3168 #if !defined(NO_RSA)
3169 /* Store Rsa Key, may save later, Dsa could use in future */
3170 static int StoreRsaKey(DecodedCert* cert)
3171 {
3172  int length;
3173  word32 recvd = cert->srcIdx;
3174 
3175  if (GetSequence(cert->source, &cert->srcIdx, &length, cert->maxIdx) < 0)
3176  return ASN_PARSE_E;
3177 
3178  recvd = cert->srcIdx - recvd;
3179  length += recvd;
3180 
3181  while (recvd--)
3182  cert->srcIdx--;
3183 
3184  cert->pubKeySize = length;
3185  cert->publicKey = cert->source + cert->srcIdx;
3186  cert->srcIdx += length;
3187 
3188  return 0;
3189 }

3211 static int GetKey(DecodedCert* cert)
3212 {
3213  int length;
3214 #ifdef HAVE_NTRU
3215  int tmpIdx = cert->srcIdx;
3216 #endif
3217 
3218  if (GetSequence(cert->source, &cert->srcIdx, &length, cert->maxIdx) < 0)
3219  return ASN_PARSE_E;
3220 
3221  if (GetAlgoId(cert->source, &cert->srcIdx,
3222  &cert->keyOID, oidKeyType, cert->maxIdx) < 0)
3223  return ASN_PARSE_E;
3224 
3225  switch (cert->keyOID) {
3226  #ifndef NO_RSA
3227  case RSAk:
3228  {
3229  int ret;
3230  ret = CheckBitString(cert->source, &cert->srcIdx, NULL,
3231  cert->maxIdx, 1, NULL);
3232  if (ret != 0)
3233  return ret;
3234 
3235  return StoreRsaKey(cert);
3236  }
3237 
3238  #endif /* NO_RSA */
3239  #ifdef HAVE_NTRU
3240  case NTRUk:
3241  {
3242  const byte* key = &cert->source[tmpIdx];
3243  byte* next = (byte*)key;
3244  word16 keyLen;
3245  word32 rc;
3246  word32 remaining = cert->maxIdx - cert->srcIdx;
3247 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
3248  byte* keyBlob = NULL;
3249 #else
3250  byte keyBlob[MAX_NTRU_KEY_SZ];
3251 #endif
3252  rc = ntru_crypto_ntru_encrypt_subjectPublicKeyInfo2PublicKey(key,
3253  &keyLen, NULL, &next, &remaining);
3254  if (rc != NTRU_OK)
3255  return ASN_NTRU_KEY_E;
3256  if (keyLen > MAX_NTRU_KEY_SZ)
3257  return ASN_NTRU_KEY_E;
3258 
3259 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
3260  keyBlob = (byte*)XMALLOC(MAX_NTRU_KEY_SZ, NULL,
3261  DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
3262  if (keyBlob == NULL)
3263  return MEMORY_E;
3264 #endif
3265 
3266  rc = ntru_crypto_ntru_encrypt_subjectPublicKeyInfo2PublicKey(key,
3267  &keyLen, keyBlob, &next, &remaining);
3268  if (rc != NTRU_OK) {
3269 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
3270  XFREE(keyBlob, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
3271 #endif
3272  return ASN_NTRU_KEY_E;
3273  }
3274 
3275  if ( (next - key) < 0) {
3276 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
3277  XFREE(keyBlob, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
3278 #endif
3279  return ASN_NTRU_KEY_E;
3280  }
3281 
3282  cert->srcIdx = tmpIdx + (int)(next - key);
3283 
3284  cert->publicKey = (byte*) XMALLOC(keyLen, cert->heap,
3285  DYNAMIC_TYPE_PUBLIC_KEY);
3286  if (cert->publicKey == NULL) {
3287 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
3288  XFREE(keyBlob, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
3289 #endif
3290  return MEMORY_E;
3291  }
3292  XMEMCPY(cert->publicKey, keyBlob, keyLen);
3293  cert->pubKeyStored = 1;
3294  cert->pubKeySize = keyLen;
3295 
3296 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
3297  XFREE(keyBlob, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
3298 #endif
3299 
3300  return 0;
3301  }
3302  #endif /* HAVE_NTRU */
3303  #ifdef HAVE_ECC
3304  case ECDSAk:
3305  {
3306  int ret;
3307 
3308  if (GetObjectId(cert->source, &cert->srcIdx,
3309  &cert->pkCurveOID, oidCurveType, cert->maxIdx) < 0)
3310  return ASN_PARSE_E;
3311 
3312  if (CheckCurve(cert->pkCurveOID) < 0)
3313  return ECC_CURVE_OID_E;
3314 
3315  /* key header */
3316  ret = CheckBitString(cert->source, &cert->srcIdx, &length,
3317  cert->maxIdx, 1, NULL);
3318  if (ret != 0)
3319  return ret;
3320 
3321  cert->publicKey = (byte*)XMALLOC(length, cert->heap,
3322  DYNAMIC_TYPE_PUBLIC_KEY);
3323  if (cert->publicKey == NULL)
3324  return MEMORY_E;
3325  XMEMCPY(cert->publicKey, &cert->source[cert->srcIdx], length);
3326  cert->pubKeyStored = 1;
3327  cert->pubKeySize = length;
3328 
3329  cert->srcIdx += length;
3330 
3331  return 0;
3332  }
3333  #endif /* HAVE_ECC */
3334  #ifdef HAVE_ED25519
3335  case ED25519k:
3336  {
3337  int ret;
3338 
3339  cert->pkCurveOID = ED25519k;
3340 
3341  ret = CheckBitString(cert->source, &cert->srcIdx, &length,
3342  cert->maxIdx, 1, NULL);
3343  if (ret != 0)
3344  return ret;
3345 
3346  cert->publicKey = (byte*) XMALLOC(length, cert->heap,
3347  DYNAMIC_TYPE_PUBLIC_KEY);
3348  if (cert->publicKey == NULL)
3349  return MEMORY_E;
3350  XMEMCPY(cert->publicKey, &cert->source[cert->srcIdx], length);
3351  cert->pubKeyStored = 1;
3352  cert->pubKeySize = length;
3353 
3354  cert->srcIdx += length;
3355 
3356  return 0;
3357  }
3358  #endif /* HAVE_ED25519 */
3359  default:
3360  return ASN_UNKNOWN_OID_E;
3361  }
3362 }
3363 
3364 /* process NAME, either issuer or subject */
3365 static int GetName(DecodedCert* cert, int nameType)
3366 {
3367  int length; /* length of all distinguished names */
3368  int dummy;
3369  int ret;
3370  char* full;
3371  byte* hash;
3372  word32 idx;
3373  #ifdef OPENSSL_EXTRA
3374  DecodedName* dName =
3375  (nameType == ISSUER) ? &cert->issuerName : &cert->subjectName;
3376  #endif /* OPENSSL_EXTRA */
3377 
3378  WOLFSSL_MSG("Getting Cert Name");
3379 
3380  if (nameType == ISSUER) {
3381  full = cert->issuer;
3382  hash = cert->issuerHash;
3383  }
3384  else {
3385  full = cert->subject;
3386  hash = cert->subjectHash;
3387  }
3388 
3389  if (cert->source[cert->srcIdx] == ASN_OBJECT_ID) {
3390  WOLFSSL_MSG("Trying optional prefix...");
3391 
3392  if (SkipObjectId(cert->source, &cert->srcIdx, cert->maxIdx) < 0)
3393  return ASN_PARSE_E;
3394  WOLFSSL_MSG("Got optional prefix");
3395  }
3396 
3397  /* For OCSP, RFC2560 section 4.1.1 states the issuer hash should be
3398  * calculated over the entire DER encoding of the Name field, including
3399  * the tag and length. */
3400  idx = cert->srcIdx;
3401  if (GetSequence(cert->source, &cert->srcIdx, &length, cert->maxIdx) < 0)
3402  return ASN_PARSE_E;
3403 
3404 #ifdef NO_SHA
3405  ret = wc_Sha256Hash(&cert->source[idx], length + cert->srcIdx - idx, hash);
3406 #else
3407  ret = wc_ShaHash(&cert->source[idx], length + cert->srcIdx - idx, hash);
3408 #endif
3409  if (ret != 0)
3410  return ret;
3411 
3412  length += cert->srcIdx;
3413  idx = 0;
3414 
3415 #ifdef HAVE_PKCS7
3416  /* store pointer to raw issuer */
3417  if (nameType == ISSUER) {
3418  cert->issuerRaw = &cert->source[cert->srcIdx];
3419  cert->issuerRawLen = length - cert->srcIdx;
3420  }
3421 #endif
3422 #ifndef IGNORE_NAME_CONSTRAINTS
3423  if (nameType == SUBJECT) {
3424  cert->subjectRaw = &cert->source[cert->srcIdx];
3425  cert->subjectRawLen = length - cert->srcIdx;
3426  }
3427 #endif
3428 
3429  while (cert->srcIdx < (word32)length) {
3430  byte b;
3431  byte joint[2];
3432  byte tooBig = FALSE;
3433  int oidSz;
3434 
3435  if (GetSet(cert->source, &cert->srcIdx, &dummy, cert->maxIdx) < 0) {
3436  WOLFSSL_MSG("Cert name lacks set header, trying sequence");
3437  }
3438 
3439  if (GetSequence(cert->source, &cert->srcIdx, &dummy, cert->maxIdx) <= 0)
3440  return ASN_PARSE_E;
3441 
3442  ret = GetASNObjectId(cert->source, &cert->srcIdx, &oidSz, cert->maxIdx);
3443  if (ret != 0)
3444  return ret;
3445 
3446  /* make sure there is room for joint */
3447  if ((cert->srcIdx + sizeof(joint)) > cert->maxIdx)
3448  return ASN_PARSE_E;
3449 
3450  XMEMCPY(joint, &cert->source[cert->srcIdx], sizeof(joint));
3451 
3452  /* v1 name types */
3453  if (joint[0] == 0x55 && joint[1] == 0x04) {
3454  byte id;
3455  byte copy = FALSE;
3456  int strLen;
3457 
3458  cert->srcIdx += 2;
3459  id = cert->source[cert->srcIdx++];
3460  b = cert->source[cert->srcIdx++]; /* encoding */
3461 
3462  if (GetLength(cert->source, &cert->srcIdx, &strLen,
3463  cert->maxIdx) < 0)
3464  return ASN_PARSE_E;
3465 
3466  if ( (strLen + 14) > (int)(ASN_NAME_MAX - idx)) {
3467  /* include biggest pre fix header too 4 = "/serialNumber=" */
3468  WOLFSSL_MSG("ASN Name too big, skipping");
3469  tooBig = TRUE;
3470  }
3471 
3472  if (id == ASN_COMMON_NAME) {
3473  if (nameType == SUBJECT) {
3474  cert->subjectCN = (char *)&cert->source[cert->srcIdx];
3475  cert->subjectCNLen = strLen;
3476  cert->subjectCNEnc = b;
3477  }
3478 
3479  if (!tooBig) {
3480  XMEMCPY(&full[idx], "/CN=", 4);
3481  idx += 4;
3482  copy = TRUE;
3483  }
3484  #ifdef OPENSSL_EXTRA
3485  dName->cnIdx = cert->srcIdx;
3486  dName->cnLen = strLen;
3487  #endif /* OPENSSL_EXTRA */
3488  }
3489  else if (id == ASN_SUR_NAME) {
3490  if (!tooBig) {
3491  XMEMCPY(&full[idx], "/SN=", 4);
3492  idx += 4;
3493  copy = TRUE;
3494  }
3495  #ifdef WOLFSSL_CERT_GEN
3496  if (nameType == SUBJECT) {
3497  cert->subjectSN = (char*)&cert->source[cert->srcIdx];
3498  cert->subjectSNLen = strLen;
3499  cert->subjectSNEnc = b;
3500  }
3501  #endif /* WOLFSSL_CERT_GEN */
3502  #ifdef OPENSSL_EXTRA
3503  dName->snIdx = cert->srcIdx;
3504  dName->snLen = strLen;
3505  #endif /* OPENSSL_EXTRA */
3506  }
3507  else if (id == ASN_COUNTRY_NAME) {
3508  if (!tooBig) {
3509  XMEMCPY(&full[idx], "/C=", 3);
3510  idx += 3;
3511  copy = TRUE;
3512  }
3513  #ifdef WOLFSSL_CERT_GEN
3514  if (nameType == SUBJECT) {
3515  cert->subjectC = (char*)&cert->source[cert->srcIdx];
3516  cert->subjectCLen = strLen;
3517  cert->subjectCEnc = b;
3518  }
3519  #endif /* WOLFSSL_CERT_GEN */
3520  #ifdef OPENSSL_EXTRA
3521  dName->cIdx = cert->srcIdx;
3522  dName->cLen = strLen;
3523  #endif /* OPENSSL_EXTRA */
3524  }
3525  else if (id == ASN_LOCALITY_NAME) {
3526  if (!tooBig) {
3527  XMEMCPY(&full[idx], "/L=", 3);
3528  idx += 3;
3529  copy = TRUE;
3530  }
3531  #ifdef WOLFSSL_CERT_GEN
3532  if (nameType == SUBJECT) {
3533  cert->subjectL = (char*)&cert->source[cert->srcIdx];
3534  cert->subjectLLen = strLen;
3535  cert->subjectLEnc = b;
3536  }
3537  #endif /* WOLFSSL_CERT_GEN */
3538  #ifdef OPENSSL_EXTRA
3539  dName->lIdx = cert->srcIdx;
3540  dName->lLen = strLen;
3541  #endif /* OPENSSL_EXTRA */
3542  }
3543  else if (id == ASN_STATE_NAME) {
3544  if (!tooBig) {
3545  XMEMCPY(&full[idx], "/ST=", 4);
3546  idx += 4;
3547  copy = TRUE;
3548  }
3549  #ifdef WOLFSSL_CERT_GEN
3550  if (nameType == SUBJECT) {
3551  cert->subjectST = (char*)&cert->source[cert->srcIdx];
3552  cert->subjectSTLen = strLen;
3553  cert->subjectSTEnc = b;
3554  }
3555  #endif /* WOLFSSL_CERT_GEN */
3556  #ifdef OPENSSL_EXTRA
3557  dName->stIdx = cert->srcIdx;
3558  dName->stLen = strLen;
3559  #endif /* OPENSSL_EXTRA */
3560  }
3561  else if (id == ASN_ORG_NAME) {
3562  if (!tooBig) {
3563  XMEMCPY(&full[idx], "/O=", 3);
3564  idx += 3;
3565  copy = TRUE;
3566  }
3567  #ifdef WOLFSSL_CERT_GEN
3568  if (nameType == SUBJECT) {
3569  cert->subjectO = (char*)&cert->source[cert->srcIdx];
3570  cert->subjectOLen = strLen;
3571  cert->subjectOEnc = b;
3572  }
3573  #endif /* WOLFSSL_CERT_GEN */
3574  #ifdef OPENSSL_EXTRA
3575  dName->oIdx = cert->srcIdx;
3576  dName->oLen = strLen;
3577  #endif /* OPENSSL_EXTRA */
3578  }
3579  else if (id == ASN_ORGUNIT_NAME) {
3580  if (!tooBig) {
3581  XMEMCPY(&full[idx], "/OU=", 4);
3582  idx += 4;
3583  copy = TRUE;
3584  }
3585  #ifdef WOLFSSL_CERT_GEN
3586  if (nameType == SUBJECT) {
3587  cert->subjectOU = (char*)&cert->source[cert->srcIdx];
3588  cert->subjectOULen = strLen;
3589  cert->subjectOUEnc = b;
3590  }
3591  #endif /* WOLFSSL_CERT_GEN */
3592  #ifdef OPENSSL_EXTRA
3593  dName->ouIdx = cert->srcIdx;
3594  dName->ouLen = strLen;
3595  #endif /* OPENSSL_EXTRA */
3596  }
3597  else if (id == ASN_SERIAL_NUMBER) {
3598  if (!tooBig) {
3599  XMEMCPY(&full[idx], "/serialNumber=", 14);
3600  idx += 14;
3601  copy = TRUE;
3602  }
3603  #ifdef OPENSSL_EXTRA
3604  dName->snIdx = cert->srcIdx;
3605  dName->snLen = strLen;
3606  #endif /* OPENSSL_EXTRA */
3607  }
3608 
3609  if (copy && !tooBig) {
3610  XMEMCPY(&full[idx], &cert->source[cert->srcIdx], strLen);
3611  idx += strLen;
3612  }
3613 
3614  cert->srcIdx += strLen;
3615  }
3616  else {
3617  /* skip */
3618  byte email = FALSE;
3619  byte uid = FALSE;
3620  int adv;
3621 
3622  if (joint[0] == 0x2a && joint[1] == 0x86) /* email id hdr */
3623  email = TRUE;
3624 
3625  if (joint[0] == 0x9 && joint[1] == 0x92) /* uid id hdr */
3626  uid = TRUE;
3627 
3628  cert->srcIdx += oidSz + 1;
3629 
3630  if (GetLength(cert->source, &cert->srcIdx, &adv, cert->maxIdx) < 0)
3631  return ASN_PARSE_E;
3632 
3633  if (adv > (int)(ASN_NAME_MAX - idx)) {
3634  WOLFSSL_MSG("ASN name too big, skipping");
3635  tooBig = TRUE;
3636  }
3637 
3638  if (email) {
3639  if ( (14 + adv) > (int)(ASN_NAME_MAX - idx)) {
3640  WOLFSSL_MSG("ASN name too big, skipping");
3641  tooBig = TRUE;
3642  }
3643  if (!tooBig) {
3644  XMEMCPY(&full[idx], "/emailAddress=", 14);
3645  idx += 14;
3646  }
3647 
3648  #ifdef WOLFSSL_CERT_GEN
3649  if (nameType == SUBJECT) {
3650  cert->subjectEmail = (char*)&cert->source[cert->srcIdx];
3651  cert->subjectEmailLen = adv;
3652  }
3653  #endif /* WOLFSSL_CERT_GEN */
3654  #ifdef OPENSSL_EXTRA
3655  dName->emailIdx = cert->srcIdx;
3656  dName->emailLen = adv;
3657  #endif /* OPENSSL_EXTRA */
3658  #ifndef IGNORE_NAME_CONSTRAINTS
3659  {
3660  DNS_entry* emailName = NULL;
3661 
3662  emailName = (DNS_entry*)XMALLOC(sizeof(DNS_entry),
3663  cert->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_ALTNAME);
3664  if (emailName == NULL) {
3665  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tOut of Memory");
3666  return MEMORY_E;
3667  }
3668  emailName->name = (char*)XMALLOC(adv + 1,
3669  cert->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_ALTNAME);
3670  if (emailName->name == NULL) {
3671  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tOut of Memory");
3672  XFREE(emailName, cert->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_ALTNAME);
3673  return MEMORY_E;
3674  }
3675  XMEMCPY(emailName->name,
3676  &cert->source[cert->srcIdx], adv);
3677  emailName->name[adv] = 0;
3678 
3679  emailName->next = cert->altEmailNames;
3680  cert->altEmailNames = emailName;
3681  }
3682  #endif /* IGNORE_NAME_CONSTRAINTS */
3683  if (!tooBig) {
3684  XMEMCPY(&full[idx], &cert->source[cert->srcIdx], adv);
3685  idx += adv;
3686  }
3687  }
3688 
3689  if (uid) {
3690  if ( (5 + adv) > (int)(ASN_NAME_MAX - idx)) {
3691  WOLFSSL_MSG("ASN name too big, skipping");
3692  tooBig = TRUE;
3693  }
3694  if (!tooBig) {
3695  XMEMCPY(&full[idx], "/UID=", 5);
3696  idx += 5;
3697 
3698  XMEMCPY(&full[idx], &cert->source[cert->srcIdx], adv);
3699  idx += adv;
3700  }
3701  #ifdef OPENSSL_EXTRA
3702  dName->uidIdx = cert->srcIdx;
3703  dName->uidLen = adv;
3704  #endif /* OPENSSL_EXTRA */
3705  }
3706 
3707  cert->srcIdx += adv;
3708  }
3709  }
3710  full[idx++] = 0;
3711 
3712  #ifdef OPENSSL_EXTRA
3713  {
3714  int totalLen = 0;
3715 
3716  if (dName->cnLen != 0)
3717  totalLen += dName->cnLen + 4;
3718  if (dName->snLen != 0)
3719  totalLen += dName->snLen + 4;
3720  if (dName->cLen != 0)
3721  totalLen += dName->cLen + 3;
3722  if (dName->lLen != 0)
3723  totalLen += dName->lLen + 3;
3724  if (dName->stLen != 0)
3725  totalLen += dName->stLen + 4;
3726  if (dName->oLen != 0)
3727  totalLen += dName->oLen + 3;
3728  if (dName->ouLen != 0)
3729  totalLen += dName->ouLen + 4;
3730  if (dName->emailLen != 0)
3731  totalLen += dName->emailLen + 14;
3732  if (dName->uidLen != 0)
3733  totalLen += dName->uidLen + 5;
3734  if (dName->serialLen != 0)
3735  totalLen += dName->serialLen + 14;
3736 
3737  dName->fullName = (char*)XMALLOC(totalLen + 1, cert->heap,
3738  DYNAMIC_TYPE_X509);
3739  if (dName->fullName != NULL) {
3740  idx = 0;
3741 
3742  if (dName->cnLen != 0) {
3743  dName->entryCount++;
3744  XMEMCPY(&dName->fullName[idx], "/CN=", 4);
3745  idx += 4;
3746  XMEMCPY(&dName->fullName[idx],
3747  &cert->source[dName->cnIdx], dName->cnLen);
3748  dName->cnIdx = idx;
3749  idx += dName->cnLen;
3750  }
3751  if (dName->snLen != 0) {
3752  dName->entryCount++;
3753  XMEMCPY(&dName->fullName[idx], "/SN=", 4);
3754  idx += 4;
3755  XMEMCPY(&dName->fullName[idx],
3756  &cert->source[dName->snIdx], dName->snLen);
3757  dName->snIdx = idx;
3758  idx += dName->snLen;
3759  }
3760  if (dName->cLen != 0) {
3761  dName->entryCount++;
3762  XMEMCPY(&dName->fullName[idx], "/C=", 3);
3763  idx += 3;
3764  XMEMCPY(&dName->fullName[idx],
3765  &cert->source[dName->cIdx], dName->cLen);
3766  dName->cIdx = idx;
3767  idx += dName->cLen;
3768  }
3769  if (dName->lLen != 0) {
3770  dName->entryCount++;
3771  XMEMCPY(&dName->fullName[idx], "/L=", 3);
3772  idx += 3;
3773  XMEMCPY(&dName->fullName[idx],
3774  &cert->source[dName->lIdx], dName->lLen);
3775  dName->lIdx = idx;
3776  idx += dName->lLen;
3777  }
3778  if (dName->stLen != 0) {
3779  dName->entryCount++;
3780  XMEMCPY(&dName->fullName[idx], "/ST=", 4);
3781  idx += 4;
3782  XMEMCPY(&dName->fullName[idx],
3783  &cert->source[dName->stIdx], dName->stLen);
3784  dName->stIdx = idx;
3785  idx += dName->stLen;
3786  }
3787  if (dName->oLen != 0) {
3788  dName->entryCount++;
3789  XMEMCPY(&dName->fullName[idx], "/O=", 3);
3790  idx += 3;
3791  XMEMCPY(&dName->fullName[idx],
3792  &cert->source[dName->oIdx], dName->oLen);
3793  dName->oIdx = idx;
3794  idx += dName->oLen;
3795  }
3796  if (dName->ouLen != 0) {
3797  dName->entryCount++;
3798  XMEMCPY(&dName->fullName[idx], "/OU=", 4);
3799  idx += 4;
3800  XMEMCPY(&dName->fullName[idx],
3801  &cert->source[dName->ouIdx], dName->ouLen);
3802  dName->ouIdx = idx;
3803  idx += dName->ouLen;
3804  }
3805  if (dName->emailLen != 0) {
3806  dName->entryCount++;
3807  XMEMCPY(&dName->fullName[idx], "/emailAddress=", 14);
3808  idx += 14;
3809  XMEMCPY(&dName->fullName[idx],
3810  &cert->source[dName->emailIdx], dName->emailLen);
3811  dName->emailIdx = idx;
3812  idx += dName->emailLen;
3813  }
3814  if (dName->uidLen != 0) {
3815  dName->entryCount++;
3816  XMEMCPY(&dName->fullName[idx], "/UID=", 5);
3817  idx += 5;
3818  XMEMCPY(&dName->fullName[idx],
3819  &cert->source[dName->uidIdx], dName->uidLen);
3820  dName->uidIdx = idx;
3821  idx += dName->uidLen;
3822  }
3823  if (dName->serialLen != 0) {
3824  dName->entryCount++;
3825  XMEMCPY(&dName->fullName[idx], "/serialNumber=", 14);
3826  idx += 14;
3827  XMEMCPY(&dName->fullName[idx],
3828  &cert->source[dName->serialIdx], dName->serialLen);
3829  dName->serialIdx = idx;
3830  idx += dName->serialLen;
3831  }
3832  dName->fullName[idx] = '\0';
3833  dName->fullNameLen = totalLen;
3834  }
3835  }
3836  #endif /* OPENSSL_EXTRA */
3837 
3838  return 0;
3839 }
3840 
3841 
3842 #ifndef NO_ASN_TIME
3843 #if !defined(NO_TIME_H) && defined(USE_WOLF_VALIDDATE)
3844 
3845 /* to the second */
3846 static int DateGreaterThan(const struct tm* a, const struct tm* b)
3847 {
3848  if (a->tm_year > b->tm_year)
3849  return 1;
3850 
3851  if (a->tm_year == b->tm_year && a->tm_mon > b->tm_mon)
3852  return 1;
3853 
3854  if (a->tm_year == b->tm_year && a->tm_mon == b->tm_mon &&
3855  a->tm_mday > b->tm_mday)
3856  return 1;
3857 
3858  if (a->tm_year == b->tm_year && a->tm_mon == b->tm_mon &&
3859  a->tm_mday == b->tm_mday && a->tm_hour > b->tm_hour)
3860  return 1;
3861 
3862  if (a->tm_year == b->tm_year && a->tm_mon == b->tm_mon &&
3863  a->tm_mday == b->tm_mday && a->tm_hour == b->tm_hour &&
3864  a->tm_min > b->tm_min)
3865  return 1;
3866 
3867  if (a->tm_year == b->tm_year && a->tm_mon == b->tm_mon &&
3868  a->tm_mday == b->tm_mday && a->tm_hour == b->tm_hour &&
3869  a->tm_min == b->tm_min && a->tm_sec > b->tm_sec)
3870  return 1;
3871 
3872  return 0; /* false */
3873 }
3874 
3875 
3876 static INLINE int DateLessThan(const struct tm* a, const struct tm* b)
3877 {
3878  return DateGreaterThan(b,a);
3879 }
