3881 
3882 #if defined(WOLFSSL_MYSQL_COMPATIBLE) || defined(WOLFSSL_NGINX) || defined(WOLFSSL_HAPROXY)
3883 int GetTimeString(byte* date, int format, char* buf, int len)
3884 {
3885  struct tm t;
3886  int idx = 0;
3887 
3888  if (!ExtractDate(date, format, &t, &idx)) {
3889  return 0;
3890  }
3891 
3892  if (date[idx] != 'Z') {
3893  WOLFSSL_MSG("UTCtime, not Zulu") ;
3894  return 0;
3895  }
3896 
3897  /* place month in buffer */
3898  buf[0] = '\0';
3899  switch(t.tm_mon) {
3900  case 0: XSTRNCAT(buf, "Jan ", 4); break;
3901  case 1: XSTRNCAT(buf, "Feb ", 4); break;
3902  case 2: XSTRNCAT(buf, "Mar ", 4); break;
3903  case 3: XSTRNCAT(buf, "Apr ", 4); break;
3904  case 4: XSTRNCAT(buf, "May ", 4); break;
3905  case 5: XSTRNCAT(buf, "Jun ", 4); break;
3906  case 6: XSTRNCAT(buf, "Jul ", 4); break;
3907  case 7: XSTRNCAT(buf, "Aug ", 4); break;
3908  case 8: XSTRNCAT(buf, "Sep ", 4); break;
3909  case 9: XSTRNCAT(buf, "Oct ", 4); break;
3910  case 10: XSTRNCAT(buf, "Nov ", 4); break;
3911  case 11: XSTRNCAT(buf, "Dec ", 4); break;
3912  default:
3913  return 0;
3914 
3915  }
3916  idx = 4; /* use idx now for char buffer */
3917  buf[idx] = ' ';
3918 
3919  XSNPRINTF(buf + idx, len - idx, "%2d %02d:%02d:%02d %d GMT",
3920  t.tm_mday, t.tm_hour, t.tm_min, t.tm_sec, t.tm_year + 1900);
3921 
3922  return 1;
3923 }
3924 #endif /* WOLFSSL_MYSQL_COMPATIBLE */
3925 
3926 int ExtractDate(const unsigned char* date, unsigned char format,
3927  struct tm* certTime, int* idx)
3928 {
3929  XMEMSET(certTime, 0, sizeof(struct tm));
3930 
3931  if (format == ASN_UTC_TIME) {
3932  if (btoi(date[0]) >= 5)
3933  certTime->tm_year = 1900;
3934  else
3935  certTime->tm_year = 2000;
3936  }
3937  else { /* format == GENERALIZED_TIME */
3938  certTime->tm_year += btoi(date[*idx]) * 1000; *idx = *idx + 1;
3939  certTime->tm_year += btoi(date[*idx]) * 100; *idx = *idx + 1;
3940  }
3941 
3942  /* adjust tm_year, tm_mon */
3943  GetTime((int*)&certTime->tm_year, date, idx); certTime->tm_year -= 1900;
3944  GetTime((int*)&certTime->tm_mon, date, idx); certTime->tm_mon -= 1;
3945  GetTime((int*)&certTime->tm_mday, date, idx);
3946  GetTime((int*)&certTime->tm_hour, date, idx);
3947  GetTime((int*)&certTime->tm_min, date, idx);
3948  GetTime((int*)&certTime->tm_sec, date, idx);
3949 
3950  return 1;
3951 }
3952 
3953 
3954 /* like atoi but only use first byte */
3955 /* Make sure before and after dates are valid */
3956 int ValidateDate(const byte* date, byte format, int dateType)
3957 {
3958  time_t ltime;
3959  struct tm certTime;
3960  struct tm* localTime;
3961  struct tm* tmpTime = NULL;
3962  int i = 0;
3963  int timeDiff = 0 ;
3964  int diffHH = 0 ; int diffMM = 0 ;
3965  int diffSign = 0 ;
3966 
3967 #if defined(NEED_TMP_TIME)
3968  struct tm tmpTimeStorage;
3969  tmpTime = &tmpTimeStorage;
3970 #else
3971  (void)tmpTime;
3972 #endif
3973 
3974  ltime = XTIME(0);
3975 
3976 #ifdef WOLFSSL_BEFORE_DATE_CLOCK_SKEW
3977  if (dateType == BEFORE) {
3978  WOLFSSL_MSG("Skewing local time for before date check");
3979  ltime += WOLFSSL_BEFORE_DATE_CLOCK_SKEW;
3980  }
3981 #endif
3982 
3983 #ifdef WOLFSSL_AFTER_DATE_CLOCK_SKEW
3984  if (dateType == AFTER) {
3985  WOLFSSL_MSG("Skewing local time for after date check");
3986  ltime -= WOLFSSL_AFTER_DATE_CLOCK_SKEW;
3987  }
3988 #endif
3989 
3990  if (!ExtractDate(date, format, &certTime, &i)) {
3991  WOLFSSL_MSG("Error extracting the date");
3992  return 0;
3993  }
3994 
3995  if ((date[i] == '+') || (date[i] == '-')) {
3996  WOLFSSL_MSG("Using time differential, not Zulu") ;
3997  diffSign = date[i++] == '+' ? 1 : -1 ;
3998  GetTime(&diffHH, date, &i);
3999  GetTime(&diffMM, date, &i);
4000  timeDiff = diffSign * (diffHH*60 + diffMM) * 60 ;
4001  } else if (date[i] != 'Z') {
4002  WOLFSSL_MSG("UTCtime, niether Zulu or time differential") ;
4003  return 0;
4004  }
4005 
4006  ltime -= (time_t)timeDiff ;
4007  localTime = XGMTIME(&ltime, tmpTime);
4008 
4009  if (localTime == NULL) {
4010  WOLFSSL_MSG("XGMTIME failed");
4011  return 0;
4012  }
4013 
4014  if (dateType == BEFORE) {
4015  if (DateLessThan(localTime, &certTime)) {
4016  WOLFSSL_MSG("Date BEFORE check failed");
4017  return 0;
4018  }
4019  }
4020  else { /* dateType == AFTER */
4021  if (DateGreaterThan(localTime, &certTime)) {
4022  WOLFSSL_MSG("Date AFTER check failed");
4023  return 0;
4024  }
4025  }
4026 
4027  return 1;
4028 }
4029 #endif /* !NO_TIME_H && USE_WOLF_VALIDDATE */
4030 
4031 int wc_GetTime(void* timePtr, word32 timeSize)
4032 {
4033  time_t* ltime = (time_t*)timePtr;
4034 
4035  if (timePtr == NULL) {
4036  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
4037  }
4038 
4039  if ((word32)sizeof(time_t) > timeSize) {
4040  return BUFFER_E;
4041  }
4042 
4043  *ltime = XTIME(0);
4044 
4045  return 0;
4046 }
4047 
4048 #endif /* !NO_ASN_TIME */
4049 
4050 static int GetDate(DecodedCert* cert, int dateType)
4051 {
4052  int length;
4053  byte date[MAX_DATE_SIZE];
4054  byte b;
4055  word32 startIdx = 0;
4056 
4057  XMEMSET(date, 0, MAX_DATE_SIZE);
4058 
4059  if (dateType == BEFORE)
4060  cert->beforeDate = &cert->source[cert->srcIdx];
4061  else
4062  cert->afterDate = &cert->source[cert->srcIdx];
4063  startIdx = cert->srcIdx;
4064 
4065  b = cert->source[cert->srcIdx++];
4066  if (b != ASN_UTC_TIME && b != ASN_GENERALIZED_TIME)
4067  return ASN_TIME_E;
4068 
4069  if (GetLength(cert->source, &cert->srcIdx, &length, cert->maxIdx) < 0)
4070  return ASN_PARSE_E;
4071 
4072  if (length > MAX_DATE_SIZE || length < MIN_DATE_SIZE)
4073  return ASN_DATE_SZ_E;
4074 
4075  XMEMCPY(date, &cert->source[cert->srcIdx], length);
4076  cert->srcIdx += length;
4077 
4078  if (dateType == BEFORE)
4079  cert->beforeDateLen = cert->srcIdx - startIdx;
4080  else
4081  cert->afterDateLen = cert->srcIdx - startIdx;
4082 
4083 #ifndef NO_ASN_TIME
4084  if (!XVALIDATE_DATE(date, b, dateType)) {
4085  if (dateType == BEFORE)
4086  return ASN_BEFORE_DATE_E;
4087  else
4088  return ASN_AFTER_DATE_E;
4089  }
4090 #endif
4091 
4092  return 0;
4093 }
4094 
4095 static int GetValidity(DecodedCert* cert, int verify)
4096 {
4097  int length;
4098  int badDate = 0;
4099 
4100  if (GetSequence(cert->source, &cert->srcIdx, &length, cert->maxIdx) < 0)
4101  return ASN_PARSE_E;
4102 
4103  if (GetDate(cert, BEFORE) < 0 && verify != NO_VERIFY)
4104  badDate = ASN_BEFORE_DATE_E; /* continue parsing */
4105 
4106  if (GetDate(cert, AFTER) < 0 && verify != NO_VERIFY)
4107  return ASN_AFTER_DATE_E;
4108 
4109  if (badDate != 0)
4110  return badDate;
4111 
4112  return 0;
4113 }

4115 
4116 int DecodeToKey(DecodedCert* cert, int verify)
4117 {
4118  int badDate = 0;
4119  int ret;
4120 
4121  if ( (ret = GetCertHeader(cert)) < 0)
4122  return ret;
4123 
4124  WOLFSSL_MSG("Got Cert Header");
4125 
4126  if ( (ret = GetAlgoId(cert->source, &cert->srcIdx, &cert->signatureOID,
4127  oidSigType, cert->maxIdx)) < 0)
4128  return ret;
4129 
4130  WOLFSSL_MSG("Got Algo ID");
4131 
4132  if ( (ret = GetName(cert, ISSUER)) < 0)
4133  return ret;
4134 
4135  if ( (ret = GetValidity(cert, verify)) < 0)
4136  badDate = ret;
4137 
4138  if ( (ret = GetName(cert, SUBJECT)) < 0)
4139  return ret;
4140 
4141  WOLFSSL_MSG("Got Subject Name");
4142 
4143  if ( (ret = GetKey(cert)) < 0)
4144  return ret;
4145 
4146  WOLFSSL_MSG("Got Key");
4147 
4148  if (badDate != 0)
4149  return badDate;
4150 
4151  return ret;
4152 }
4153 
4154 static int GetSignature(DecodedCert* cert)
4155 {
4156  int length;
4157  int ret;
4158  ret = CheckBitString(cert->source, &cert->srcIdx, &length, cert->maxIdx, 1,
4159  NULL);
4160  if (ret != 0)
4161  return ret;
4162 
4163  cert->sigLength = length;
4164  cert->signature = &cert->source[cert->srcIdx];
4165  cert->srcIdx += cert->sigLength;
4166 
4167  return 0;
4168 }

4186 static word32 BytePrecision(word32 value)
4187 {
4188  word32 i;
4189  for (i = sizeof(value); i; --i)
4190  if (value >> ((i - 1) * WOLFSSL_BIT_SIZE))
4191  break;
4192 
4193  return i;
4194 }
4195 
4196 
4197 WOLFSSL_LOCAL word32 SetLength(word32 length, byte* output)
4198 {
4199  word32 i = 0, j;
4200 
4201  if (length < ASN_LONG_LENGTH)
4202  output[i++] = (byte)length;
4203  else {
4204  output[i++] = (byte)(BytePrecision(length) | ASN_LONG_LENGTH);
4205 
4206  for (j = BytePrecision(length); j; --j) {
4207  output[i] = (byte)(length >> ((j - 1) * WOLFSSL_BIT_SIZE));
4208  i++;
4209  }
4210  }
4211 
4212  return i;
4213 }
4214

4216 WOLFSSL_LOCAL word32 SetSequence(word32 len, byte* output)
4217 {
4218  output[0] = ASN_SEQUENCE | ASN_CONSTRUCTED;
4219  return SetLength(len, output + 1) + 1;
4220 }

4223 {
4224  output[0] = ASN_OCTET_STRING;
4225  return SetLength(len, output + 1) + 1;
4226 }

4232  return SetLength(len, output + 1) + 1;

4252 static int SetCurve(ecc_key* key, byte* output)
4253 {
4254 #ifdef HAVE_OID_ENCODING
4255  int ret;
4256 #endif
4257  int idx = 0;
4258  word32 oidSz = 0;
4259

4261  if (key == NULL || key->dp == NULL) {
4262  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
4263  }
4264 
4265 #ifdef HAVE_OID_ENCODING
4266  ret = EncodeObjectId(key->dp->oid, key->dp->oidSz, NULL, &oidSz);
4267  if (ret != 0) {
4268  return ret;
4269  }
4270 #else
4271  oidSz = key->dp->oidSz;
4272 #endif
4273 
4274  idx += SetObjectId(oidSz, output);
4275 
4276 #ifdef HAVE_OID_ENCODING
4277  ret = EncodeObjectId(key->dp->oid, key->dp->oidSz, output+idx, &oidSz);
4278  if (ret != 0) {
4279  return ret;
4280  }
4281 #else
4282  XMEMCPY(output+idx, key->dp->oid, oidSz);
4283 #endif
4284  idx += oidSz;
4285 
4286  return idx;
4287 }

4289 #endif /* HAVE_ECC && WOLFSSL_CERT_GEN */

4292 static INLINE int IsSigAlgoECDSA(int algoOID)
4293 {
4294  /* ECDSA sigAlgo must not have ASN1 NULL parameters */
4295  if (algoOID == CTC_SHAwECDSA || algoOID == CTC_SHA256wECDSA ||
4296  algoOID == CTC_SHA384wECDSA || algoOID == CTC_SHA512wECDSA) {
4297  return 1;
4298  }
4299 
4300  return 0;
4301 }
4302 
4303 WOLFSSL_LOCAL word32 SetAlgoID(int algoOID, byte* output, int type, int curveSz)
4304 {
4305  word32 tagSz, idSz, seqSz, algoSz = 0;
4306  const byte* algoName = 0;
4307  byte ID_Length[1 + MAX_LENGTH_SZ];
4308  byte seqArray[MAX_SEQ_SZ + 1]; /* add object_id to end */
4309 
4310  tagSz = (type == oidHashType ||
4311  (type == oidSigType && !IsSigAlgoECDSA(algoOID) &&
4312  algoOID != ED25519k) ||
4313  (type == oidKeyType && algoOID == RSAk)) ? 2 : 0;
4314 
4315  algoName = OidFromId(algoOID, type, &algoSz);
4316 
4317  if (algoName == NULL) {
4318  WOLFSSL_MSG("Unknown Algorithm");
4319  return 0;
4320  }
4321 
4322  idSz = SetObjectId(algoSz, ID_Length);
4323  seqSz = SetSequence(idSz + algoSz + tagSz + curveSz, seqArray);
4324 
4325  XMEMCPY(output, seqArray, seqSz);
4326  XMEMCPY(output + seqSz, ID_Length, idSz);
4327  XMEMCPY(output + seqSz + idSz, algoName, algoSz);
4328  if (tagSz == 2)
4329  SetASNNull(&output[seqSz + idSz + algoSz]);
4330 
4331  return seqSz + idSz + algoSz + tagSz;
4332 
4333 }

4335 
4336 word32 wc_EncodeSignature(byte* out, const byte* digest, word32 digSz,
4337  int hashOID)
4338 {
4339  byte digArray[MAX_ENCODED_DIG_SZ];
4340  byte algoArray[MAX_ALGO_SZ];
4341  byte seqArray[MAX_SEQ_SZ];
4342  word32 encDigSz, algoSz, seqSz;
4343 
4344  encDigSz = SetDigest(digest, digSz, digArray);
4345  algoSz = SetAlgoID(hashOID, algoArray, oidHashType, 0);
4346  seqSz = SetSequence(encDigSz + algoSz, seqArray);
4347 
4348  XMEMCPY(out, seqArray, seqSz);
4349  XMEMCPY(out + seqSz, algoArray, algoSz);
4350  XMEMCPY(out + seqSz + algoSz, digArray, encDigSz);
4351 
4352  return encDigSz + algoSz + seqSz;
4353 }

4356 int wc_GetCTC_HashOID(int type)

4392 void InitSignatureCtx(SignatureCtx* sigCtx, void* heap, int devId)
4393 {
4394  if (sigCtx) {
4395  XMEMSET(sigCtx, 0, sizeof(SignatureCtx));
4396  sigCtx->devId = devId;
4397  sigCtx->heap = heap;
4398  }
4399 }
4400 
4401 void FreeSignatureCtx(SignatureCtx* sigCtx)
4402 {
4403  if (sigCtx == NULL)
4404  return;
4405 
4406  if (sigCtx->digest) {
4407  XFREE(sigCtx->digest, sigCtx->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_DIGEST);
4408  sigCtx->digest = NULL;
4409  }
4410 #ifndef NO_RSA
4411  if (sigCtx->plain) {
4412  XFREE(sigCtx->plain, sigCtx->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_SIGNATURE);
4413  sigCtx->plain = NULL;
4414  }
4415 #endif
4416  if (sigCtx->key.ptr) {
4417  switch (sigCtx->keyOID) {
4418  #ifndef NO_RSA
4419  case RSAk:
4420  wc_FreeRsaKey(sigCtx->key.rsa);
4421  XFREE(sigCtx->key.ptr, sigCtx->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_RSA);
4422  break;
4423  #endif /* !NO_RSA */
4424  #ifdef HAVE_ECC
4425  case ECDSAk:
4426  wc_ecc_free(sigCtx->key.ecc);
4427  XFREE(sigCtx->key.ecc, sigCtx->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_ECC);
4428  break;
4429  #endif /* HAVE_ECC */
4430  #ifdef HAVE_ED25519
4431  case ED25519k:
4432  wc_ed25519_free(sigCtx->key.ed25519);
4433  XFREE(sigCtx->key.ed25519, sigCtx->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_ED25519);
4434  break;
4435  #endif /* HAVE_ED25519 */
4436  default:
4437  break;
4438  } /* switch (keyOID) */
4439  sigCtx->key.ptr = NULL;
4440  }
4441 
4442  /* reset state, we are done */
4443  sigCtx->state = SIG_STATE_BEGIN;
4444 }
4445 
4446 static int HashForSignature(const byte* buf, word32 bufSz, word32 sigOID,
4447  byte* digest, int* typeH, int* digestSz, int verify)
4448 {
4449  int ret = 0;
4450 
4451  (void)verify;
4452 
4453  switch (sigOID) {
4454  #if defined(WOLFSSL_MD2)
4455  case CTC_MD2wRSA:
4456  if (!verify) {
4457  ret = HASH_TYPE_E;
4458  WOLFSSL_MSG("MD2 not supported for signing");
4459  }
4460  else if ((ret = wc_Md2Hash(buf, bufSz, digest)) == 0) {
4461  *typeH = MD2h;
4462  *digestSz = MD2_DIGEST_SIZE;
4463  }
4464  break;
4465  #endif
4466  #ifndef NO_MD5
4467  case CTC_MD5wRSA:
4468  if ((ret = wc_Md5Hash(buf, bufSz, digest)) == 0) {
4469  *typeH = MD5h;
4470  *digestSz = MD5_DIGEST_SIZE;
4471  }
4472  break;
4473  #endif
4474  #ifndef NO_SHA
4475  case CTC_SHAwRSA:
4476  case CTC_SHAwDSA:
4477  case CTC_SHAwECDSA:
4478  if ((ret = wc_ShaHash(buf, bufSz, digest)) == 0) {
4479  *typeH = SHAh;
4480  *digestSz = SHA_DIGEST_SIZE;
4481  }
4482  break;
4483  #endif
4484  #ifdef WOLFSSL_SHA224
4485  case CTC_SHA224wRSA:
4486  case CTC_SHA224wECDSA:
4487  if ((ret = wc_Sha224Hash(buf, bufSz, digest)) == 0) {
4488  *typeH = SHA224h;
4489  *digestSz = SHA224_DIGEST_SIZE;
4490  }
4491  break;
4492  #endif
4493  #ifndef NO_SHA256
4494  case CTC_SHA256wRSA:
4495  case CTC_SHA256wECDSA:
4496  if ((ret = wc_Sha256Hash(buf, bufSz, digest)) == 0) {
4497  *typeH = SHA256h;
4498  *digestSz = SHA256_DIGEST_SIZE;
4499  }
4500  break;
4501  #endif
4502  #ifdef WOLFSSL_SHA384
4503  case CTC_SHA384wRSA:
4504  case CTC_SHA384wECDSA:
4505  if ((ret = wc_Sha384Hash(buf, bufSz, digest)) == 0) {
4506  *typeH = SHA384h;
4507  *digestSz = SHA384_DIGEST_SIZE;
4508  }
4509  break;
4510  #endif
4511  #ifdef WOLFSSL_SHA512
4512  case CTC_SHA512wRSA:
4513  case CTC_SHA512wECDSA:
4514  if ((ret = wc_Sha512Hash(buf, bufSz, digest)) == 0) {
4515  *typeH = SHA512h;
4516  *digestSz = SHA512_DIGEST_SIZE;
4517  }
4518  break;
4519  #endif
4520  case CTC_ED25519:
4521  /* Hashes done in signing operation.
4522  * Two dependent hashes with prefixes performed.
4523  */
4524  break;
4525  default:
4526  ret = HASH_TYPE_E;
4527  WOLFSSL_MSG("Hash for Signature has unsupported type");
4528  }
4529 
4530  return ret;
4531 }
4532 
4533 /* Return codes: 0=Success, Negative (see error-crypt.h), ASN_SIG_CONFIRM_E */
4534 static int ConfirmSignature(SignatureCtx* sigCtx,
4535  const byte* buf, word32 bufSz,
4536  const byte* key, word32 keySz, word32 keyOID,
4537  const byte* sig, word32 sigSz, word32 sigOID)
4538 {
4539  int ret = 0;
4540 
4541  if (sigCtx == NULL || buf == NULL || bufSz == 0 || key == NULL ||
4542  keySz == 0 || sig == NULL || sigSz == 0) {
4543  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
4544  }
4545 
4546  (void)key;
4547  (void)keySz;
4548  (void)sig;
4549  (void)sigSz;
4550 
4551  WOLFSSL_ENTER("ConfirmSignature");
4552 
4553  switch (sigCtx->state) {
4554  case SIG_STATE_BEGIN:
4555  {
4556  sigCtx->digest = (byte*)XMALLOC(WC_MAX_DIGEST_SIZE, sigCtx->heap,
4557  DYNAMIC_TYPE_DIGEST);
4558  if (sigCtx->digest == NULL) {
4559  ERROR_OUT(MEMORY_E, exit_cs);
4560  }
4561 
4562  sigCtx->state = SIG_STATE_HASH;
4563  } /* SIG_STATE_BEGIN */
4564  FALL_THROUGH;
4565 
4566  case SIG_STATE_HASH:
4567  {
4568  ret = HashForSignature(buf, bufSz, sigOID, sigCtx->digest,
4569  &sigCtx->typeH, &sigCtx->digestSz, 1);
4570  if (ret != 0) {
4571  goto exit_cs;
4572  }
4573 
4574  sigCtx->state = SIG_STATE_KEY;
4575  } /* SIG_STATE_HASH */
4576  FALL_THROUGH;
4577 
4578  case SIG_STATE_KEY:
4579  {
4580  sigCtx->keyOID = keyOID;
4581 
4582  switch (keyOID) {
4583  #ifndef NO_RSA
4584  case RSAk:
4585  {
4586  word32 idx = 0;
4587 
4588  sigCtx->key.rsa = (RsaKey*)XMALLOC(sizeof(RsaKey),
4589  sigCtx->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_RSA);
4590  sigCtx->plain = (byte*)XMALLOC(MAX_ENCODED_SIG_SZ,
4591  sigCtx->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_SIGNATURE);
4592  if (sigCtx->key.rsa == NULL || sigCtx->plain == NULL) {
4593  ERROR_OUT(MEMORY_E, exit_cs);
4594  }
4595  if ((ret = wc_InitRsaKey_ex(sigCtx->key.rsa, sigCtx->heap,
4596  sigCtx->devId)) != 0) {
4597  goto exit_cs;
4598  }
4599  if (sigSz > MAX_ENCODED_SIG_SZ) {
4600  WOLFSSL_MSG("Verify Signature is too big");
4601  ERROR_OUT(BUFFER_E, exit_cs);
4602  }
4603  if ((ret = wc_RsaPublicKeyDecode(key, &idx, sigCtx->key.rsa,
4604  keySz)) != 0) {
4605  WOLFSSL_MSG("ASN Key decode error RSA");
4606  goto exit_cs;
4607  }
4608  XMEMCPY(sigCtx->plain, sig, sigSz);
4609  sigCtx->out = NULL;
4610 
4611  #ifdef WOLFSSL_ASYNC_CRYPT
4612  sigCtx->asyncDev = &sigCtx->key.rsa->asyncDev;
4613  #endif
4614  break;
4615  }
4616  #endif /* !NO_RSA */
4617  #ifdef HAVE_ECC
4618  case ECDSAk:
4619  {
4620  sigCtx->verify = 0;
4621  sigCtx->key.ecc = (ecc_key*)XMALLOC(sizeof(ecc_key),
4622  sigCtx->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_ECC);
4623  if (sigCtx->key.ecc == NULL) {
4624  ERROR_OUT(MEMORY_E, exit_cs);
4625  }
4626  if ((ret = wc_ecc_init_ex(sigCtx->key.ecc, sigCtx->heap,
4627  sigCtx->devId)) < 0) {
4628  goto exit_cs;
4629  }
4630  if ((ret = wc_ecc_import_x963(key, keySz,
4631  sigCtx->key.ecc)) < 0) {
4632  WOLFSSL_MSG("ASN Key import error ECC");
4633  goto exit_cs;
4634  }
4635  #ifdef WOLFSSL_ASYNC_CRYPT
4636  sigCtx->asyncDev = &sigCtx->key.ecc->asyncDev;
4637  #endif
4638  break;
4639  }
4640  #endif /* HAVE_ECC */
4641  #ifdef HAVE_ED25519
4642  case ED25519k:
4643  {
4644  sigCtx->verify = 0;
4645  sigCtx->key.ed25519 = (ed25519_key*)XMALLOC(
4646  sizeof(ed25519_key), sigCtx->heap,
4647  DYNAMIC_TYPE_ED25519);
4648  if (sigCtx->key.ed25519 == NULL) {
4649  ERROR_OUT(MEMORY_E, exit_cs);
4650  }
4651  if ((ret = wc_ed25519_init(sigCtx->key.ed25519)) < 0) {
4652  goto exit_cs;
4653  }
4654  if ((ret = wc_ed25519_import_public(key, keySz,
4655  sigCtx->key.ed25519)) < 0) {
4656  WOLFSSL_MSG("ASN Key import error ED25519");
4657  goto exit_cs;
4658  }
4659  #ifdef WOLFSSL_ASYNC_CRYPT
4660  sigCtx->asyncDev = &sigCtx->key.ed25519->asyncDev;
4661  #endif
4662  break;
4663  }
4664  #endif
4665  default:
4666  WOLFSSL_MSG("Verify Key type unknown");
4667  ret = ASN_UNKNOWN_OID_E;
4668  break;
4669  } /* switch (keyOID) */
4670 
4671  if (ret != 0) {
4672  goto exit_cs;
4673  }
4674 
4675  sigCtx->state = SIG_STATE_DO;
4676 
4677  #ifdef WOLFSSL_ASYNC_CRYPT
4678  if (sigCtx->devId != INVALID_DEVID && sigCtx->asyncDev && sigCtx->asyncCtx) {
4679  /* make sure event is intialized */
4680  WOLF_EVENT* event = &sigCtx->asyncDev->event;
4681  ret = wolfAsync_EventInit(event, WOLF_EVENT_TYPE_ASYNC_WOLFSSL,
4682  sigCtx->asyncCtx, WC_ASYNC_FLAG_CALL_AGAIN);
4683  }
4684  #endif
4685  } /* SIG_STATE_KEY */
4686  FALL_THROUGH;
4687 
4688  case SIG_STATE_DO:
4689  {
4690  switch (keyOID) {
4691  #ifndef NO_RSA
4692  case RSAk:
4693  {
4694  ret = wc_RsaSSL_VerifyInline(sigCtx->plain, sigSz,
4695  &sigCtx->out, sigCtx->key.rsa);
4696  break;
4697  }
4698  #endif /* !NO_RSA */
4699  #ifdef HAVE_ECC
4700  case ECDSAk:
4701  {
4702  ret = wc_ecc_verify_hash(sig, sigSz, sigCtx->digest,
4703  sigCtx->digestSz, &sigCtx->verify, sigCtx->key.ecc);
4704  break;
4705  }
4706  #endif /* HAVE_ECC */
4707  #ifdef HAVE_ED25519
4708  case ED25519k:
4709  {
4710  ret = wc_ed25519_verify_msg(sig, sigSz, buf, bufSz,
4711  &sigCtx->verify, sigCtx->key.ed25519);
4712  break;
4713  }
4714  #endif
4715  default:
4716  break;
4717  } /* switch (keyOID) */
4718 
4719  if (ret < 0) {
4720  /* treat all non async RSA errors as ASN_SIG_CONFIRM_E */
4721  if (ret != WC_PENDING_E)
4722  ret = ASN_SIG_CONFIRM_E;
4723  goto exit_cs;
4724  }
4725 
4726  sigCtx->state = SIG_STATE_CHECK;
4727  } /* SIG_STATE_DO */
4728  FALL_THROUGH;
4729 
4730  case SIG_STATE_CHECK:
4731  {
4732  switch (keyOID) {
4733  #ifndef NO_RSA
4734  case RSAk:
4735  {
4736  int encodedSigSz, verifySz;
4737  #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
4738  byte* encodedSig = (byte*)XMALLOC(MAX_ENCODED_SIG_SZ,
4739  sigCtx->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
4740  if (encodedSig == NULL) {
4741  ERROR_OUT(MEMORY_E, exit_cs);
4742  }
4743  #else
4744  byte encodedSig[MAX_ENCODED_SIG_SZ];
4745  #endif
4746 
4747  verifySz = ret;
4748 
4749  /* make sure we're right justified */
4750  encodedSigSz = wc_EncodeSignature(encodedSig,
4751  sigCtx->digest, sigCtx->digestSz, sigCtx->typeH);
4752  if (encodedSigSz == verifySz &&
4753  XMEMCMP(sigCtx->out, encodedSig, encodedSigSz) == 0) {
4754  ret = 0;
4755  }
4756  else {
4757  WOLFSSL_MSG("RSA SSL verify match encode error");
4758  ret = ASN_SIG_CONFIRM_E;
4759  }
4760 
4761  #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
4762  XFREE(encodedSig, sigCtx->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
4763  #endif
4764  break;
4765  }
4766  #endif /* NO_RSA */
4767  #ifdef HAVE_ECC
4768  case ECDSAk:
4769  {
4770  if (sigCtx->verify == 1) {
4771  ret = 0;
4772  }
4773  else {
4774  WOLFSSL_MSG("ECC Verify didn't match");
4775  ret = ASN_SIG_CONFIRM_E;
4776  }
4777  break;
4778  }
4779  #endif /* HAVE_ECC */
4780  #ifdef HAVE_ED25519
4781  case ED25519k:
4782  {
4783  if (sigCtx->verify == 1) {
4784  ret = 0;
4785  }
4786  else {
4787  WOLFSSL_MSG("ED25519 Verify didn't match");
4788  ret = ASN_SIG_CONFIRM_E;
4789  }
4790  break;
4791  }
4792  #endif /* HAVE_ED25519 */
4793  default:
4794  break;
4795  } /* switch (keyOID) */
4796 
4797  break;
4798  } /* SIG_STATE_CHECK */
4799  } /* switch (sigCtx->state) */
4800 
4801 exit_cs:
4802 
4803  WOLFSSL_LEAVE("ConfirmSignature", ret);
4804 
4805  if (ret != WC_PENDING_E) {
4806  FreeSignatureCtx(sigCtx);
4807  }
4808 
4809  return ret;
4810 }
4811 
4812 
4813 #ifndef IGNORE_NAME_CONSTRAINTS
4814 
4815 static int MatchBaseName(int type, const char* name, int nameSz,
4816  const char* base, int baseSz)
4817 {
4818  if (base == NULL || baseSz <= 0 || name == NULL || nameSz <= 0 ||
4819  name[0] == '.' || nameSz < baseSz ||
4820  (type != ASN_RFC822_TYPE && type != ASN_DNS_TYPE))
4821  return 0;
4822 
4823  /* If an email type, handle special cases where the base is only
4824  * a domain, or is an email address itself. */
4825  if (type == ASN_RFC822_TYPE) {
4826  const char* p = NULL;
4827  int count = 0;
4828 
4829  if (base[0] != '.') {
4830  p = base;
4831  count = 0;
4832 
4833  /* find the '@' in the base */
4834  while (*p != '@' && count < baseSz) {
4835  count++;
4836  p++;
4837  }
4838 
4839  /* No '@' in base, reset p to NULL */
4840  if (count >= baseSz)
4841  p = NULL;
4842  }
4843 
4844  if (p == NULL) {
4845  /* Base isn't an email address, it is a domain name,
4846  * wind the name forward one character past its '@'. */
4847  p = name;
4848  count = 0;
4849  while (*p != '@' && count < baseSz) {
4850  count++;
4851  p++;
4852  }
4853 
4854  if (count < baseSz && *p == '@') {
4855  name = p + 1;
4856  nameSz -= count + 1;
4857  }
4858  }
4859  }
4860 
4861  if ((type == ASN_DNS_TYPE || type == ASN_RFC822_TYPE) && base[0] == '.') {
4862  int szAdjust = nameSz - baseSz;
4863  name += szAdjust;
4864  nameSz -= szAdjust;
4865  }
4866 
4867  while (nameSz > 0) {
4868  if (XTOLOWER((unsigned char)*name++) !=
4869  XTOLOWER((unsigned char)*base++))
4870  return 0;
4871  nameSz--;
4872  }
4873 
4874  return 1;
4875 }
4876 
4877 
4878 static int ConfirmNameConstraints(Signer* signer, DecodedCert* cert)
4879 {
4880  if (signer == NULL || cert == NULL)
4881  return 0;
4882 
4883  /* Check against the excluded list */
4884  if (signer->excludedNames) {
4885  Base_entry* base = signer->excludedNames;
4886 
4887  while (base != NULL) {
4888  switch (base->type) {
4889  case ASN_DNS_TYPE:
4890  {
4891  DNS_entry* name = cert->altNames;
4892  while (name != NULL) {
4893  if (MatchBaseName(ASN_DNS_TYPE,
4894  name->name, (int)XSTRLEN(name->name),
4895  base->name, base->nameSz)) {
4896  return 0;
4897  }
4898  name = name->next;
4899  }
4900  break;
4901  }
4902  case ASN_RFC822_TYPE:
4903  {
4904  DNS_entry* name = cert->altEmailNames;
4905  while (name != NULL) {
4906  if (MatchBaseName(ASN_RFC822_TYPE,
4907  name->name, (int)XSTRLEN(name->name),
4908  base->name, base->nameSz)) {
4909  return 0;
4910  }
4911  name = name->next;
4912  }
4913  break;
4914  }
4915  case ASN_DIR_TYPE:
4916  {
4917  /* allow permitted dirName smaller than actual subject */
4918  if (cert->subjectRawLen >= base->nameSz &&
4919  XMEMCMP(cert->subjectRaw, base->name,
4920  base->nameSz) == 0) {
4921  return 0;
4922  }
4923  break;
4924  }
4925  }; /* switch */
4926  base = base->next;
4927  }
4928  }
4929 
4930  /* Check against the permitted list */
4931  if (signer->permittedNames != NULL) {
4932  int needDns = 0;
4933  int matchDns = 0;
4934  int needEmail = 0;
4935  int matchEmail = 0;
4936  int needDir = 0;
4937  int matchDir = 0;
4938  Base_entry* base = signer->permittedNames;
4939 
4940  while (base != NULL) {
4941  switch (base->type) {
4942  case ASN_DNS_TYPE:
4943  {
4944  DNS_entry* name = cert->altNames;
4945 
4946  if (name != NULL)
4947  needDns = 1;
4948 
4949  while (name != NULL) {
4950  matchDns = MatchBaseName(ASN_DNS_TYPE,
4951  name->name, (int)XSTRLEN(name->name),
4952  base->name, base->nameSz);
4953  name = name->next;
4954  }
4955  break;
4956  }
4957  case ASN_RFC822_TYPE:
4958  {
4959  DNS_entry* name = cert->altEmailNames;
4960 
4961  if (name != NULL)
4962  needEmail = 1;
4963 
4964  while (name != NULL) {
4965  matchEmail = MatchBaseName(ASN_DNS_TYPE,
4966  name->name, (int)XSTRLEN(name->name),
4967  base->name, base->nameSz);
4968  name = name->next;
4969  }
4970  break;
4971  }
4972  case ASN_DIR_TYPE:
4973  {
4974  /* allow permitted dirName smaller than actual subject */
4975  needDir = 1;
4976  if (cert->subjectRaw != NULL &&
4977  cert->subjectRawLen >= base->nameSz &&
4978  XMEMCMP(cert->subjectRaw, base->name,
4979  base->nameSz) == 0) {
4980  matchDir = 1;
4981  }
4982  break;
4983  }
4984  } /* switch */
4985  base = base->next;
4986  }
4987 
4988  if ((needDns && !matchDns) ||
4989  (needEmail && !matchEmail) ||
4990  (needDir && !matchDir)) {
4991  return 0;
4992  }
4993  }
4994 
4995  return 1;
4996 }
4997 
4998 #endif /* IGNORE_NAME_CONSTRAINTS */
4999 
5000 static int DecodeAltNames(byte* input, int sz, DecodedCert* cert)
5001 {
5002  word32 idx = 0;
5003  int length = 0;
5004 
5005  WOLFSSL_ENTER("DecodeAltNames");
5006 
5007  if (GetSequence(input, &idx, &length, sz) < 0) {
5008  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tBad Sequence");
5009  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5010  }
5011 
5012  cert->weOwnAltNames = 1;
5013 
5014  while (length > 0) {
5015  byte b = input[idx++];
5016 
5017  length--;
5018 
5019  /* Save DNS Type names in the altNames list. */
5020  /* Save Other Type names in the cert's OidMap */
5021  if (b == (ASN_CONTEXT_SPECIFIC | ASN_DNS_TYPE)) {
5022  DNS_entry* dnsEntry;
5023  int strLen;
5024  word32 lenStartIdx = idx;
5025 
5026  if (GetLength(input, &idx, &strLen, sz) < 0) {
5027  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tfail: str length");
5028  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5029  }
5030  length -= (idx - lenStartIdx);
5031 
5032  dnsEntry = (DNS_entry*)XMALLOC(sizeof(DNS_entry), cert->heap,
5033  DYNAMIC_TYPE_ALTNAME);
5034  if (dnsEntry == NULL) {
5035  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tOut of Memory");
5036  return MEMORY_E;
5037  }
5038 
5039  dnsEntry->name = (char*)XMALLOC(strLen + 1, cert->heap,
5040  DYNAMIC_TYPE_ALTNAME);
5041  if (dnsEntry->name == NULL) {
5042  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tOut of Memory");
5043  XFREE(dnsEntry, cert->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_ALTNAME);
5044  return MEMORY_E;
5045  }
5046 
5047  XMEMCPY(dnsEntry->name, &input[idx], strLen);
5048  dnsEntry->name[strLen] = '\0';
5049 
5050  dnsEntry->next = cert->altNames;
5051  cert->altNames = dnsEntry;
5052 
5053  length -= strLen;
5054  idx += strLen;
5055  }
5056  #ifndef IGNORE_NAME_CONSTRAINTS
5057  else if (b == (ASN_CONTEXT_SPECIFIC | ASN_RFC822_TYPE)) {
5058  DNS_entry* emailEntry;
5059  int strLen;
5060  word32 lenStartIdx = idx;
5061 
5062  if (GetLength(input, &idx, &strLen, sz) < 0) {
5063  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tfail: str length");
5064  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5065  }
5066  length -= (idx - lenStartIdx);
5067 
5068  emailEntry = (DNS_entry*)XMALLOC(sizeof(DNS_entry), cert->heap,
5069  DYNAMIC_TYPE_ALTNAME);
5070  if (emailEntry == NULL) {
5071  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tOut of Memory");
5072  return MEMORY_E;
5073  }
5074 
5075  emailEntry->name = (char*)XMALLOC(strLen + 1, cert->heap,
5076  DYNAMIC_TYPE_ALTNAME);
5077  if (emailEntry->name == NULL) {
5078  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tOut of Memory");
5079  XFREE(emailEntry, cert->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_ALTNAME);
5080  return MEMORY_E;
5081  }
5082 
5083  XMEMCPY(emailEntry->name, &input[idx], strLen);
5084  emailEntry->name[strLen] = '\0';
5085 
5086  emailEntry->next = cert->altEmailNames;
5087  cert->altEmailNames = emailEntry;
5088 
5089  length -= strLen;
5090  idx += strLen;
5091  }
5092  #endif /* IGNORE_NAME_CONSTRAINTS */
5093  #ifdef WOLFSSL_SEP
5094  else if (b == (ASN_CONTEXT_SPECIFIC | ASN_CONSTRUCTED | ASN_OTHER_TYPE))
5095  {
5096  int strLen;
5097  word32 lenStartIdx = idx;
5098  word32 oid = 0;
5099  int ret;
5100 
5101  if (GetLength(input, &idx, &strLen, sz) < 0) {
5102  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tfail: other name length");
5103  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5104  }
5105  /* Consume the rest of this sequence. */
5106  length -= (strLen + idx - lenStartIdx);
5107 
5108  if (GetObjectId(input, &idx, &oid, oidCertAltNameType, sz) < 0) {
5109  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tbad OID");
5110  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5111  }
5112 
5113  if (oid != HW_NAME_OID) {
5114  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tincorrect OID");
5115  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5116  }
5117 
5118  if (input[idx++] != (ASN_CONTEXT_SPECIFIC | ASN_CONSTRUCTED)) {
5119  WOLFSSL_MSG("\twrong type");
5120  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5121  }
5122 
5123  if (GetLength(input, &idx, &strLen, sz) < 0) {
5124  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tfail: str len");
5125  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5126  }
5127 
5128  if (GetSequence(input, &idx, &strLen, sz) < 0) {
5129  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tBad Sequence");
5130  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5131  }
5132 
5133  ret = GetASNObjectId(input, &idx, &strLen, sz);
5134  if (ret != 0) {
5135  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tbad OID");
5136  return ret;
5137  }
5138 
5139  cert->hwType = (byte*)XMALLOC(strLen, cert->heap,
5140  DYNAMIC_TYPE_X509_EXT);
5141  if (cert->hwType == NULL) {
5142  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tOut of Memory");
5143  return MEMORY_E;
5144  }
5145 
5146  XMEMCPY(cert->hwType, &input[idx], strLen);
5147  cert->hwTypeSz = strLen;
5148  idx += strLen;
5149 
5150  ret = GetOctetString(input, &idx, &strLen, sz);
5151  if (ret < 0)
5152  return ret;
5153 
5154  cert->hwSerialNum = (byte*)XMALLOC(strLen + 1, cert->heap,
5155  DYNAMIC_TYPE_X509_EXT);
5156  if (cert->hwSerialNum == NULL) {
5157  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tOut of Memory");
5158  return MEMORY_E;
5159  }
5160 
5161  XMEMCPY(cert->hwSerialNum, &input[idx], strLen);
5162  cert->hwSerialNum[strLen] = '\0';
5163  cert->hwSerialNumSz = strLen;
5164  idx += strLen;
5165  }
5166  #endif /* WOLFSSL_SEP */
5167  else {
5168  int strLen;
5169  word32 lenStartIdx = idx;
5170 
5171  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tUnsupported name type, skipping");
5172 
5173  if (GetLength(input, &idx, &strLen, sz) < 0) {
5174  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tfail: unsupported name length");
5175  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5176  }
5177  length -= (strLen + idx - lenStartIdx);
5178  idx += strLen;
5179  }
5180  }
5181  return 0;
5182 }
5183 
5184 static int DecodeBasicCaConstraint(byte* input, int sz, DecodedCert* cert)
5185 {
5186  word32 idx = 0;
5187  int length = 0;
5188  int ret;
5189 
5190  WOLFSSL_ENTER("DecodeBasicCaConstraint");
5191 
5192  if (GetSequence(input, &idx, &length, sz) < 0) {
5193  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tfail: bad SEQUENCE");
5194  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5195  }
5196 
5197  if (length == 0)
5198  return 0;
5199 
5200  /* If the basic ca constraint is false, this extension may be named, but
5201  * left empty. So, if the length is 0, just return. */
5202 
5203  ret = GetBoolean(input, &idx, sz);
5204  if (ret < 0) {
5205  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tfail: constraint not valid BOOLEAN");
5206  return ret;
5207  }
5208 
5209  cert->isCA = (byte)ret;
5210 
5211  /* If there isn't any more data, return. */
5212  if (idx >= (word32)sz)
5213  return 0;
5214 
5215  ret = GetInteger7Bit(input, &idx, sz);
5216  if (ret < 0)
5217  return ret;
5218 
5219  cert->pathLength = (byte)ret;
5220  cert->pathLengthSet = 1;
5221 
5222  return 0;
5223 }
5224 
5225 
5226 #define CRLDP_FULL_NAME 0
5227  /* From RFC3280 SS4.2.1.14, Distribution Point Name*/
5228 #define GENERALNAME_URI 6
5229  /* From RFC3280 SS4.2.1.7, GeneralName */
5230 
5231 static int DecodeCrlDist(byte* input, int sz, DecodedCert* cert)
5232 {
5233  word32 idx = 0;
5234  int length = 0;
5235 
5236  WOLFSSL_ENTER("DecodeCrlDist");
5237 
5238  /* Unwrap the list of Distribution Points*/
5239  if (GetSequence(input, &idx, &length, sz) < 0)
5240  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5241 
5242  /* Unwrap a single Distribution Point */
5243  if (GetSequence(input, &idx, &length, sz) < 0)
5244  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5245 
5246  /* The Distribution Point has three explicit optional members
5247  * First check for a DistributionPointName
5248  */
5249  if (input[idx] == (ASN_CONSTRUCTED | ASN_CONTEXT_SPECIFIC | 0))
5250  {
5251  idx++;
5252  if (GetLength(input, &idx, &length, sz) < 0)
5253  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5254 
5255  if (input[idx] ==
5256  (ASN_CONTEXT_SPECIFIC | ASN_CONSTRUCTED | CRLDP_FULL_NAME))
5257  {
5258  idx++;
5259  if (GetLength(input, &idx, &length, sz) < 0)
5260  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5261 
5262  if (input[idx] == (ASN_CONTEXT_SPECIFIC | GENERALNAME_URI))
5263  {
5264  idx++;
5265  if (GetLength(input, &idx, &length, sz) < 0)
5266  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5267 
5268  cert->extCrlInfoSz = length;
5269  cert->extCrlInfo = input + idx;
5270  idx += length;
5271  }
5272  else
5273  /* This isn't a URI, skip it. */
5274  idx += length;
5275  }
5276  else {
5277  /* This isn't a FULLNAME, skip it. */
5278  idx += length;
5279  }
5280  }
5281 
5282  /* Check for reasonFlags */
5283  if (idx < (word32)sz &&
5284  input[idx] == (ASN_CONSTRUCTED | ASN_CONTEXT_SPECIFIC | 1))
5285  {
5286  idx++;
5287  if (GetLength(input, &idx, &length, sz) < 0)
5288  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5289  idx += length;
5290  }
5291 
5292  /* Check for cRLIssuer */
5293  if (idx < (word32)sz &&
5294  input[idx] == (ASN_CONSTRUCTED | ASN_CONTEXT_SPECIFIC | 2))
5295  {
5296  idx++;
5297  if (GetLength(input, &idx, &length, sz) < 0)
5298  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5299  idx += length;
5300  }
5301 
5302  if (idx < (word32)sz)
5303  {
5304  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tThere are more CRL Distribution Point records, "
5305  "but we only use the first one.");
5306  }
5307 
5308  return 0;
5309 }
5310

5312 static int DecodeAuthInfo(byte* input, int sz, DecodedCert* cert)
5313 /*
5314  * Read the first of the Authority Information Access records. If there are
5315  * any issues, return without saving the record.
5316  */
5317 {
5318  word32 idx = 0;
5319  int length = 0;
5320  byte b;
5321  word32 oid;
5322 
5323  WOLFSSL_ENTER("DecodeAuthInfo");
5324 
5325  /* Unwrap the list of AIAs */
5326  if (GetSequence(input, &idx, &length, sz) < 0)
5327  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5328 
5329  while (idx < (word32)sz) {
5330  /* Unwrap a single AIA */
5331  if (GetSequence(input, &idx, &length, sz) < 0)
5332  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5333 
5334  oid = 0;
5335  if (GetObjectId(input, &idx, &oid, oidCertAuthInfoType, sz) < 0)
5336  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5337 
5338 
5339  /* Only supporting URIs right now. */
5340  b = input[idx++];
5341  if (GetLength(input, &idx, &length, sz) < 0)
5342  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5343 
5344  if (b == (ASN_CONTEXT_SPECIFIC | GENERALNAME_URI) &&
5345  oid == AIA_OCSP_OID)
5346  {
5347  cert->extAuthInfoSz = length;
5348  cert->extAuthInfo = input + idx;
5349  break;
5350  }
5351  idx += length;
5352  }
5353 
5354  return 0;
5355 }

5358 static int DecodeAuthKeyId(byte* input, int sz, DecodedCert* cert)
5359 {
5360  word32 idx = 0;
5361  int length = 0, ret = 0;
5362 
5363  WOLFSSL_ENTER("DecodeAuthKeyId");
5364 
5365  if (GetSequence(input, &idx, &length, sz) < 0) {
5366  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tfail: should be a SEQUENCE\n");
5367  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5368  }
5369 
5370  if (input[idx++] != (ASN_CONTEXT_SPECIFIC | 0)) {
5371  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tinfo: OPTIONAL item 0, not available\n");
5372  return 0;
5373  }
5374 
5375  if (GetLength(input, &idx, &length, sz) <= 0) {
5376  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tfail: extension data length");
5377  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5378  }
5379 
5380 #ifdef OPENSSL_EXTRA
5381  cert->extAuthKeyIdSrc = &input[idx];
5382  cert->extAuthKeyIdSz = length;
5383 #endif /* OPENSSL_EXTRA */
5384 
5385  if (length == KEYID_SIZE) {
5386  XMEMCPY(cert->extAuthKeyId, input + idx, length);
5387  }
5388  else {
5389  #ifdef NO_SHA
5390  ret = wc_Sha256Hash(input + idx, length, cert->extAuthKeyId);
5391  #else
5392  ret = wc_ShaHash(input + idx, length, cert->extAuthKeyId);
5393  #endif
5394  }
5395

5434 static int DecodeKeyUsage(byte* input, int sz, DecodedCert* cert)
5435 {
5436  word32 idx = 0;
5437  int length;
5438  int ret;
5439  WOLFSSL_ENTER("DecodeKeyUsage");
5440 
5441  ret = CheckBitString(input, &idx, &length, sz, 0, NULL);
5442  if (ret != 0)
5443  return ret;
5444 
5445  cert->extKeyUsage = (word16)(input[idx]);
5446  if (length == 2)
5447  cert->extKeyUsage |= (word16)(input[idx+1] << 8);
5448 
5449  return 0;

5453 static int DecodeExtKeyUsage(byte* input, int sz, DecodedCert* cert)
5454 {
5455  word32 idx = 0, oid;
5456  int length;
5457 
5458  WOLFSSL_ENTER("DecodeExtKeyUsage");
5459 
5460  if (GetSequence(input, &idx, &length, sz) < 0) {
5461  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tfail: should be a SEQUENCE");
5462  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5463  }
5464 
5465 #ifdef OPENSSL_EXTRA
5466  cert->extExtKeyUsageSrc = input + idx;
5467  cert->extExtKeyUsageSz = length;
5468 #endif
5469 
5470  while (idx < (word32)sz) {
5471  if (GetObjectId(input, &idx, &oid, oidCertKeyUseType, sz) < 0)
5472  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5473 
5474  switch (oid) {
5475  case EKU_ANY_OID:
5476  cert->extExtKeyUsage |= EXTKEYUSE_ANY;
5477  break;
5478  case EKU_SERVER_AUTH_OID:
5479  cert->extExtKeyUsage |= EXTKEYUSE_SERVER_AUTH;
5480  break;
5481  case EKU_CLIENT_AUTH_OID:
5482  cert->extExtKeyUsage |= EXTKEYUSE_CLIENT_AUTH;
5483  break;
5484  case EKU_OCSP_SIGN_OID:
5485  cert->extExtKeyUsage |= EXTKEYUSE_OCSP_SIGN;
5486  break;
5487  }
5488 
5489  #ifdef OPENSSL_EXTRA
5490  cert->extExtKeyUsageCount++;
5491  #endif
5492  }
5493 
5494  return 0;
5495 }
5496 
5497 
5498 #ifndef IGNORE_NAME_CONSTRAINTS
5499 #define ASN_TYPE_MASK 0xF
5500 static int DecodeSubtree(byte* input, int sz, Base_entry** head, void* heap)
5501 {
5502  word32 idx = 0;
5503 
5504  (void)heap;
5505 
5506  while (idx < (word32)sz) {
5507  int seqLength, strLength;
5508  word32 nameIdx;
5509  byte b, bType;
5510 
5511  if (GetSequence(input, &idx, &seqLength, sz) < 0) {
5512  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tfail: should be a SEQUENCE");
5513  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5514  }
5515  nameIdx = idx;
5516  b = input[nameIdx++];
5517 
5518  if (GetLength(input, &nameIdx, &strLength, sz) <= 0) {
5519  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tinvalid length");
5520  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5521  }
5522 
5523  /* Get type, LSB 4-bits */
5524  bType = (b & ASN_TYPE_MASK);
5525 
5526  if (bType == ASN_DNS_TYPE || bType == ASN_RFC822_TYPE ||
5527  bType == ASN_DIR_TYPE) {
5528  Base_entry* entry;
5529 
5530  /* if constructed has leading sequence */
5531  if (b & ASN_CONSTRUCTED) {
5532  if (GetSequence(input, &nameIdx, &strLength, sz) < 0) {
5533  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tfail: constructed be a SEQUENCE");
5534  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5535  }
5536  }
5537 
5538  entry = (Base_entry*)XMALLOC(sizeof(Base_entry), heap,
5539  DYNAMIC_TYPE_ALTNAME);
5540  if (entry == NULL) {
5541  WOLFSSL_MSG("allocate error");
5542  return MEMORY_E;
5543  }
5544 
5545  entry->name = (char*)XMALLOC(strLength, heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_ALTNAME);
5546  if (entry->name == NULL) {
5547  WOLFSSL_MSG("allocate error");
5548  XFREE(entry, heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_ALTNAME);
5549  return MEMORY_E;
5550  }
5551 
5552  XMEMCPY(entry->name, &input[nameIdx], strLength);
5553  entry->nameSz = strLength;
5554  entry->type = bType;
5555 
5556  entry->next = *head;
5557  *head = entry;
5558  }
5559 
5560  idx += seqLength;
5561  }
5562 
5563  return 0;
5564 }
5565

5567 static int DecodeNameConstraints(byte* input, int sz, DecodedCert* cert)
5568 {
5569  word32 idx = 0;
5570  int length = 0;
5571 
5572  WOLFSSL_ENTER("DecodeNameConstraints");
5573 
5574  if (GetSequence(input, &idx, &length, sz) < 0) {
5575  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tfail: should be a SEQUENCE");
5576  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5577  }
5578 
5579  while (idx < (word32)sz) {
5580  byte b = input[idx++];
5581  Base_entry** subtree = NULL;
5582 
5583  if (GetLength(input, &idx, &length, sz) <= 0) {
5584  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tinvalid length");
5585  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5586  }
5587 
5588  if (b == (ASN_CONTEXT_SPECIFIC | ASN_CONSTRUCTED | 0))
5589  subtree = &cert->permittedNames;
5590  else if (b == (ASN_CONTEXT_SPECIFIC | ASN_CONSTRUCTED | 1))
5591  subtree = &cert->excludedNames;
5592  else {
5593  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tinvalid subtree");
5594  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5595  }
5596 
5597  DecodeSubtree(input + idx, length, subtree, cert->heap);
5598 
5599  idx += length;
5600  }
5601 
5602  return 0;
5603 }
5604 #endif /* IGNORE_NAME_CONSTRAINTS */
5605 
5606 
5607 #if defined(WOLFSSL_CERT_EXT) && !defined(WOLFSSL_SEP)
5608 
5609 static int Word32ToString(char* d, word32 number)
5610 {
5611  int i = 0;
5612 
5613  if (d != NULL) {
5614  word32 order = 1000000000;
5615  word32 digit;
5616 
5617  if (number == 0) {
5618  d[i++] = '0';
5619  }
5620  else {
5621  while (order) {
5622  digit = number / order;
5623  if (i > 0 || digit != 0) {
5624  d[i++] = (char)digit + '0';
5625  }
5626  if (digit != 0)
5627  number %= digit * order;
5628  if (order > 1)
5629  order /= 10;
5630  else
5631  order = 0;
5632  }
5633  }
5634  d[i] = 0;
5635  }
5636 
5637  return i;
5638 }
5639 
5640 
5641 /* Decode ITU-T X.690 OID format to a string representation
5642  * return string length */
5643 static int DecodePolicyOID(char *out, word32 outSz, byte *in, word32 inSz)
5644 {
5645  word32 val, idx = 0, nb_bytes;
5646  size_t w_bytes = 0;
5647 
5648  if (out == NULL || in == NULL || outSz < 4 || inSz < 2)
5649  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
5650 
5651  /* first two byte must be interpreted as : 40 * int1 + int2 */
5652  val = (word16)in[idx++];
5653 
5654  w_bytes = Word32ToString(out, val / 40);
5655  out[w_bytes++] = '.';
5656  w_bytes += Word32ToString(out+w_bytes, val % 40);
5657 
5658  while (idx < inSz) {
5659  /* init value */
5660  val = 0;
5661  nb_bytes = 0;
5662 
5663  /* check that output size is ok */
5664  if (w_bytes > (outSz - 3))
5665  return BUFFER_E;
5666 
5667  /* first bit is used to set if value is coded on 1 or multiple bytes */
5668  while ((in[idx+nb_bytes] & 0x80))
5669  nb_bytes++;
5670 
5671  if (!nb_bytes)
5672  val = (word32)(in[idx++] & 0x7f);
5673  else {
5674  word32 base = 1, tmp = nb_bytes;
5675 
5676  while (tmp != 0) {
5677  val += (word32)(in[idx+tmp] & 0x7f) * base;
5678  base *= 128;
5679  tmp--;
5680  }
5681  val += (word32)(in[idx++] & 0x7f) * base;
5682 
5683  idx += nb_bytes;
5684  }
5685 
5686  out[w_bytes++] = '.';
5687  w_bytes += Word32ToString(out+w_bytes, val);
5688  }
5689 
5690  return 0;
5691 }
5692 #endif /* WOLFSSL_CERT_EXT && !WOLFSSL_SEP */
5693 
5694 #if defined(WOLFSSL_SEP) || defined(WOLFSSL_CERT_EXT)
5695  /* Reference: https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5280#section-4.2.1.4 */
5696  static int DecodeCertPolicy(byte* input, int sz, DecodedCert* cert)
5697  {
5698  word32 idx = 0;
5699  word32 oldIdx;
5700  int ret;
5701  int total_length = 0, policy_length = 0, length = 0;
5702  #if !defined(WOLFSSL_SEP) && defined(WOLFSSL_CERT_EXT) && \
5703  !defined(WOLFSSL_DUP_CERTPOL)
5704  int i;
5705  #endif
5706 
5707  WOLFSSL_ENTER("DecodeCertPolicy");
5708 
5709  if (GetSequence(input, &idx, &total_length, sz) < 0) {
5710  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tGet CertPolicy total seq failed");
5711  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5712  }
5713 
5714  /* Validate total length */
5715  if (total_length > (sz - (int)idx)) {
5716  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tCertPolicy length mismatch");
5717  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5718  }
5719 
5720  /* Unwrap certificatePolicies */
5721  do {
5722  if (GetSequence(input, &idx, &policy_length, sz) < 0) {
5723  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tGet CertPolicy seq failed");
5724  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5725  }
5726 
5727  oldIdx = idx;
5728  ret = GetASNObjectId(input, &idx, &length, sz);
5729  if (ret != 0)
5730  return ret;
5731  policy_length -= idx - oldIdx;
5732 
5733  if (length > 0) {
5734  /* Verify length won't overrun buffer */
5735  if (length > (sz - (int)idx)) {
5736  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tCertPolicy length exceeds input buffer");
5737  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5738  }
5739 
5740  #if defined(WOLFSSL_SEP)
5741  cert->deviceType = (byte*)XMALLOC(length, cert->heap,
5742  DYNAMIC_TYPE_X509_EXT);
5743  if (cert->deviceType == NULL) {
5744  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tCouldn't alloc memory for deviceType");
5745  return MEMORY_E;
5746  }
5747  cert->deviceTypeSz = length;
5748  XMEMCPY(cert->deviceType, input + idx, length);
5749  break;
5750  #elif defined(WOLFSSL_CERT_EXT)
5751  /* decode cert policy */
5752  if (DecodePolicyOID(cert->extCertPolicies[cert->extCertPoliciesNb],
5753  MAX_CERTPOL_SZ, input + idx, length) != 0) {
5754  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tCouldn't decode CertPolicy");
5755  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5756  }
5757  #ifndef WOLFSSL_DUP_CERTPOL
5758  /* From RFC 5280 section 4.2.1.3 "A certificate policy OID MUST
5759  * NOT appear more than once in a certificate policies
5760  * extension". This is a sanity check for duplicates.
5761  * extCertPolicies should only have OID values, additional
5762  * qualifiers need to be stored in a seperate array. */
5763  for (i = 0; i < cert->extCertPoliciesNb; i++) {
5764  if (XMEMCMP(cert->extCertPolicies[i],
5765  cert->extCertPolicies[cert->extCertPoliciesNb],
5766  MAX_CERTPOL_SZ) == 0) {
5767  WOLFSSL_MSG("Duplicate policy OIDs not allowed");
5768  WOLFSSL_MSG("Use WOLFSSL_DUP_CERTPOL if wanted");
5769  return CERTPOLICIES_E;
5770  }
5771  }
5772  #endif /* !WOLFSSL_DUP_CERTPOL */
5773  cert->extCertPoliciesNb++;
5774  #else
5775  WOLFSSL_LEAVE("DecodeCertPolicy : unsupported mode", 0);
5776  return 0;
5777  #endif
5778  }
5779  idx += policy_length;
5780  } while((int)idx < total_length
5781  #if defined(WOLFSSL_CERT_EXT)
5782  && cert->extCertPoliciesNb < MAX_CERTPOL_NB
5783  #endif
5784  );
5785 
5786  WOLFSSL_LEAVE("DecodeCertPolicy", 0);
5787  return 0;
5788  }
5789 #endif /* WOLFSSL_SEP */
5790 
5791 static int DecodeCertExtensions(DecodedCert* cert)
5792 /*
5793  * Processing the Certificate Extensions. This does not modify the current
5794  * index. It is works starting with the recorded extensions pointer.
5795  */
5796 {
5797  int ret;
5798  word32 idx = 0;
5799  int sz = cert->extensionsSz;
5800  byte* input = cert->extensions;
5801  int length;
5802  word32 oid;
5803  byte critical = 0;
5804  byte criticalFail = 0;
5805 
5806  WOLFSSL_ENTER("DecodeCertExtensions");
5807 
5808  if (input == NULL || sz == 0)
5809  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
5810 
5811  if (input[idx++] != ASN_EXTENSIONS) {
5812  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tfail: should be an EXTENSIONS");
5813  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5814  }
5815 
5816  if (GetLength(input, &idx, &length, sz) < 0) {
5817  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tfail: invalid length");
5818  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5819  }
5820 
5821  if (GetSequence(input, &idx, &length, sz) < 0) {
5822  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tfail: should be a SEQUENCE (1)");
5823  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5824  }
5825 
5826  while (idx < (word32)sz) {
5827  if (GetSequence(input, &idx, &length, sz) < 0) {
5828  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tfail: should be a SEQUENCE");
5829  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5830  }
5831 
5832  oid = 0;
5833  if ((ret = GetObjectId(input, &idx, &oid, oidCertExtType, sz)) < 0) {
5834  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tfail: OBJECT ID");
5835  return ret;
5836  }
5837 
5838  /* check for critical flag */
5839  critical = 0;
5840  if (input[idx] == ASN_BOOLEAN) {
5841  ret = GetBoolean(input, &idx, sz);
5842  if (ret < 0) {
5843  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tfail: critical boolean");
5844  return ret;
5845  }
5846 
5847  critical = (byte)ret;
5848  }
5849 
5850  /* process the extension based on the OID */
5851  ret = GetOctetString(input, &idx, &length, sz);
5852  if (ret < 0) {
5853  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tfail: bad OCTET STRING");
5854  return ret;
5855  }
5856 
5857  switch (oid) {
5858  case BASIC_CA_OID:
5859  #ifdef OPENSSL_EXTRA
5860  cert->extBasicConstSet = 1;
5861  cert->extBasicConstCrit = critical;
5862  #endif
5863  if (DecodeBasicCaConstraint(&input[idx], length, cert) < 0)
5864  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5865  break;
5866 
5867  case CRL_DIST_OID:
5868  #ifdef OPENSSL_EXTRA
5869  cert->extCRLdistSet = 1;
5870  cert->extCRLdistCrit = critical;
5871  #endif
5872  if (DecodeCrlDist(&input[idx], length, cert) < 0)
5873  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5874  break;
5875 
5876  case AUTH_INFO_OID:
5877  #ifdef OPENSSL_EXTRA
5878  cert->extAuthInfoSet = 1;
5879  cert->extAuthInfoCrit = critical;
5880  #endif
5881  if (DecodeAuthInfo(&input[idx], length, cert) < 0)
5882  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5883  break;
5884 
5885  case ALT_NAMES_OID:
5886  #ifdef OPENSSL_EXTRA
5887  cert->extSubjAltNameSet = 1;
5888  cert->extSubjAltNameCrit = critical;
5889  #endif
5890  if (DecodeAltNames(&input[idx], length, cert) < 0)
5891  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5892  break;
5893 
5894  case AUTH_KEY_OID:
5895  cert->extAuthKeyIdSet = 1;
5896  #ifdef OPENSSL_EXTRA
5897  cert->extAuthKeyIdCrit = critical;
5898  #endif
5899  if (DecodeAuthKeyId(&input[idx], length, cert) < 0)
5900  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5901  break;
5902 
5903  case SUBJ_KEY_OID:
5904  cert->extSubjKeyIdSet = 1;
5905  #ifdef OPENSSL_EXTRA
5906  cert->extSubjKeyIdCrit = critical;
5907  #endif
5908  #ifndef WOLFSSL_ALLOW_CRIT_SKID
5909  /* This check is added due to RFC 5280 section 4.2.1.2
5910  * stating that conforming CA's must mark this extension
5911  * as non-critical. When parsing extensions check that
5912  * certificate was made in compliance with this. */
5913  if (critical) {
5914  WOLFSSL_MSG("Critical Subject Key ID is not allowed");
5915  WOLFSSL_MSG("Use macro WOLFSSL_ALLOW_CRIT_SKID if wanted");
5916  return ASN_CRIT_EXT_E;
5917  }
5918  #endif
5919 
5920  if (DecodeSubjKeyId(&input[idx], length, cert) < 0)
5921  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5922  break;
5923 
5924  case CERT_POLICY_OID:
5925  #ifdef WOLFSSL_SEP
5926  #ifdef OPENSSL_EXTRA
5927  cert->extCertPolicySet = 1;
5928  cert->extCertPolicyCrit = critical;
5929  #endif
5930  #endif
5931  #if defined(WOLFSSL_SEP) || defined(WOLFSSL_CERT_EXT)
5932  if (DecodeCertPolicy(&input[idx], length, cert) < 0) {
5933  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5934  }
5935  #else
5936  WOLFSSL_MSG("Certificate Policy extension not supported yet.");
5937  #endif
5938  break;
5939 
5940  case KEY_USAGE_OID:
5941  cert->extKeyUsageSet = 1;
5942  #ifdef OPENSSL_EXTRA
5943  cert->extKeyUsageCrit = critical;
5944  #endif
5945  if (DecodeKeyUsage(&input[idx], length, cert) < 0)
5946  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5947  break;
5948 
5949  case EXT_KEY_USAGE_OID:
5950  cert->extExtKeyUsageSet = 1;
5951  #ifdef OPENSSL_EXTRA
5952  cert->extExtKeyUsageCrit = critical;
5953  #endif
5954  if (DecodeExtKeyUsage(&input[idx], length, cert) < 0)
5955  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5956  break;
5957 
5958  #ifndef IGNORE_NAME_CONSTRAINTS
5959  case NAME_CONS_OID:
5960  cert->extNameConstraintSet = 1;
5961  #ifdef OPENSSL_EXTRA
5962  cert->extNameConstraintCrit = critical;
5963  #endif
5964  if (DecodeNameConstraints(&input[idx], length, cert) < 0)
5965  return ASN_PARSE_E;
5966  break;
5967  #endif /* IGNORE_NAME_CONSTRAINTS */
5968 
5969  case INHIBIT_ANY_OID:
5970  WOLFSSL_MSG("Inhibit anyPolicy extension not supported yet.");
5971  break;
5972 
5973  default:
5974  /* While it is a failure to not support critical extensions,
5975  * still parse the certificate ignoring the unsupported
5976  * extension to allow caller to accept it with the verify
5977  * callback. */
5978  if (critical)
5979  criticalFail = 1;
5980  break;
5981  }
5982  idx += length;
5983  }
5984 
5985  return criticalFail ? ASN_CRIT_EXT_E : 0;
5986 }
5987 
5988 int ParseCert(DecodedCert* cert, int type, int verify, void* cm)
5989 {
5990  int ret;
5991  char* ptr;
5992 
5993  ret = ParseCertRelative(cert, type, verify, cm);
5994  if (ret < 0)
5995  return ret;
5996 
5997  if (cert->subjectCNLen > 0) {
5998  ptr = (char*) XMALLOC(cert->subjectCNLen + 1, cert->heap,
5999  DYNAMIC_TYPE_SUBJECT_CN);
6000  if (ptr == NULL)
6001  return MEMORY_E;
6002  XMEMCPY(ptr, cert->subjectCN, cert->subjectCNLen);
6003  ptr[cert->subjectCNLen] = '\0';
6004  cert->subjectCN = ptr;
6005  cert->subjectCNStored = 1;
6006  }
6007 
6008  if (cert->keyOID == RSAk &&
6009  cert->publicKey != NULL && cert->pubKeySize > 0) {
6010  ptr = (char*) XMALLOC(cert->pubKeySize, cert->heap,
6011  DYNAMIC_TYPE_PUBLIC_KEY);
6012  if (ptr == NULL)
6013  return MEMORY_E;
6014  XMEMCPY(ptr, cert->publicKey, cert->pubKeySize);
6015  cert->publicKey = (byte *)ptr;
6016  cert->pubKeyStored = 1;
6017  }
6018 
6019  return ret;
6020 }

6022 /* from SSL proper, for locking can't do find here anymore */
6023 #ifdef __cplusplus
6024  extern "C" {
6025 #endif
6026  WOLFSSL_LOCAL Signer* GetCA(void* signers, byte* hash);
6027  #ifndef NO_SKID
6028  WOLFSSL_LOCAL Signer* GetCAByName(void* signers, byte* hash);
6029  #endif
6030 #ifdef __cplusplus
6031  }
6032 #endif
6033 
6034 
6035 #if defined(WOLFCRYPT_ONLY) || defined(NO_CERTS)
6036 
6037 /* dummy functions, not using wolfSSL so don't need actual ones */
6038 Signer* GetCA(void* signers, byte* hash)
6039 {
6040  (void)hash;
6041 
6042  return (Signer*)signers;
6043 }
6044 
6045 #ifndef NO_SKID
6046 Signer* GetCAByName(void* signers, byte* hash)
6047 {
6048  (void)hash;
6049 
6050  return (Signer*)signers;
6051 }
6052 #endif /* NO_SKID */
6053 
6054 #endif /* WOLFCRYPT_ONLY || NO_CERTS */
6055 
6056 int ParseCertRelative(DecodedCert* cert, int type, int verify, void* cm)
6057 {
6058  int ret = 0;
6059  int badDate = 0;
6060  int criticalExt = 0;
6061  word32 confirmOID;
6062 
6063  if (cert == NULL) {
6064  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
6065  }
6066 
6067  if (cert->sigCtx.state == SIG_STATE_BEGIN) {
6068  if ((ret = DecodeToKey(cert, verify)) < 0) {
6069  if (ret == ASN_BEFORE_DATE_E || ret == ASN_AFTER_DATE_E)
6070  badDate = ret;
6071  else
6072  return ret;
6073  }
6074 
6075  WOLFSSL_MSG("Parsed Past Key");
6076 
6077  if (cert->srcIdx < cert->sigIndex) {
6078  #ifndef ALLOW_V1_EXTENSIONS
6079  if (cert->version < 2) {
6080  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tv1 and v2 certs not allowed extensions");
6081  return ASN_VERSION_E;
6082  }
6083  #endif
6084 
6085  /* save extensions */
6086  cert->extensions = &cert->source[cert->srcIdx];
6087  cert->extensionsSz = cert->sigIndex - cert->srcIdx;
6088  cert->extensionsIdx = cert->srcIdx; /* for potential later use */
6089 
6090  if ((ret = DecodeCertExtensions(cert)) < 0) {
6091  if (ret == ASN_CRIT_EXT_E)
6092  criticalExt = ret;
6093  else
6094  return ret;
6095  }
6096 
6097  /* advance past extensions */
6098  cert->srcIdx = cert->sigIndex;
6099  }
6100 
6101  if ((ret = GetAlgoId(cert->source, &cert->srcIdx, &confirmOID,
6102  oidSigType, cert->maxIdx)) < 0)
6103  return ret;
6104 
6105  if ((ret = GetSignature(cert)) < 0)
6106  return ret;
6107 
6108  if (confirmOID != cert->signatureOID)
6109  return ASN_SIG_OID_E;
6110 
6111  #ifndef NO_SKID
6112  if (cert->extSubjKeyIdSet == 0 && cert->publicKey != NULL &&
6113  cert->pubKeySize > 0) {
6114  #ifdef NO_SHA
6115  ret = wc_Sha256Hash(cert->publicKey, cert->pubKeySize,
6116  cert->extSubjKeyId);
6117  #else
6118  ret = wc_ShaHash(cert->publicKey, cert->pubKeySize,
6119  cert->extSubjKeyId);
6120  #endif /* NO_SHA */
6121  if (ret != 0)
6122  return ret;
6123  }
6124  #endif /* !NO_SKID */
6125 
6126  if (verify != NO_VERIFY && type != CA_TYPE && type != TRUSTED_PEER_TYPE) {
6127  cert->ca = NULL;
6128  #ifndef NO_SKID
6129  if (cert->extAuthKeyIdSet)
6130  cert->ca = GetCA(cm, cert->extAuthKeyId);
6131  if (cert->ca == NULL)
6132  cert->ca = GetCAByName(cm, cert->issuerHash);
6133 
6134  /* alternate lookup method using subject and match on public key */
6135  #ifdef WOLFSSL_NO_TRUSTED_CERTS_VERIFY
6136  if (cert->ca == NULL && verify == VERIFY_OCSP) {
6137  if (cert->extSubjKeyIdSet) {
6138  cert->ca = GetCA(cm, cert->extSubjKeyId);
6139  }
6140  if (cert->ca == NULL) {
6141  cert->ca = GetCAByName(cm, cert->subjectHash);
6142  }
6143  if (cert->ca) {
6144  if ((cert->ca->pubKeySize == cert->pubKeySize) &&
6145  (XMEMCMP(cert->ca->publicKey, cert->publicKey,
6146  cert->ca->pubKeySize) == 0)) {
6147  ret = 0; /* success */
6148  goto exit_pcr;
6149  }
6150  }
6151  }
6152  #endif /* WOLFSSL_NO_TRUSTED_CERTS_VERIFY */
6153  #else
6154  cert->ca = GetCA(cm, cert->issuerHash);
6155  #endif /* !NO_SKID */
6156 
6157  WOLFSSL_MSG("About to verify certificate signature");
6158  if (cert->ca) {
6159  if (cert->isCA) {
6160  if (cert->ca->pathLengthSet) {
6161  if (cert->ca->pathLength == 0) {
6162  WOLFSSL_MSG("CA with path length 0 signing a CA");
6163  return ASN_PATHLEN_INV_E;
6164  }
6165  if (cert->pathLengthSet &&
6166  cert->pathLength >= cert->ca->pathLength) {
6167 
6168  WOLFSSL_MSG("CA signing CA with longer path length");
6169  return ASN_PATHLEN_INV_E;
6170  }
6171  }
6172  }
6173 
6174  #ifdef HAVE_OCSP
6175  /* Need the CA's public key hash for OCSP */
6176  #ifdef NO_SHA
6177  ret = wc_Sha256Hash(cert->ca->publicKey, cert->ca->pubKeySize,
6178  cert->issuerKeyHash);
6179  #else
6180  ret = wc_ShaHash(cert->ca->publicKey, cert->ca->pubKeySize,
6181  cert->issuerKeyHash);
6182  #endif /* NO_SHA */
6183  if (ret != 0)
6184  return ret;
6185  #endif /* HAVE_OCSP */
6186  }
6187  }
6188  }
6189 
6190  if (verify != NO_VERIFY && type != CA_TYPE && type != TRUSTED_PEER_TYPE) {
6191  if (cert->ca) {
6192  if (verify == VERIFY || verify == VERIFY_OCSP) {
6193  /* try to confirm/verify signature */
6194  if ((ret = ConfirmSignature(&cert->sigCtx,
6195  cert->source + cert->certBegin,
6196  cert->sigIndex - cert->certBegin,
6197  cert->ca->publicKey, cert->ca->pubKeySize,
6198  cert->ca->keyOID, cert->signature,
6199  cert->sigLength, cert->signatureOID)) != 0) {
6200  if (ret != WC_PENDING_E) {
6201  WOLFSSL_MSG("Confirm signature failed");
6202  }
6203  return ret;
6204  }
6205  #ifndef IGNORE_NAME_CONSTRAINTS
6206  /* check that this cert's name is permitted by the signer's
6207  * name constraints */
6208  if (!ConfirmNameConstraints(cert->ca, cert)) {
6209  WOLFSSL_MSG("Confirm name constraint failed");
6210  return ASN_NAME_INVALID_E;
6211  }
6212  #endif /* IGNORE_NAME_CONSTRAINTS */
6213  }
6214  }
6215  else {
6216  /* no signer */
6217  WOLFSSL_MSG("No CA signer to verify with");
6218  return ASN_NO_SIGNER_E;
6219  }
6220  }
6221 
6222 #ifdef WOLFSSL_NO_TRUSTED_CERTS_VERIFY
6223 exit_pcr:
6224 #endif
6225 
6226  if (badDate != 0)
6227  return badDate;
6228 
6229  if (criticalExt != 0)
6230  return criticalExt;
6231 
6232  return ret;
6233 }
6234 
6235 /* Create and init an new signer */
6236 Signer* MakeSigner(void* heap)
6237 {
6238  Signer* signer = (Signer*) XMALLOC(sizeof(Signer), heap,
6239  DYNAMIC_TYPE_SIGNER);
6240  if (signer) {
6241  signer->pubKeySize = 0;
6242  signer->keyOID = 0;
6243  signer->publicKey = NULL;
6244  signer->nameLen = 0;
6245  signer->name = NULL;
6246  #ifndef IGNORE_NAME_CONSTRAINTS
6247  signer->permittedNames = NULL;
6248  signer->excludedNames = NULL;
6249  #endif /* IGNORE_NAME_CONSTRAINTS */
6250  signer->pathLengthSet = 0;
6251  signer->pathLength = 0;
6252  signer->next = NULL;
6253  }
6254  (void)heap;
6255 
6256  return signer;
6257 }
6258 
6259 
6260 /* Free an individual signer */
6261 void FreeSigner(Signer* signer, void* heap)
6262 {
6263  XFREE(signer->name, heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_SUBJECT_CN);
6264  XFREE(signer->publicKey, heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_PUBLIC_KEY);
6265 #ifndef IGNORE_NAME_CONSTRAINTS
6266  if (signer->permittedNames)
6267  FreeNameSubtrees(signer->permittedNames, heap);
6268  if (signer->excludedNames)
6269  FreeNameSubtrees(signer->excludedNames, heap);
6270 #endif
6271  XFREE(signer, heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_SIGNER);
6272 
6273  (void)heap;
6274 }

6277 /* Free the whole singer table with number of rows */
6278 void FreeSignerTable(Signer** table, int rows, void* heap)
6279 {
6280  int i;
6281 
6282  for (i = 0; i < rows; i++) {
6283  Signer* signer = table[i];
6284  while (signer) {
6285  Signer* next = signer->next;
6286  FreeSigner(signer, heap);
6287  signer = next;
6288  }
6289  table[i] = NULL;
6290  }
6291 }

6293 #ifdef WOLFSSL_TRUST_PEER_CERT
6294 /* Free an individual trusted peer cert */
6295 void FreeTrustedPeer(TrustedPeerCert* tp, void* heap)
6296 {
6297  if (tp == NULL) {
6298  return;
6299  }
6300 
6301  if (tp->name) {
6302  XFREE(tp->name, heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_SUBJECT_CN);
6303  }
6304 
6305  if (tp->sig) {
6306  XFREE(tp->sig, heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_SIGNATURE);
6307  }
6308 #ifndef IGNORE_NAME_CONSTRAINTS
6309  if (tp->permittedNames)
6310  FreeNameSubtrees(tp->permittedNames, heap);
6311  if (tp->excludedNames)
6312  FreeNameSubtrees(tp->excludedNames, heap);
6313 #endif
6314  XFREE(tp, heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_CERT);
6315 
6316  (void)heap;
6317 }
6318 
6319 /* Free the whole Trusted Peer linked list */
6320 void FreeTrustedPeerTable(TrustedPeerCert** table, int rows, void* heap)
6321 {
6322  int i;
6323 
6324  for (i = 0; i < rows; i++) {
6325  TrustedPeerCert* tp = table[i];
6326  while (tp) {
6327  TrustedPeerCert* next = tp->next;
6328  FreeTrustedPeer(tp, heap);
6329  tp = next;
6330  }
6331  table[i] = NULL;
6332  }
6333 }
6334 #endif /* WOLFSSL_TRUST_PEER_CERT */

6336 WOLFSSL_LOCAL int SetMyVersion(word32 version, byte* output, int header)
6337 {
6338  int i = 0;
6339 
6340  if (output == NULL)
6341  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
6342 
6343  if (header) {
6344  output[i++] = ASN_CONTEXT_SPECIFIC | ASN_CONSTRUCTED;
6345  output[i++] = 3;
6346  }
6347  output[i++] = ASN_INTEGER;
6348  output[i++] = 0x01;
6349  output[i++] = (byte)version;
6350 
6351  return i;
6352 }

6355 WOLFSSL_LOCAL int SetSerialNumber(const byte* sn, word32 snSz, byte* output)
6356 {
6357  int result = 0;
6358 
6359  WOLFSSL_ENTER("SetSerialNumber");
6360 
6361  if (sn == NULL || output == NULL)
6362  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
6363 
6364  if (snSz <= EXTERNAL_SERIAL_SIZE) {
6365  output[0] = ASN_INTEGER;
6366  /* The serial number is always positive. When encoding the
6367  * INTEGER, if the MSB is 1, add a padding zero to keep the
6368  * number positive. */
6369  if (sn[0] & 0x80) {
6370  output[1] = (byte)snSz + 1;
6371  output[2] = 0;
6372  XMEMCPY(&output[3], sn, snSz);
6373  result = snSz + 3;
6374  }
6375  else {
6376  output[1] = (byte)snSz;
6377  XMEMCPY(&output[2], sn, snSz);
6378  result = snSz + 2;
6379  }
6380  }
6381  return result;
6382 }
6383 
6384 WOLFSSL_LOCAL int GetSerialNumber(const byte* input, word32* inOutIdx,
6385  byte* serial, int* serialSz, word32 maxIdx)
6386 {
6387  int result = 0;
6388  int ret;
6389 
6390  WOLFSSL_ENTER("GetSerialNumber");
6391 
6392  if (serial == NULL || input == NULL || serialSz == NULL) {
6393  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
6394  }
6395 
6396  /* First byte is ASN type */
6397  if ((*inOutIdx+1) > maxIdx) {
6398  WOLFSSL_MSG("Bad idx first");
6399  return BUFFER_E;
6400  }
6401 
6402  ret = GetASNInt(input, inOutIdx, serialSz, maxIdx);
6403  if (ret != 0)
6404  return ret;
6405 
6406  if (*serialSz > EXTERNAL_SERIAL_SIZE) {
6407  WOLFSSL_MSG("Serial size bad");
6408  return ASN_PARSE_E;
6409  }
6410 
6411  /* return serial */
6412  XMEMCPY(serial, &input[*inOutIdx], *serialSz);
6413  *inOutIdx += *serialSz;
6414 
6415  return result;
6416 }

6420 const char* BEGIN_CERT = "-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----";
6421 const char* END_CERT = "-----END CERTIFICATE-----";
6422 const char* BEGIN_CERT_REQ = "-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE REQUEST-----";
6423 const char* END_CERT_REQ = "-----END CERTIFICATE REQUEST-----";
6424 const char* BEGIN_DH_PARAM = "-----BEGIN DH PARAMETERS-----";
6425 const char* END_DH_PARAM = "-----END DH PARAMETERS-----";
6426 const char* BEGIN_DSA_PARAM = "-----BEGIN DSA PARAMETERS-----";
6427 const char* END_DSA_PARAM = "-----END DSA PARAMETERS-----";
6428 const char* BEGIN_X509_CRL = "-----BEGIN X509 CRL-----";
6429 const char* END_X509_CRL = "-----END X509 CRL-----";
6430 const char* BEGIN_RSA_PRIV = "-----BEGIN RSA PRIVATE KEY-----";
6431 const char* END_RSA_PRIV = "-----END RSA PRIVATE KEY-----";
6432 const char* BEGIN_PRIV_KEY = "-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----";
6433 const char* END_PRIV_KEY = "-----END PRIVATE KEY-----";
6434 const char* BEGIN_ENC_PRIV_KEY = "-----BEGIN ENCRYPTED PRIVATE KEY-----";
6435 const char* END_ENC_PRIV_KEY = "-----END ENCRYPTED PRIVATE KEY-----";
6436 const char* BEGIN_EC_PRIV = "-----BEGIN EC PRIVATE KEY-----";
6437 const char* END_EC_PRIV = "-----END EC PRIVATE KEY-----";
6438 const char* BEGIN_DSA_PRIV = "-----BEGIN DSA PRIVATE KEY-----";
6439 const char* END_DSA_PRIV = "-----END DSA PRIVATE KEY-----";
6440 const char* BEGIN_PUB_KEY = "-----BEGIN PUBLIC KEY-----";
6441 const char* END_PUB_KEY = "-----END PUBLIC KEY-----";
6442 const char* BEGIN_EDDSA_PRIV = "-----BEGIN EDDSA PRIVATE KEY-----";
6443 const char* END_EDDSA_PRIV = "-----END EDDSA PRIVATE KEY-----";
6444 
6445 #if defined(WOLFSSL_KEY_GEN) || defined(WOLFSSL_CERT_GEN) || defined(OPENSSL_EXTRA)
6446 
6447 /* Used for compatibility API */
6448 int wc_DerToPem(const byte* der, word32 derSz,
6449  byte* output, word32 outSz, int type)
6450 {
6451  return wc_DerToPemEx(der, derSz, output, outSz, NULL, type);
6452 }
6453 
6454 /* convert der buffer to pem into output, can't do inplace, der and output
6455  need to be different */
6456 int wc_DerToPemEx(const byte* der, word32 derSz, byte* output, word32 outSz,
6457  byte *cipher_info, int type)
6458 {
6459 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
6460  char* header = NULL;
6461  char* footer = NULL;
6462 #else
6463  char header[40 + HEADER_ENCRYPTED_KEY_SIZE];
6464  char footer[40];
6465 #endif
6466 
6467  int headerLen = 40 + HEADER_ENCRYPTED_KEY_SIZE;
6468  int footerLen = 40;
6469  int i;
6470  int err;
6471  int outLen; /* return length or error */
6472 
6473  if (der == output) /* no in place conversion */
6474  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
6475 
6476 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
6477  header = (char*)XMALLOC(headerLen, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
6478  if (header == NULL)
6479  return MEMORY_E;
6480 
6481  footer = (char*)XMALLOC(footerLen, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
6482  if (footer == NULL) {
6483  XFREE(header, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
6484  return MEMORY_E;
6485  }
6486 #endif
6487  if (type == CERT_TYPE) {
6488  XSTRNCPY(header, BEGIN_CERT, headerLen);
6489  XSTRNCAT(header, "\n", 1);
6490 
6491  XSTRNCPY(footer, END_CERT, footerLen);
6492  XSTRNCAT(footer, "\n", 1);
6493  }
6494  else if (type == PRIVATEKEY_TYPE) {
6495  XSTRNCPY(header, BEGIN_RSA_PRIV, headerLen);
6496  XSTRNCAT(header, "\n", 1);
6497 
6498  XSTRNCPY(footer, END_RSA_PRIV, footerLen);
6499  XSTRNCAT(footer, "\n", 1);
6500  }
6501 #ifndef NO_DSA
6502  else if (type == DSA_PRIVATEKEY_TYPE) {
6503  XSTRNCPY(header, BEGIN_DSA_PRIV, headerLen);
6504  XSTRNCAT(header, "\n", 1);
6505 
6506  XSTRNCPY(footer, END_DSA_PRIV, footerLen);
6507  XSTRNCAT(footer, "\n", 1);
6508  }
6509 #endif
6510 #ifdef HAVE_ECC
6511  else if (type == ECC_PRIVATEKEY_TYPE) {
6512  XSTRNCPY(header, BEGIN_EC_PRIV, headerLen);
6513  XSTRNCAT(header, "\n", 1);
6514 
6515  XSTRNCPY(footer, END_EC_PRIV, footerLen);
6516  XSTRNCAT(footer, "\n", 1);
6517  }
6518 #endif
6519 #ifdef HAVE_ED25519
6520  else if (type == EDDSA_PRIVATEKEY_TYPE) {
6521  XSTRNCPY(header, BEGIN_EDDSA_PRIV, headerLen);
6522  XSTRNCAT(header, "\n", 1);
6523 
6524  XSTRNCPY(footer, END_EDDSA_PRIV, footerLen);
6525  XSTRNCAT(footer, "\n", 1);
6526  }
6527 #endif
6528 #ifdef WOLFSSL_CERT_REQ
6529  else if (type == CERTREQ_TYPE)
6530  {
6531  XSTRNCPY(header, BEGIN_CERT_REQ, headerLen);
6532  XSTRNCAT(header, "\n", 1);
6533 
6534  XSTRNCPY(footer, END_CERT_REQ, footerLen);
6535  XSTRNCAT(footer, "\n", 1);
6536  }
6537 #endif
6538 #ifdef HAVE_CRL
6539  else if (type == CRL_TYPE)
6540  {
6541  XSTRNCPY(header, BEGIN_X509_CRL, headerLen);
6542  XSTRNCAT(header, "\n", 1);
6543 
6544  XSTRNCPY(footer, END_X509_CRL, footerLen);
6545  XSTRNCAT(footer, "\n", 1);
6546  }
6547 #endif
6548  else {
6549 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
6550  XFREE(header, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
6551  XFREE(footer, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
6552 #endif
6553  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
6554  }
6555 
6556  /* extra header information for encrypted key */
6557  if (cipher_info != NULL) {
6558  size_t cipherInfoStrLen = XSTRLEN((char*)cipher_info);
6559  if (cipherInfoStrLen > HEADER_ENCRYPTED_KEY_SIZE - (23+10+2))
6560  cipherInfoStrLen = HEADER_ENCRYPTED_KEY_SIZE - (23+10+2);
6561 
6562  XSTRNCAT(header, "Proc-Type: 4,ENCRYPTED\n", 23);
6563  XSTRNCAT(header, "DEK-Info: ", 10);
6564  XSTRNCAT(header, (char*)cipher_info, cipherInfoStrLen);
6565  XSTRNCAT(header, "\n\n", 2);
6566  }
6567 
6568  headerLen = (int)XSTRLEN(header);
6569  footerLen = (int)XSTRLEN(footer);
6570 
6571  /* if null output and 0 size passed in then return size needed */
6572  if (!output && outSz == 0) {
6573 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
6574  XFREE(header, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
6575  XFREE(footer, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
6576 #endif
6577  outLen = 0;
6578  if ((err = Base64_Encode(der, derSz, NULL, (word32*)&outLen))
6579  != LENGTH_ONLY_E) {
6580  return err;
6581  }
6582  return headerLen + footerLen + outLen;
6583  }
6584 
6585  if (!der || !output) {
6586 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
6587  XFREE(header, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
6588  XFREE(footer, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
6589 #endif
6590  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
6591  }
6592 
6593  /* don't even try if outSz too short */
6594  if (outSz < headerLen + footerLen + derSz) {
6595 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
6596  XFREE(header, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
6597  XFREE(footer, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
6598 #endif
6599  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
6600  }
6601 
6602  /* header */
6603  XMEMCPY(output, header, headerLen);
6604  i = headerLen;
6605 
6606 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
6607  XFREE(header, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
6608 #endif
6609 
6610  /* body */
6611  outLen = outSz - (headerLen + footerLen); /* input to Base64_Encode */
6612  if ( (err = Base64_Encode(der, derSz, output + i, (word32*)&outLen)) < 0) {
6613 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
6614  XFREE(footer, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
6615 #endif
6616  return err;
6617  }
6618  i += outLen;
6619 
6620  /* footer */
6621  if ( (i + footerLen) > (int)outSz) {
6622 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
6623  XFREE(footer, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
6624 #endif
6625  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
6626  }
6627  XMEMCPY(output + i, footer, footerLen);
6628 
6629 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
6630  XFREE(footer, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
6631 #endif
6632 
6633  return outLen + headerLen + footerLen;
6634 }
6635 
6636 #endif /* WOLFSSL_KEY_GEN || WOLFSSL_CERT_GEN */
6637 
6638 #if !defined(NO_RSA) && (defined(WOLFSSL_CERT_GEN) || (defined(WOLFSSL_KEY_GEN) && !defined(HAVE_USER_RSA)))
6639 /* USER RSA ifdef portions used instead of refactor in consideration for
6640  possible fips build */
6641 /* Write a public RSA key to output */
6642 static int SetRsaPublicKey(byte* output, RsaKey* key,
6643  int outLen, int with_header)
6644 {
6645 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
6646  byte* n = NULL;
6647  byte* e = NULL;
6648 #else
6649  byte n[MAX_RSA_INT_SZ];
6650  byte e[MAX_RSA_E_SZ];
6651 #endif
6652  byte seq[MAX_SEQ_SZ];
6653  byte bitString[1 + MAX_LENGTH_SZ + 1];
6654  int nSz;
6655  int eSz;
6656  int seqSz;
6657  int bitStringSz;
6658  int idx;
6659 
6660  if (output == NULL || key == NULL || outLen < MAX_SEQ_SZ)
6661  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
6662 
6663  /* n */
6664 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
6665  n = (byte*)XMALLOC(MAX_RSA_INT_SZ, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
6666  if (n == NULL)
6667  return MEMORY_E;
6668 #endif
6669 
6670 #ifdef HAVE_USER_RSA
6671  nSz = SetASNIntRSA(key->n, n);
6672 #else
6673  nSz = SetASNIntMP(&key->n, MAX_RSA_INT_SZ, n);
6674 #endif
6675  if (nSz < 0) {
6676 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
6677  XFREE(n, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
6678 #endif
6679  return nSz;
6680  }
6681 
6682  /* e */
6683 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
6684  e = (byte*)XMALLOC(MAX_RSA_E_SZ, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
6685  if (e == NULL) {
6686 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
6687  XFREE(n, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
6688 #endif
6689  return MEMORY_E;
6690  }
6691 #endif
6692 
6693 #ifdef HAVE_USER_RSA
6694  eSz = SetASNIntRSA(key->e, e);
6695 #else
6696  eSz = SetASNIntMP(&key->e, MAX_RSA_INT_SZ, e);
6697 #endif
6698  if (eSz < 0) {
6699 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
6700  XFREE(n, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
6701  XFREE(e, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
6702 #endif
6703  return eSz;
6704  }
6705 
6706  seqSz = SetSequence(nSz + eSz, seq);
6707 
6708  /* check output size */
6709  if ( (seqSz + nSz + eSz) > outLen) {
6710 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
6711  XFREE(n, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
6712  XFREE(e, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
6713 #endif
6714  return BUFFER_E;
6715  }
6716 
6717  /* headers */
6718  if (with_header) {
6719  int algoSz;
6720 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
6721  byte* algo = NULL;
6722 
6723  algo = (byte*)XMALLOC(MAX_ALGO_SZ, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
6724  if (algo == NULL) {
6725  XFREE(n, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
6726  XFREE(e, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
6727  return MEMORY_E;
6728  }
6729 #else
6730  byte algo[MAX_ALGO_SZ];
6731 #endif
6732  algoSz = SetAlgoID(RSAk, algo, oidKeyType, 0);
6733  bitStringSz = SetBitString(seqSz + nSz + eSz, 0, bitString);
6734 
6735  idx = SetSequence(nSz + eSz + seqSz + bitStringSz + algoSz, output);
6736 
6737  /* check output size */
6738  if ( (idx + algoSz + bitStringSz + seqSz + nSz + eSz) > outLen) {
6739  #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
6740  XFREE(n, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
6741  XFREE(e, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
6742  XFREE(algo, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
6743  #endif
6744 
6745  return BUFFER_E;
6746  }
6747 
6748  /* algo */
6749  XMEMCPY(output + idx, algo, algoSz);
6750  idx += algoSz;
6751  /* bit string */
6752  XMEMCPY(output + idx, bitString, bitStringSz);
6753  idx += bitStringSz;
6754 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
6755  XFREE(algo, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
6756 #endif
6757  }
6758  else
6759  idx = 0;
6760 
6761  /* seq */
6762  XMEMCPY(output + idx, seq, seqSz);
6763  idx += seqSz;
6764  /* n */
6765  XMEMCPY(output + idx, n, nSz);
6766  idx += nSz;
6767  /* e */
6768  XMEMCPY(output + idx, e, eSz);
6769  idx += eSz;
6770 
6771 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
6772  XFREE(n, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
6773  XFREE(e, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
6774 #endif
6775 
6776  return idx;
6777 }
6778 #endif /* !NO_RSA && (WOLFSSL_CERT_GEN || (WOLFSSL_KEY_GEN &&
6779  !HAVE_USER_RSA))) */
6780 
6781 
6782 #if defined(WOLFSSL_KEY_GEN) && !defined(NO_RSA) && !defined(HAVE_USER_RSA)
6783 
6784 
6785 static mp_int* GetRsaInt(RsaKey* key, int idx)
6786 {
6787  if (idx == 0)
6788  return &key->n;
6789  if (idx == 1)
6790  return &key->e;
6791  if (idx == 2)
6792  return &key->d;
6793  if (idx == 3)
6794  return &key->p;
6795  if (idx == 4)
6796  return &key->q;
6797  if (idx == 5)
6798  return &key->dP;
6799  if (idx == 6)
6800  return &key->dQ;
6801  if (idx == 7)
6802  return &key->u;
6803 
6804  return NULL;
6805 }
6806

6808 /* Release Tmp RSA resources */
6809 static INLINE void FreeTmpRsas(byte** tmps, void* heap)
6810 {
6811  int i;
6812 
6813  (void)heap;
6814 
6815  for (i = 0; i < RSA_INTS; i++)
6816  XFREE(tmps[i], heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_RSA);
6817 }
6818 
6819 
6820 /* Convert RsaKey key to DER format, write to output (inLen), return bytes
6821  written */
6822 int wc_RsaKeyToDer(RsaKey* key, byte* output, word32 inLen)
6823 {
6824  word32 seqSz, verSz, rawLen, intTotalLen = 0;
6825  word32 sizes[RSA_INTS];
6826  int i, j, outLen, ret = 0, mpSz;
6827 
6828  byte seq[MAX_SEQ_SZ];
6829  byte ver[MAX_VERSION_SZ];
6830  byte* tmps[RSA_INTS];
6831 
6832  if (!key || !output)
6833  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
6834 
6835  if (key->type != RSA_PRIVATE)
6836  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
6837 
6838  for (i = 0; i < RSA_INTS; i++)
6839  tmps[i] = NULL;
6840 
6841  /* write all big ints from key to DER tmps */
6842  for (i = 0; i < RSA_INTS; i++) {
6843  mp_int* keyInt = GetRsaInt(key, i);
6844 
6845  rawLen = mp_unsigned_bin_size(keyInt) + 1;
6846  tmps[i] = (byte*)XMALLOC(rawLen + MAX_SEQ_SZ, key->heap,
6847  DYNAMIC_TYPE_RSA);
6848  if (tmps[i] == NULL) {
6849  ret = MEMORY_E;
6850  break;
6851  }
6852 
6853  mpSz = SetASNIntMP(keyInt, MAX_RSA_INT_SZ, tmps[i]);
6854  if (mpSz < 0) {
6855  ret = mpSz;
6856  break;
6857  }
6858  intTotalLen += (sizes[i] = mpSz);
6859  }
6860 
6861  if (ret != 0) {
6862  FreeTmpRsas(tmps, key->heap);
6863  return ret;
6864  }
6865 
6866  /* make headers */
6867  verSz = SetMyVersion(0, ver, FALSE);
6868  seqSz = SetSequence(verSz + intTotalLen, seq);
6869 
6870  outLen = seqSz + verSz + intTotalLen;
6871  if (outLen > (int)inLen)
6872  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
6873 
6874  /* write to output */
6875  XMEMCPY(output, seq, seqSz);
6876  j = seqSz;
6877  XMEMCPY(output + j, ver, verSz);
6878  j += verSz;
6879 
6880  for (i = 0; i < RSA_INTS; i++) {
6881  XMEMCPY(output + j, tmps[i], sizes[i]);
6882  j += sizes[i];
6883  }
6884  FreeTmpRsas(tmps, key->heap);
6885 
6886  return outLen;
6887 }
6888 
6889 
6890 /* Convert Rsa Public key to DER format, write to output (inLen), return bytes
6891  written */
6892 int wc_RsaKeyToPublicDer(RsaKey* key, byte* output, word32 inLen)
6893 {
6894  return SetRsaPublicKey(output, key, inLen, 1);
6895 }

6897 #endif /* WOLFSSL_KEY_GEN && !NO_RSA && !HAVE_USER_RSA */
