6900 #if defined(WOLFSSL_CERT_GEN) && !defined(NO_RSA)
6901 
6902 /* Initialize and Set Certificate defaults:
6903  version = 3 (0x2)
6904  serial = 0
6905  sigType = SHA_WITH_RSA
6906  issuer = blank
6907  daysValid = 500
6908  selfSigned = 1 (true) use subject as issuer
6909  subject = blank
6910 */
6911 int wc_InitCert(Cert* cert)
6912 {
6913  if (cert == NULL) {
6914  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
6915  }
6916 
6917  cert->version = 2; /* version 3 is hex 2 */
6918  cert->sigType = CTC_SHAwRSA;
6919  cert->daysValid = 500;
6920  cert->selfSigned = 1;
6921  cert->isCA = 0;
6922  cert->bodySz = 0;
6923 #ifdef WOLFSSL_ALT_NAMES
6924  cert->altNamesSz = 0;
6925  cert->beforeDateSz = 0;
6926  cert->afterDateSz = 0;
6927 #endif
6928 #ifdef WOLFSSL_CERT_EXT
6929  cert->skidSz = 0;
6930  cert->akidSz = 0;
6931  cert->keyUsage = 0;
6932  cert->certPoliciesNb = 0;
6933  XMEMSET(cert->akid, 0, CTC_MAX_AKID_SIZE);
6934  XMEMSET(cert->skid, 0, CTC_MAX_SKID_SIZE);
6935  XMEMSET(cert->certPolicies, 0, CTC_MAX_CERTPOL_NB*CTC_MAX_CERTPOL_SZ);
6936 #endif
6937  cert->keyType = RSA_KEY;
6938  XMEMSET(cert->serial, 0, CTC_SERIAL_SIZE);
6939 
6940  cert->issuer.country[0] = '\0';
6941  cert->issuer.countryEnc = CTC_PRINTABLE;
6942  cert->issuer.state[0] = '\0';
6943  cert->issuer.stateEnc = CTC_UTF8;
6944  cert->issuer.locality[0] = '\0';
6945  cert->issuer.localityEnc = CTC_UTF8;
6946  cert->issuer.sur[0] = '\0';
6947  cert->issuer.surEnc = CTC_UTF8;
6948  cert->issuer.org[0] = '\0';
6949  cert->issuer.orgEnc = CTC_UTF8;
6950  cert->issuer.unit[0] = '\0';
6951  cert->issuer.unitEnc = CTC_UTF8;
6952  cert->issuer.commonName[0] = '\0';
6953  cert->issuer.commonNameEnc = CTC_UTF8;
6954  cert->issuer.email[0] = '\0';
6955 
6956  cert->subject.country[0] = '\0';
6957  cert->subject.countryEnc = CTC_PRINTABLE;
6958  cert->subject.state[0] = '\0';
6959  cert->subject.stateEnc = CTC_UTF8;
6960  cert->subject.locality[0] = '\0';
6961  cert->subject.localityEnc = CTC_UTF8;
6962  cert->subject.sur[0] = '\0';
6963  cert->subject.surEnc = CTC_UTF8;
6964  cert->subject.org[0] = '\0';
6965  cert->subject.orgEnc = CTC_UTF8;
6966  cert->subject.unit[0] = '\0';
6967  cert->subject.unitEnc = CTC_UTF8;
6968  cert->subject.commonName[0] = '\0';
6969  cert->subject.commonNameEnc = CTC_UTF8;
6970  cert->subject.email[0] = '\0';
6971 
6972 #ifdef WOLFSSL_CERT_REQ
6973  cert->challengePw[0] ='\0';
6974 #endif
6975 #ifdef WOLFSSL_HEAP_TEST
6976  cert->heap = (void*)WOLFSSL_HEAP_TEST;
6977 #else
6978  cert->heap = NULL;
6979 #endif
6980 
6981  return 0;
6982 }

6985 /* DER encoded x509 Certificate */
6986 typedef struct DerCert {
6987  byte size[MAX_LENGTH_SZ]; /* length encoded */
6988  byte version[MAX_VERSION_SZ]; /* version encoded */
6989  byte serial[CTC_SERIAL_SIZE + MAX_LENGTH_SZ]; /* serial number encoded */
6990  byte sigAlgo[MAX_ALGO_SZ]; /* signature algo encoded */
6991  byte issuer[ASN_NAME_MAX]; /* issuer encoded */
6992  byte subject[ASN_NAME_MAX]; /* subject encoded */
6993  byte validity[MAX_DATE_SIZE*2 + MAX_SEQ_SZ*2]; /* before and after dates */
6994  byte publicKey[MAX_PUBLIC_KEY_SZ]; /* rsa / ntru public key encoded */
6995  byte ca[MAX_CA_SZ]; /* basic constraint CA true size */
6996  byte extensions[MAX_EXTENSIONS_SZ]; /* all extensions */
6997 #ifdef WOLFSSL_CERT_EXT
6998  byte skid[MAX_KID_SZ]; /* Subject Key Identifier extension */
6999  byte akid[MAX_KID_SZ]; /* Authority Key Identifier extension */
7000  byte keyUsage[MAX_KEYUSAGE_SZ]; /* Key Usage extension */
7001  byte certPolicies[MAX_CERTPOL_NB*MAX_CERTPOL_SZ]; /* Certificate Policies */
7002 #endif
7003 #ifdef WOLFSSL_CERT_REQ
7004  byte attrib[MAX_ATTRIB_SZ]; /* Cert req attributes encoded */
7005 #endif
7006 #ifdef WOLFSSL_ALT_NAMES
7007  byte altNames[CTC_MAX_ALT_SIZE]; /* Alternative Names encoded */
7008 #endif
7009  int sizeSz; /* encoded size length */
7010  int versionSz; /* encoded version length */
7011  int serialSz; /* encoded serial length */
7012  int sigAlgoSz; /* encoded sig alog length */
7013  int issuerSz; /* encoded issuer length */
7014  int subjectSz; /* encoded subject length */
7015  int validitySz; /* encoded validity length */
7016  int publicKeySz; /* encoded public key length */
7017  int caSz; /* encoded CA extension length */
7018 #ifdef WOLFSSL_CERT_EXT
7019  int skidSz; /* encoded SKID extension length */
7020  int akidSz; /* encoded SKID extension length */
7021  int keyUsageSz; /* encoded KeyUsage extension length */
7022  int certPoliciesSz; /* encoded CertPolicies extension length*/
7023 #endif
7024 #ifdef WOLFSSL_ALT_NAMES
7025  int altNamesSz; /* encoded AltNames extension length */
7026 #endif
7027  int extensionsSz; /* encoded extensions total length */
7028  int total; /* total encoded lengths */
7029 #ifdef WOLFSSL_CERT_REQ
7030  int attribSz;
7031 #endif
7032 } DerCert;

7037 /* Write a set header to output */
7038 static word32 SetUTF8String(word32 len, byte* output)
7039 {
7040  output[0] = ASN_UTF8STRING;
7041  return SetLength(len, output + 1) + 1;
7042 }

7047 /* Write a serial number to output */
7048 static int SetSerial(const byte* serial, byte* output)
7049 {
7050  int length = 0;
7051 
7052  output[length++] = ASN_INTEGER;
7053  length += SetLength(CTC_SERIAL_SIZE, &output[length]);
7054  XMEMCPY(&output[length], serial, CTC_SERIAL_SIZE);
7055 
7056  return length + CTC_SERIAL_SIZE;
7057 }
7058 
7059 #endif /* defined(WOLFSSL_CERT_GEN) && !defined(NO_RSA) */
7060 #if defined(HAVE_ECC) && (defined(WOLFSSL_CERT_GEN) || defined(WOLFSSL_KEY_GEN))
7061 
7062 /* Write a public ECC key to output */
7063 static int SetEccPublicKey(byte* output, ecc_key* key, int with_header)
7064 {
7065  byte bitString[1 + MAX_LENGTH_SZ + 1];
7066  int algoSz;
7067  int curveSz;
7068  int bitStringSz;
7069  int idx;
7070  word32 pubSz = ECC_BUFSIZE;
7071 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
7072  byte* algo = NULL;
7073  byte* curve = NULL;
7074  byte* pub = NULL;
7075 #else
7076  byte algo[MAX_ALGO_SZ];
7077  byte curve[MAX_ALGO_SZ];
7078  byte pub[ECC_BUFSIZE];
7079 #endif
7080 
7081 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
7082  pub = (byte*)XMALLOC(ECC_BUFSIZE, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
7083  if (pub == NULL)
7084  return MEMORY_E;
7085 #endif
7086 
7087  int ret = wc_ecc_export_x963(key, pub, &pubSz);
7088  if (ret != 0) {
7089 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
7090  XFREE(pub, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
7091 #endif
7092  return ret;
7093  }
7094 
7095  /* headers */
7096  if (with_header) {
7097 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
7098  curve = (byte*)XMALLOC(MAX_ALGO_SZ, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
7099  if (curve == NULL) {
7100  XFREE(pub, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
7101  return MEMORY_E;
7102  }
7103 #endif
7104  curveSz = SetCurve(key, curve);
7105  if (curveSz <= 0) {
7106 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
7107  XFREE(curve, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
7108  XFREE(pub, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
7109 #endif
7110  return curveSz;
7111  }
7112 
7113 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
7114  algo = (byte*)XMALLOC(MAX_ALGO_SZ, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
7115  if (algo == NULL) {
7116  XFREE(curve, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
7117  XFREE(pub, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
7118  return MEMORY_E;
7119  }
7120 #endif
7121  algoSz = SetAlgoID(ECDSAk, algo, oidKeyType, curveSz);
7122 
7123  bitStringSz = SetBitString(pubSz, 0, bitString);
7124 
7125  idx = SetSequence(pubSz + curveSz + bitStringSz + algoSz, output);
7126  /* algo */
7127  XMEMCPY(output + idx, algo, algoSz);
7128  idx += algoSz;
7129  /* curve */
7130  XMEMCPY(output + idx, curve, curveSz);
7131  idx += curveSz;
7132  /* bit string */
7133  XMEMCPY(output + idx, bitString, bitStringSz);
7134  idx += bitStringSz;
7135  }
7136  else
7137  idx = 0;
7138 
7139  /* pub */
7140  XMEMCPY(output + idx, pub, pubSz);
7141  idx += pubSz;
7142 
7143 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
7144  if (with_header) {
7145  XFREE(algo, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
7146  XFREE(curve, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
7147  }
7148  XFREE(pub, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
7149 #endif
7150 
7151  return idx;
7152 }
7153 
7154 
7155 /* returns the size of buffer used, the public ECC key in DER format is stored
7156  in output buffer
7157  with_AlgCurve is a flag for when to include a header that has the Algorithm
7158  and Curve infromation */
7159 int wc_EccPublicKeyToDer(ecc_key* key, byte* output, word32 inLen,
7160  int with_AlgCurve)
7161 {
7162  word32 infoSz = 0;
7163  word32 keySz = 0;
7164  int ret;
7165 
7166  if (output == NULL || key == NULL) {
7167  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
7168  }
7169 
7170  if (with_AlgCurve) {
7171  /* buffer space for algorithm/curve */
7172  infoSz += MAX_SEQ_SZ;
7173  infoSz += 2 * MAX_ALGO_SZ;
7174 
7175  /* buffer space for public key sequence */
7176  infoSz += MAX_SEQ_SZ;
7177  infoSz += TRAILING_ZERO;
7178  }
7179 
7180  if ((ret = wc_ecc_export_x963(key, NULL, &keySz)) != LENGTH_ONLY_E) {
7181  WOLFSSL_MSG("Error in getting ECC public key size");
7182  return ret;
7183  }
7184 
7185  if (inLen < keySz + infoSz) {
7186  return BUFFER_E;
7187  }
7188 
7189  return SetEccPublicKey(output, key, with_AlgCurve);
7190 }
7191 #endif /* HAVE_ECC && (WOLFSSL_CERT_GEN || WOLFSSL_KEY_GEN) */
7192 #if defined(HAVE_ED25519) && (defined(WOLFSSL_CERT_GEN) || \
7193  defined(WOLFSSL_KEY_GEN))
7194 
7195 /* Write a public ECC key to output */
7196 static int SetEd25519PublicKey(byte* output, ed25519_key* key, int with_header)
7197 {
7198  byte bitString[1 + MAX_LENGTH_SZ + 1];
7199  int algoSz;
7200  int bitStringSz;
7201  int idx;
7202  word32 pubSz = ED25519_PUB_KEY_SIZE;
7203 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
7204  byte* algo = NULL;
7205  byte* pub = NULL;
7206 #else
7207  byte algo[MAX_ALGO_SZ];
7208  byte pub[ED25519_PUB_KEY_SIZE];
7209 #endif
7210 
7211 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
7212  pub = (byte*)XMALLOC(ECC_BUFSIZE, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
7213  if (pub == NULL)
7214  return MEMORY_E;
7215 #endif
7216 
7217  int ret = wc_ed25519_export_public(key, pub, &pubSz);
7218  if (ret != 0) {
7219 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
7220  XFREE(pub, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
7221 #endif
7222  return ret;
7223  }
7224 
7225  /* headers */
7226  if (with_header) {
7227 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
7228  algo = (byte*)XMALLOC(MAX_ALGO_SZ, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
7229  if (algo == NULL) {
7230  XFREE(pub, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
7231  return MEMORY_E;
7232  }
7233 #endif
7234  algoSz = SetAlgoID(ED25519k, algo, oidKeyType, 0);
7235 
7236  bitStringSz = SetBitString(pubSz, 0, bitString);
7237 
7238  idx = SetSequence(pubSz + bitStringSz + algoSz, output);
7239  /* algo */
7240  XMEMCPY(output + idx, algo, algoSz);
7241  idx += algoSz;
7242  /* bit string */
7243  XMEMCPY(output + idx, bitString, bitStringSz);
7244  idx += bitStringSz;
7245  }
7246  else
7247  idx = 0;
7248 
7249  /* pub */
7250  XMEMCPY(output + idx, pub, pubSz);
7251  idx += pubSz;
7252 
7253 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
7254  if (with_header) {
7255  XFREE(algo, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
7256  }
7257  XFREE(pub, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
7258 #endif
7259 
7260  return idx;
7261 }

7298 static INLINE byte itob(int number)
7299 {
7300  return (byte)number + 0x30;
7301 }

7304 /* write time to output, format */
7305 static void SetTime(struct tm* date, byte* output)
7306 {
7307  int i = 0;
7308 
7309  output[i++] = itob((date->tm_year % 10000) / 1000);
7310  output[i++] = itob((date->tm_year % 1000) / 100);
7311  output[i++] = itob((date->tm_year % 100) / 10);
7312  output[i++] = itob( date->tm_year % 10);
7313 
7314  output[i++] = itob(date->tm_mon / 10);
7315  output[i++] = itob(date->tm_mon % 10);
7316 
7317  output[i++] = itob(date->tm_mday / 10);
7318  output[i++] = itob(date->tm_mday % 10);
7319 
7320  output[i++] = itob(date->tm_hour / 10);
7321  output[i++] = itob(date->tm_hour % 10);
7322 
7323  output[i++] = itob(date->tm_min / 10);
7324  output[i++] = itob(date->tm_min % 10);
7325 
7326  output[i++] = itob(date->tm_sec / 10);
7327  output[i++] = itob(date->tm_sec % 10);
7328 
7329  output[i] = 'Z'; /* Zulu profile */
7330 }

7335 /* Copy Dates from cert, return bytes written */
7336 static int CopyValidity(byte* output, Cert* cert)
7337 {
7338  int seqSz;
7339 
7340  WOLFSSL_ENTER("CopyValidity");
7341 
7342  /* headers and output */
7343  seqSz = SetSequence(cert->beforeDateSz + cert->afterDateSz, output);
7344  XMEMCPY(output + seqSz, cert->beforeDate, cert->beforeDateSz);
7345  XMEMCPY(output + seqSz + cert->beforeDateSz, cert->afterDate,
7346  cert->afterDateSz);
7347  return seqSz + cert->beforeDateSz + cert->afterDateSz;
7348 }

7350 #endif

7353 /* for systems where mktime() doesn't normalize fully */
7354 static void RebuildTime(time_t* in, struct tm* out)
7355 {
7356  #if defined(FREESCALE_MQX) || defined(FREESCALE_KSDK_MQX)
7357  out = localtime_r(in, out);
7358  #else
7359  (void)in;
7360  (void)out;
7361  #endif
7362 }

7364 
7365 /* Set Date validity from now until now + daysValid
7366  * return size in bytes written to output, 0 on error */
7367 static int SetValidity(byte* output, int daysValid)
7368 {
7369  byte before[MAX_DATE_SIZE];
7370  byte after[MAX_DATE_SIZE];
7371 
7372  int beforeSz;
7373  int afterSz;
7374  int seqSz;
7375 
7376  time_t ticks;
7377  time_t normalTime;
7378  struct tm* now;
7379  struct tm* tmpTime = NULL;
7380  struct tm local;
7381 
7382 #if defined(NEED_TMP_TIME)
7383  /* for use with gmtime_r */
7384  struct tm tmpTimeStorage;
7385  tmpTime = &tmpTimeStorage;
7386 #else
7387  (void)tmpTime;
7388 #endif
7389 
7390  ticks = XTIME(0);
7391  now = XGMTIME(&ticks, tmpTime);
7392 
7393  if (now == NULL) {
7394  WOLFSSL_MSG("XGMTIME failed");
7395  return 0; /* error */
7396  }
7397 
7398  /* before now */
7399  local = *now;
7400  before[0] = ASN_GENERALIZED_TIME;
7401  beforeSz = SetLength(ASN_GEN_TIME_SZ, before + 1) + 1; /* gen tag */
7402 
7403  /* subtract 1 day for more compliance */
7404  local.tm_mday -= 1;
7405  normalTime = mktime(&local);
7406  RebuildTime(&normalTime, &local);
7407 
7408  /* adjust */
7409  local.tm_year += 1900;
7410  local.tm_mon += 1;
7411 
7412  SetTime(&local, before + beforeSz);
7413  beforeSz += ASN_GEN_TIME_SZ;
7414 
7415  /* after now + daysValid */
7416  local = *now;
7417  after[0] = ASN_GENERALIZED_TIME;
7418  afterSz = SetLength(ASN_GEN_TIME_SZ, after + 1) + 1; /* gen tag */
7419 
7420  /* add daysValid */
7421  local.tm_mday += daysValid;
7422  normalTime = mktime(&local);
7423  RebuildTime(&normalTime, &local);
7424 
7425  /* adjust */
7426  local.tm_year += 1900;
7427  local.tm_mon += 1;
7428 
7429  SetTime(&local, after + afterSz);
7430  afterSz += ASN_GEN_TIME_SZ;
7431 
7432  /* headers and output */
7433  seqSz = SetSequence(beforeSz + afterSz, output);
7434  XMEMCPY(output + seqSz, before, beforeSz);
7435  XMEMCPY(output + seqSz + beforeSz, after, afterSz);
7436 
7437  return seqSz + beforeSz + afterSz;
7438 }

7447  byte encoded[CTC_NAME_SIZE * 2]; /* encoding */
7448 } EncodedName;

7550 /*
7551  Extensions ::= SEQUENCE OF Extension
7552 
7553  Extension ::= SEQUENCE {
7554  extnId OBJECT IDENTIFIER,
7555  critical BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE,
7556  extnValue OCTET STRING }
7557  */
7558 
7559 /* encode all extensions, return total bytes written */
7560 static int SetExtensions(byte* out, word32 outSz, int *IdxInOut,
7561  const byte* ext, int extSz)
7562 {
7563  if (out == NULL || IdxInOut == NULL || ext == NULL)
7564  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
7565 
7566  if (outSz < (word32)(*IdxInOut+extSz))
7567  return BUFFER_E;
7568 
7569  XMEMCPY(&out[*IdxInOut], ext, extSz); /* extensions */
7570  *IdxInOut += extSz;
7571 
7572  return *IdxInOut;
7573 }
7574 
7575 /* encode extensions header, return total bytes written */
7576 static int SetExtensionsHeader(byte* out, word32 outSz, int extSz)
7577 {
7578  byte sequence[MAX_SEQ_SZ];
7579  byte len[MAX_LENGTH_SZ];
7580  int seqSz, lenSz, idx = 0;
7581 
7582  if (out == NULL)
7583  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
7584 
7585  if (outSz < 3)
7586  return BUFFER_E;
7587 
7588  seqSz = SetSequence(extSz, sequence);
7589 
7590  /* encode extensions length provided */
7591  lenSz = SetLength(extSz+seqSz, len);
7592 
7593  if (outSz < (word32)(lenSz+seqSz+1))
7594  return BUFFER_E;
7595 
7596  out[idx++] = ASN_EXTENSIONS; /* extensions id */
7597  XMEMCPY(&out[idx], len, lenSz); /* length */
7598  idx += lenSz;
7599 
7600  XMEMCPY(&out[idx], sequence, seqSz); /* sequence */
7601  idx += seqSz;
7602 
7603  return idx;
7604 }

7606 
7607 /* encode CA basic constraint true, return total bytes written */
7608 static int SetCa(byte* out, word32 outSz)
7609 {
7610  static const byte ca[] = { 0x30, 0x0c, 0x06, 0x03, 0x55, 0x1d, 0x13, 0x04,
7611  0x05, 0x30, 0x03, 0x01, 0x01, 0xff };
7612 
7613  if (out == NULL)
7614  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
7615 
7616  if (outSz < sizeof(ca))
7617  return BUFFER_E;
7618 
7619  XMEMCPY(out, ca, sizeof(ca));
7620 
7621  return (int)sizeof(ca);
7622 }

7625 #ifdef WOLFSSL_CERT_EXT
7626 /* encode OID and associated value, return total bytes written */
7627 static int SetOidValue(byte* out, word32 outSz, const byte *oid, word32 oidSz,
7628  byte *in, word32 inSz)
7629 {
7630  int idx = 0;
7631 
7632  if (out == NULL || oid == NULL || in == NULL)
7633  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
7634 
7635  if (outSz < 3)
7636  return BUFFER_E;
7637 
7638  /* sequence, + 1 => byte to put value size */
7639  idx = SetSequence(inSz + oidSz + 1, out);
7640 
7641  if ((idx + inSz + oidSz + 1) > outSz)
7642  return BUFFER_E;
7643 
7644  XMEMCPY(out+idx, oid, oidSz);
7645  idx += oidSz;
7646  out[idx++] = (byte)inSz;
7647  XMEMCPY(out+idx, in, inSz);
7648 
7649  return (idx+inSz);
7650 }
7651 
7652 /* encode Subject Key Identifier, return total bytes written
7653  * RFC5280 : non-critical */
7654 static int SetSKID(byte* output, word32 outSz, const byte *input, word32 length)
7655 {
7656  byte skid_len[1 + MAX_LENGTH_SZ];
7657  byte skid_enc_len[MAX_LENGTH_SZ];
7658  int idx = 0, skid_lenSz, skid_enc_lenSz;
7659  static const byte skid_oid[] = { 0x06, 0x03, 0x55, 0x1d, 0x0e, 0x04 };
7660 
7661  if (output == NULL || input == NULL)
7662  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
7663 
7664  /* Octet String header */
7665  skid_lenSz = SetOctetString(length, skid_len);
7666 
7667  /* length of encoded value */
7668  skid_enc_lenSz = SetLength(length + skid_lenSz, skid_enc_len);
7669 
7670  if (outSz < 3)
7671  return BUFFER_E;
7672 
7673  idx = SetSequence(length + sizeof(skid_oid) + skid_lenSz + skid_enc_lenSz,
7674  output);
7675 
7676  if ((length + sizeof(skid_oid) + skid_lenSz + skid_enc_lenSz) > outSz)
7677  return BUFFER_E;
7678 
7679  /* put oid */
7680  XMEMCPY(output+idx, skid_oid, sizeof(skid_oid));
7681  idx += sizeof(skid_oid);
7682 
7683  /* put encoded len */
7684  XMEMCPY(output+idx, skid_enc_len, skid_enc_lenSz);
7685  idx += skid_enc_lenSz;
7686 
7687  /* put octet header */
7688  XMEMCPY(output+idx, skid_len, skid_lenSz);
7689  idx += skid_lenSz;
7690 
7691  /* put value */
7692  XMEMCPY(output+idx, input, length);
7693  idx += length;
7694 
7695  return idx;
7696 }
7697 
7698 /* encode Authority Key Identifier, return total bytes written
7699  * RFC5280 : non-critical */
7700 static int SetAKID(byte* output, word32 outSz,
7701  byte *input, word32 length, void* heap)
7702 {
7703  byte *enc_val;
7704  int ret, enc_valSz;
7705  static const byte akid_oid[] = { 0x06, 0x03, 0x55, 0x1d, 0x23, 0x04 };
7706  static const byte akid_cs[] = { 0x80 };
7707 
7708  if (output == NULL || input == NULL)
7709  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
7710 
7711  enc_valSz = length + 3 + sizeof(akid_cs);
7712  enc_val = (byte *)XMALLOC(enc_valSz, heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
7713  if (enc_val == NULL)
7714  return MEMORY_E;
7715 
7716  /* sequence for ContentSpec & value */
7717  ret = SetOidValue(enc_val, enc_valSz, akid_cs, sizeof(akid_cs),
7718  input, length);
7719  if (ret > 0) {
7720  enc_valSz = ret;
7721 
7722  ret = SetOidValue(output, outSz, akid_oid, sizeof(akid_oid),
7723  enc_val, enc_valSz);
7724  }
7725 
7726  XFREE(enc_val, heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
7727  return ret;
7728 }

7730 /* encode Key Usage, return total bytes written
7731  * RFC5280 : critical */
7732 static int SetKeyUsage(byte* output, word32 outSz, word16 input)
7733 {
7734  byte ku[5];
7735  int idx;
7736  static const byte keyusage_oid[] = { 0x06, 0x03, 0x55, 0x1d, 0x0f,
7737  0x01, 0x01, 0xff, 0x04};
7738 
7739  if (output == NULL)
7740  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
7741 
7742  idx = SetBitString16Bit(input, ku);
7743  return SetOidValue(output, outSz, keyusage_oid, sizeof(keyusage_oid),
7744  ku, idx);
7745 }
7746 
7747 /* Encode OID string representation to ITU-T X.690 format */
7748 static int EncodePolicyOID(byte *out, word32 *outSz, const char *in, void* heap)
7749 {
7750  word32 val, idx = 0, nb_val;
7751  char *token, *str, *ptr;
7752  word32 len;
7753 
7754  if (out == NULL || outSz == NULL || *outSz < 2 || in == NULL)
7755  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
7756 
7757  len = (word32)XSTRLEN(in);
7758 
7759  str = (char *)XMALLOC(len+1, heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
7760  if (str == NULL)
7761  return MEMORY_E;
7762 
7763  XSTRNCPY(str, in, len);
7764  str[len] = 0x00;
7765 
7766  nb_val = 0;
7767 
7768  /* parse value, and set corresponding Policy OID value */
7769  token = XSTRTOK(str, ".", &ptr);
7770  while (token != NULL)
7771  {
7772  val = (word32)atoi(token);
7773 
7774  if (nb_val == 0) {
7775  if (val > 2) {
7776  XFREE(str, heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
7777  return ASN_OBJECT_ID_E;
7778  }
7779 
7780  out[idx] = (byte)(40 * val);
7781  }
7782  else if (nb_val == 1) {
7783  if (val > 127) {
7784  XFREE(str, heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
7785  return ASN_OBJECT_ID_E;
7786  }
7787 
7788  if (idx > *outSz) {
7789  XFREE(str, heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
7790  return BUFFER_E;
7791  }
7792 
7793  out[idx++] += (byte)val;
7794  }
7795  else {
7796  word32 tb = 0, x;
7797  int i = 0;
7798  byte oid[MAX_OID_SZ];
7799 
7800  while (val >= 128) {
7801  x = val % 128;
7802  val /= 128;
7803  oid[i++] = (byte) (((tb++) ? 0x80 : 0) | x);
7804  }
7805 
7806  if ((idx+(word32)i) > *outSz) {
7807  XFREE(str, heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
7808  return BUFFER_E;
7809  }
7810 
7811  oid[i] = (byte) (((tb++) ? 0x80 : 0) | val);
7812 
7813  /* push value in the right order */
7814  while (i >= 0)
7815  out[idx++] = oid[i--];
7816  }
7817 
7818  token = XSTRTOK(NULL, ".", &ptr);
7819  nb_val++;
7820  }
7821 
7822  *outSz = idx;
7823 
7824  XFREE(str, heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
7825  return 0;
7826 }
7827 
7828 /* encode Certificate Policies, return total bytes written
7829  * each input value must be ITU-T X.690 formatted : a.b.c...
7830  * input must be an array of values with a NULL terminated for the latest
7831  * RFC5280 : non-critical */
7832 static int SetCertificatePolicies(byte *output,
7833  word32 outputSz,
7834  char input[MAX_CERTPOL_NB][MAX_CERTPOL_SZ],
7835  word16 nb_certpol,
7836  void* heap)
7837 {
7838  byte oid[MAX_OID_SZ],
7839  der_oid[MAX_CERTPOL_NB][MAX_OID_SZ],
7840  out[MAX_CERTPOL_SZ];
7841  word32 oidSz;
7842  word32 outSz, i = 0, der_oidSz[MAX_CERTPOL_NB];
7843  int ret;
7844 
7845  static const byte certpol_oid[] = { 0x06, 0x03, 0x55, 0x1d, 0x20, 0x04 };
7846  static const byte oid_oid[] = { 0x06 };
7847 
7848  if (output == NULL || input == NULL || nb_certpol > MAX_CERTPOL_NB)
7849  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
7850 
7851  for (i = 0; i < nb_certpol; i++) {
7852  oidSz = sizeof(oid);
7853  XMEMSET(oid, 0, oidSz);
7854 
7855  ret = EncodePolicyOID(oid, &oidSz, input[i], heap);
7856  if (ret != 0)
7857  return ret;
7858 
7859  /* compute sequence value for the oid */
7860  ret = SetOidValue(der_oid[i], MAX_OID_SZ, oid_oid,
7861  sizeof(oid_oid), oid, oidSz);
7862  if (ret <= 0)
7863  return ret;
7864  else
7865  der_oidSz[i] = (word32)ret;
7866  }
7867 
7868  /* concatenate oid, keep two byte for sequence/size of the created value */
7869  for (i = 0, outSz = 2; i < nb_certpol; i++) {
7870  XMEMCPY(out+outSz, der_oid[i], der_oidSz[i]);
7871  outSz += der_oidSz[i];
7872  }
7873 
7874  /* add sequence */
7875  ret = SetSequence(outSz-2, out);
7876  if (ret <= 0)
7877  return ret;
7878 
7879  /* add Policy OID to compute final value */
7880  return SetOidValue(output, outputSz, certpol_oid, sizeof(certpol_oid),
7881  out, outSz);
7882 }
7883 #endif /* WOLFSSL_CERT_EXT */
7884 
7885 #ifdef WOLFSSL_ALT_NAMES
7886 /* encode Alternative Names, return total bytes written */
7887 static int SetAltNames(byte *out, word32 outSz, byte *input, word32 length)
7888 {
7889  if (out == NULL || input == NULL)
7890  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
7891 
7892  if (outSz < length)
7893  return BUFFER_E;
7894 
7895  /* Alternative Names come from certificate or computed by
7896  * external function, so already encoded. Just copy value */
7897  XMEMCPY(out, input, length);
7898  return length;
7899 }
7900 #endif /* WOLFSL_ALT_NAMES */
7901 
7902 
7903 /* encode CertName into output, return total bytes written */
7904 int SetName(byte* output, word32 outputSz, CertName* name)
7905 {
7906  int totalBytes = 0, i, idx;
7907 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
7908  EncodedName* names = NULL;
7909 #else
7910  EncodedName names[NAME_ENTRIES];
7911 #endif
7912 
7913  if (output == NULL || name == NULL)
7914  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
7915 
7916  if (outputSz < 3)
7917  return BUFFER_E;
7918 
7919 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
7920  names = (EncodedName*)XMALLOC(sizeof(EncodedName) * NAME_ENTRIES, NULL,
7921  DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
7922  if (names == NULL)
7923  return MEMORY_E;
7924 #endif
7925 
7926  for (i = 0; i < NAME_ENTRIES; i++) {
7927  const char* nameStr = GetOneName(name, i);
7928  if (nameStr) {
7929  /* bottom up */
7930  byte firstLen[1 + MAX_LENGTH_SZ];
7931  byte secondLen[MAX_LENGTH_SZ];
7932  byte sequence[MAX_SEQ_SZ];
7933  byte set[MAX_SET_SZ];
7934 
7935  int email = i == (NAME_ENTRIES - 1) ? 1 : 0;
7936  int strLen = (int)XSTRLEN(nameStr);
7937  int thisLen = strLen;
7938  int firstSz, secondSz, seqSz, setSz;
7939 
7940  if (strLen == 0) { /* no user data for this item */
7941  names[i].used = 0;
7942  continue;
7943  }
7944 
7945  /* Restrict country code size */
7946  if (i == 0 && strLen != CTC_COUNTRY_SIZE) {
7947 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
7948  XFREE(names, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
7949 #endif
7950  return ASN_COUNTRY_SIZE_E;
7951  }
7952 
7953  secondSz = SetLength(strLen, secondLen);
7954  thisLen += secondSz;
7955  if (email) {
7956  thisLen += EMAIL_JOINT_LEN;
7957  thisLen ++; /* id type */
7958  firstSz = SetObjectId(EMAIL_JOINT_LEN, firstLen);
7959  }
7960  else {
7961  thisLen++; /* str type */
7962  thisLen++; /* id type */
7963  thisLen += JOINT_LEN;
7964  firstSz = SetObjectId(JOINT_LEN + 1, firstLen);
7965  }
7966  thisLen += firstSz;
7967 
7968  seqSz = SetSequence(thisLen, sequence);
7969  thisLen += seqSz;
7970  setSz = SetSet(thisLen, set);
7971  thisLen += setSz;
7972 
7973  if (thisLen > (int)sizeof(names[i].encoded)) {
7974 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
7975  XFREE(names, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
7976 #endif
7977  return BUFFER_E;
7978  }
7979 
7980  /* store it */
7981  idx = 0;
7982  /* set */
7983  XMEMCPY(names[i].encoded, set, setSz);
7984  idx += setSz;
7985  /* seq */
7986  XMEMCPY(names[i].encoded + idx, sequence, seqSz);
7987  idx += seqSz;
7988  /* asn object id */
7989  XMEMCPY(names[i].encoded + idx, firstLen, firstSz);
7990  idx += firstSz;
7991  if (email) {
7992  const byte EMAIL_OID[] = { 0x2a, 0x86, 0x48, 0x86, 0xf7, 0x0d,
7993  0x01, 0x09, 0x01, 0x16 };
7994  /* email joint id */
7995  XMEMCPY(names[i].encoded + idx, EMAIL_OID, sizeof(EMAIL_OID));
7996  idx += (int)sizeof(EMAIL_OID);
7997  }
7998  else {
7999  /* joint id */
8000  byte bType = GetNameId(i);
8001  names[i].encoded[idx++] = 0x55;
8002  names[i].encoded[idx++] = 0x04;
8003  /* id type */
8004  names[i].encoded[idx++] = bType;
8005  /* str type */
8006  names[i].encoded[idx++] = GetNameType(name, i);
8007  }
8008  /* second length */
8009  XMEMCPY(names[i].encoded + idx, secondLen, secondSz);
8010  idx += secondSz;
8011  /* str value */
8012  XMEMCPY(names[i].encoded + idx, nameStr, strLen);
8013  idx += strLen;
8014 
8015  totalBytes += idx;
8016  names[i].totalLen = idx;
8017  names[i].used = 1;
8018  }
8019  else
8020  names[i].used = 0;
8021  }
8022 
8023  /* header */
8024  idx = SetSequence(totalBytes, output);
8025  totalBytes += idx;
8026  if (totalBytes > ASN_NAME_MAX) {
8027 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
8028  XFREE(names, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
8029 #endif
8030  return BUFFER_E;
8031  }
8032 
8033  for (i = 0; i < NAME_ENTRIES; i++) {
8034  if (names[i].used) {
8035  if (outputSz < (word32)(idx+names[i].totalLen)) {
8036 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
8037  XFREE(names, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
8038 #endif
8039  return BUFFER_E;
8040  }
8041 
8042  XMEMCPY(output + idx, names[i].encoded, names[i].totalLen);
8043  idx += names[i].totalLen;
8044  }
8045  }
8046 
8047 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
8048  XFREE(names, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
8049 #endif
8050 
8051  return totalBytes;
8052 }
8053 
8054 /* encode info from cert into DER encoded format */
8055 static int EncodeCert(Cert* cert, DerCert* der, RsaKey* rsaKey, ecc_key* eccKey,
8056  WC_RNG* rng, const byte* ntruKey, word16 ntruSz,
8057  ed25519_key* ed25519Key)
8058 {
8059  int ret;
8060 
8061  (void)eccKey;
8062  (void)ntruKey;
8063  (void)ntruSz;
8064  (void)ed25519Key;
8065 
8066  if (cert == NULL || der == NULL || rng == NULL)
8067  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
8068 
8069  /* init */
8070  XMEMSET(der, 0, sizeof(DerCert));
8071 
8072  /* version */
8073  der->versionSz = SetMyVersion(cert->version, der->version, TRUE);
8074 
8075  /* serial number */
8076  ret = wc_RNG_GenerateBlock(rng, cert->serial, CTC_SERIAL_SIZE);
8077  if (ret != 0)
8078  return ret;
8079 
8080  cert->serial[0] = 0x01; /* ensure positive */
8081  der->serialSz = SetSerial(cert->serial, der->serial);
8082 
8083  /* signature algo */
8084  der->sigAlgoSz = SetAlgoID(cert->sigType, der->sigAlgo, oidSigType, 0);
8085  if (der->sigAlgoSz <= 0)
8086  return ALGO_ID_E;
8087 
8088  /* public key */
8089  if (cert->keyType == RSA_KEY) {
8090  if (rsaKey == NULL)
8091  return PUBLIC_KEY_E;
8092  der->publicKeySz = SetRsaPublicKey(der->publicKey, rsaKey,
8093  sizeof(der->publicKey), 1);
8094  if (der->publicKeySz <= 0)
8095  return PUBLIC_KEY_E;
8096  }
8097 
8098 #ifdef HAVE_ECC
8099  if (cert->keyType == ECC_KEY) {
8100  if (eccKey == NULL)
8101  return PUBLIC_KEY_E;
8102  der->publicKeySz = SetEccPublicKey(der->publicKey, eccKey, 1);
8103  if (der->publicKeySz <= 0)
8104  return PUBLIC_KEY_E;
8105  }
8106 #endif /* HAVE_ECC */
8107 
8108 #ifdef HAVE_ED25519
8109  if (cert->keyType == ED25519_KEY) {
8110  if (ed25519Key == NULL)
8111  return PUBLIC_KEY_E;
8112  der->publicKeySz = SetEd25519PublicKey(der->publicKey, ed25519Key, 1);
8113  if (der->publicKeySz <= 0)
8114  return PUBLIC_KEY_E;
8115  }
8116 #endif
8117 
8118 #ifdef HAVE_NTRU
8119  if (cert->keyType == NTRU_KEY) {
8120  word32 rc;
8121  word16 encodedSz;
8122 
8123  rc = ntru_crypto_ntru_encrypt_publicKey2SubjectPublicKeyInfo( ntruSz,
8124  ntruKey, &encodedSz, NULL);
8125  if (rc != NTRU_OK)
8126  return PUBLIC_KEY_E;
8127  if (encodedSz > MAX_PUBLIC_KEY_SZ)
8128  return PUBLIC_KEY_E;
8129 
8130  rc = ntru_crypto_ntru_encrypt_publicKey2SubjectPublicKeyInfo( ntruSz,
8131  ntruKey, &encodedSz, der->publicKey);
8132  if (rc != NTRU_OK)
8133  return PUBLIC_KEY_E;
8134 
8135  der->publicKeySz = encodedSz;
8136  }
8137 #endif /* HAVE_NTRU */
8138 
8139  der->validitySz = 0;
8140 #ifdef WOLFSSL_ALT_NAMES
8141  /* date validity copy ? */
8142  if (cert->beforeDateSz && cert->afterDateSz) {
8143  der->validitySz = CopyValidity(der->validity, cert);
8144  if (der->validitySz <= 0)
8145  return DATE_E;
8146  }
8147 #endif
8148 
8149  /* date validity */
8150  if (der->validitySz == 0) {
8151  der->validitySz = SetValidity(der->validity, cert->daysValid);
8152  if (der->validitySz <= 0)
8153  return DATE_E;
8154  }
8155 
8156  /* subject name */
8157  der->subjectSz = SetName(der->subject, sizeof(der->subject), &cert->subject);
8158  if (der->subjectSz <= 0)
8159  return SUBJECT_E;
8160 
8161  /* issuer name */
8162  der->issuerSz = SetName(der->issuer, sizeof(der->issuer), cert->selfSigned ?
8163  &cert->subject : &cert->issuer);
8164  if (der->issuerSz <= 0)
8165  return ISSUER_E;
8166 
8167  /* set the extensions */
8168  der->extensionsSz = 0;
8169 
8170  /* CA */
8171  if (cert->isCA) {
8172  der->caSz = SetCa(der->ca, sizeof(der->ca));
8173  if (der->caSz <= 0)
8174  return CA_TRUE_E;
8175 
8176  der->extensionsSz += der->caSz;
8177  }
8178  else
8179  der->caSz = 0;
8180 
8181 #ifdef WOLFSSL_ALT_NAMES
8182  /* Alternative Name */
8183  if (cert->altNamesSz) {
8184  der->altNamesSz = SetAltNames(der->altNames, sizeof(der->altNames),
8185  cert->altNames, cert->altNamesSz);
8186  if (der->altNamesSz <= 0)
8187  return ALT_NAME_E;
8188 
8189  der->extensionsSz += der->altNamesSz;
8190  }
8191  else
8192  der->altNamesSz = 0;
8193 #endif
8194 
8195 #ifdef WOLFSSL_CERT_EXT
8196  /* SKID */
8197  if (cert->skidSz) {
8198  /* check the provided SKID size */
8199  if (cert->skidSz > (int)sizeof(der->skid))
8200  return SKID_E;
8201 
8202  /* Note: different skid buffers sizes for der (MAX_KID_SZ) and
8203  cert (CTC_MAX_SKID_SIZE). */
8204  der->skidSz = SetSKID(der->skid, sizeof(der->skid),
8205  cert->skid, cert->skidSz);
8206  if (der->skidSz <= 0)
8207  return SKID_E;
8208 
8209  der->extensionsSz += der->skidSz;
8210  }
8211  else
8212  der->skidSz = 0;
8213 
8214  /* AKID */
8215  if (cert->akidSz) {
8216  /* check the provided AKID size */
8217  if (cert->akidSz > (int)sizeof(der->akid))
8218  return AKID_E;
8219 
8220  der->akidSz = SetAKID(der->akid, sizeof(der->akid),
8221  cert->akid, cert->akidSz, cert->heap);
8222  if (der->akidSz <= 0)
8223  return AKID_E;
8224 
8225  der->extensionsSz += der->akidSz;
8226  }
8227  else
8228  der->akidSz = 0;
8229 
8230  /* Key Usage */
8231  if (cert->keyUsage != 0){
8232  der->keyUsageSz = SetKeyUsage(der->keyUsage, sizeof(der->keyUsage),
8233  cert->keyUsage);
8234  if (der->keyUsageSz <= 0)
8235  return KEYUSAGE_E;
8236 
8237  der->extensionsSz += der->keyUsageSz;
8238  }
8239  else
8240  der->keyUsageSz = 0;
8241 
8242  /* Certificate Policies */
8243  if (cert->certPoliciesNb != 0) {
8244  der->certPoliciesSz = SetCertificatePolicies(der->certPolicies,
8245  sizeof(der->certPolicies),
8246  cert->certPolicies,
8247  cert->certPoliciesNb,
8248  cert->heap);
8249  if (der->certPoliciesSz <= 0)
8250  return CERTPOLICIES_E;
8251 
8252  der->extensionsSz += der->certPoliciesSz;
8253  }
8254  else
8255  der->certPoliciesSz = 0;
8256 #endif /* WOLFSSL_CERT_EXT */
8257 
8258  /* put extensions */
8259  if (der->extensionsSz > 0) {
8260 
8261  /* put the start of extensions sequence (ID, Size) */
8262  der->extensionsSz = SetExtensionsHeader(der->extensions,
8263  sizeof(der->extensions),
8264  der->extensionsSz);
8265  if (der->extensionsSz <= 0)
8266  return EXTENSIONS_E;
8267 
8268  /* put CA */
8269  if (der->caSz) {
8270  ret = SetExtensions(der->extensions, sizeof(der->extensions),
8271  &der->extensionsSz,
8272  der->ca, der->caSz);
8273  if (ret == 0)
8274  return EXTENSIONS_E;
8275  }
8276 
8277 #ifdef WOLFSSL_ALT_NAMES
8278  /* put Alternative Names */
8279  if (der->altNamesSz) {
8280  ret = SetExtensions(der->extensions, sizeof(der->extensions),
8281  &der->extensionsSz,
8282  der->altNames, der->altNamesSz);
8283  if (ret <= 0)
8284  return EXTENSIONS_E;
8285  }
8286 #endif
8287 
8288 #ifdef WOLFSSL_CERT_EXT
8289  /* put SKID */
8290  if (der->skidSz) {
8291  ret = SetExtensions(der->extensions, sizeof(der->extensions),
8292  &der->extensionsSz,
8293  der->skid, der->skidSz);
8294  if (ret <= 0)
8295  return EXTENSIONS_E;
8296  }
8297 
8298  /* put AKID */
8299  if (der->akidSz) {
8300  ret = SetExtensions(der->extensions, sizeof(der->extensions),
8301  &der->extensionsSz,
8302  der->akid, der->akidSz);
8303  if (ret <= 0)
8304  return EXTENSIONS_E;
8305  }
8306 
8307  /* put KeyUsage */
8308  if (der->keyUsageSz) {
8309  ret = SetExtensions(der->extensions, sizeof(der->extensions),
8310  &der->extensionsSz,
8311  der->keyUsage, der->keyUsageSz);
8312  if (ret <= 0)
8313  return EXTENSIONS_E;
8314  }
8315 
8316  /* put Certificate Policies */
8317  if (der->certPoliciesSz) {
8318  ret = SetExtensions(der->extensions, sizeof(der->extensions),
8319  &der->extensionsSz,
8320  der->certPolicies, der->certPoliciesSz);
8321  if (ret <= 0)
8322  return EXTENSIONS_E;
8323  }
8324 #endif /* WOLFSSL_CERT_EXT */
8325  }
8326 
8327  der->total = der->versionSz + der->serialSz + der->sigAlgoSz +
8328  der->publicKeySz + der->validitySz + der->subjectSz + der->issuerSz +
8329  der->extensionsSz;
8330 
8331  return 0;
8332 }
8333 
8334 
8335 /* write DER encoded cert to buffer, size already checked */
8336 static int WriteCertBody(DerCert* der, byte* buffer)
8337 {
8338  int idx;
8339 
8340  /* signed part header */
8341  idx = SetSequence(der->total, buffer);
8342  /* version */
8343  XMEMCPY(buffer + idx, der->version, der->versionSz);
8344  idx += der->versionSz;
8345  /* serial */
8346  XMEMCPY(buffer + idx, der->serial, der->serialSz);
8347  idx += der->serialSz;
8348  /* sig algo */
8349  XMEMCPY(buffer + idx, der->sigAlgo, der->sigAlgoSz);
8350  idx += der->sigAlgoSz;
8351  /* issuer */
8352  XMEMCPY(buffer + idx, der->issuer, der->issuerSz);
8353  idx += der->issuerSz;
8354  /* validity */
8355  XMEMCPY(buffer + idx, der->validity, der->validitySz);
8356  idx += der->validitySz;
8357  /* subject */
8358  XMEMCPY(buffer + idx, der->subject, der->subjectSz);
8359  idx += der->subjectSz;
8360  /* public key */
8361  XMEMCPY(buffer + idx, der->publicKey, der->publicKeySz);
8362  idx += der->publicKeySz;
8363  if (der->extensionsSz) {
8364  /* extensions */
8365  XMEMCPY(buffer + idx, der->extensions, min(der->extensionsSz,
8366  (int)sizeof(der->extensions)));
8367  idx += der->extensionsSz;
8368  }
8369 
8370  return idx;
8371 }
8372 
8373 
8374 /* Make RSA signature from buffer (sz), write to sig (sigSz) */
8375 static int MakeSignature(CertSignCtx* certSignCtx, const byte* buffer, int sz,
8376  byte* sig, int sigSz, RsaKey* rsaKey, ecc_key* eccKey,
8377  ed25519_key* ed25519Key, WC_RNG* rng, int sigAlgoType, void* heap)
8378 {
8379  int digestSz = 0, typeH = 0, ret = 0;
8380 
8381  (void)digestSz;
8382  (void)typeH;
8383  (void)buffer;
8384  (void)sz;
8385  (void)sig;
8386  (void)sigSz;
8387  (void)rsaKey;
8388  (void)eccKey;
8389  (void)ed25519Key;
8390  (void)rng;
8391 
8392  switch (certSignCtx->state) {
8393  case CERTSIGN_STATE_BEGIN:
8394  case CERTSIGN_STATE_DIGEST:
8395 
8396  certSignCtx->state = CERTSIGN_STATE_DIGEST;
8397  certSignCtx->digest = (byte*)XMALLOC(WC_MAX_DIGEST_SIZE, heap,
8398  DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
8399  if (certSignCtx->digest == NULL) {
8400  ret = MEMORY_E; goto exit_ms;
8401  }
8402 
8403  ret = HashForSignature(buffer, sz, sigAlgoType, certSignCtx->digest,
8404  &typeH, &digestSz, 0);
8405  /* set next state, since WC_PENDING rentry for these are not "call again" */
8406  certSignCtx->state = CERTSIGN_STATE_ENCODE;
8407  if (ret != 0) {
8408  goto exit_ms;
8409  }
8410  FALL_THROUGH;
8411 
8412  case CERTSIGN_STATE_ENCODE:
8413  #ifndef NO_RSA
8414  if (rsaKey) {
8415  certSignCtx->encSig = (byte*)XMALLOC(MAX_DER_DIGEST_SZ, heap,
8416  DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
8417  if (certSignCtx->encSig == NULL) {
8418  ret = MEMORY_E; goto exit_ms;
8419  }
8420 
8421  /* signature */
8422  certSignCtx->encSigSz = wc_EncodeSignature(certSignCtx->encSig,
8423  certSignCtx->digest, digestSz, typeH);
8424  }
8425  #endif /* !NO_RSA */
8426  FALL_THROUGH;
8427 
8428  case CERTSIGN_STATE_DO:
8429  certSignCtx->state = CERTSIGN_STATE_DO;
8430  ret = ALGO_ID_E; /* default to error */
8431 
8432  #ifndef NO_RSA
8433  if (rsaKey) {
8434  /* signature */
8435  ret = wc_RsaSSL_Sign(certSignCtx->encSig, certSignCtx->encSigSz,
8436  sig, sigSz, rsaKey, rng);
8437  }
8438  #endif /* !NO_RSA */
8439 
8440  #ifdef HAVE_ECC
8441  if (!rsaKey && eccKey) {
8442  word32 outSz = sigSz;
8443 
8444  ret = wc_ecc_sign_hash(certSignCtx->digest, digestSz,
8445  sig, &outSz, rng, eccKey);
8446  if (ret == 0)
8447  ret = outSz;
8448  }
8449  #endif /* HAVE_ECC */
8450 
8451  #ifdef HAVE_ED25519
8452  if (!rsaKey && !eccKey && ed25519Key) {
8453  word32 outSz = sigSz;
8454 
8455  ret = wc_ed25519_sign_msg(buffer, sz, sig, &outSz, ed25519Key);
8456  if (ret == 0)
8457  ret = outSz;
8458  }
8459  #endif /* HAVE_ECC */
8460  break;
8461  }
8462 
8463 exit_ms:
8464 
8465  if (ret == WC_PENDING_E) {
8466  return ret;
8467  }
8468 
8469 #ifndef NO_RSA
8470  if (rsaKey) {
8471  XFREE(certSignCtx->encSig, heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
8472  }
8473 #endif /* !NO_RSA */
8474 
8475  XFREE(certSignCtx->digest, heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
8476  certSignCtx->digest = NULL;
8477 
8478  /* reset state */
8479  certSignCtx->state = CERTSIGN_STATE_BEGIN;
8480 
8481  return ret;
8482 }
8483 
8484 
8485 /* add signature to end of buffer, size of buffer assumed checked, return
8486  new length */
8487 static int AddSignature(byte* buffer, int bodySz, const byte* sig, int sigSz,
8488  int sigAlgoType)
8489 {
8490  byte seq[MAX_SEQ_SZ];
8491  int idx = bodySz, seqSz;
8492 
8493  /* algo */
8494  idx += SetAlgoID(sigAlgoType, buffer + idx, oidSigType, 0);
8495  /* bit string */
8496  idx += SetBitString(sigSz, 0, buffer + idx);
8497  /* signature */
8498  XMEMCPY(buffer + idx, sig, sigSz);
8499  idx += sigSz;
8500 
8501  /* make room for overall header */
8502  seqSz = SetSequence(idx, seq);
8503  XMEMMOVE(buffer + seqSz, buffer, idx);
8504  XMEMCPY(buffer, seq, seqSz);
8505 
8506  return idx + seqSz;
8507 }
8508 
8509 
8510 /* Make an x509 Certificate v3 any key type from cert input, write to buffer */
8511 static int MakeAnyCert(Cert* cert, byte* derBuffer, word32 derSz,
8512  RsaKey* rsaKey, ecc_key* eccKey, WC_RNG* rng,
8513  const byte* ntruKey, word16 ntruSz,
8514  ed25519_key* ed25519Key)
8515 {
8516  int ret;
8517 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
8518  DerCert* der;
8519 #else
8520  DerCert der[1];
8521 #endif
8522 
8523  cert->keyType = eccKey ? ECC_KEY : (rsaKey ? RSA_KEY :
8524  (ed25519Key ? ED25519_KEY : NTRU_KEY));
8525 
8526 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
8527  der = (DerCert*)XMALLOC(sizeof(DerCert), NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
8528  if (der == NULL)
8529  return MEMORY_E;
8530 #endif
8531 
8532  ret = EncodeCert(cert, der, rsaKey, eccKey, rng, ntruKey, ntruSz,
8533  ed25519Key);
8534  if (ret == 0) {
8535  if (der->total + MAX_SEQ_SZ * 2 > (int)derSz)
8536  ret = BUFFER_E;
8537  else
8538  ret = cert->bodySz = WriteCertBody(der, derBuffer);
8539  }
8540 
8541 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
8542  XFREE(der, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
8543 #endif
8544 
8545  return ret;
8546 }

8550 int wc_MakeCert_ex(Cert* cert, byte* derBuffer, word32 derSz, int keyType,
8551  void* key, WC_RNG* rng)
8552 {

8559  else if (keyType == ECC_TYPE)

8561  else if (keyType == ED25519_TYPE)
8562  ed25519Key = (ed25519_key*)key;
8563 
8564  return MakeAnyCert(cert, derBuffer, derSz, rsaKey, eccKey, rng, NULL, 0,
8565  ed25519Key);
8566 }

8569  ecc_key* eccKey, WC_RNG* rng)

8572  NULL);

8586 
8587 #ifdef WOLFSSL_CERT_REQ
8588 
8589 static int SetReqAttrib(byte* output, char* pw, int extSz)
8590 {
8591  static const byte cpOid[] =
8592  { ASN_OBJECT_ID, 0x09, 0x2a, 0x86, 0x48, 0x86, 0xf7, 0x0d, 0x01,
8593  0x09, 0x07 };
8594  static const byte erOid[] =
8595  { ASN_OBJECT_ID, 0x09, 0x2a, 0x86, 0x48, 0x86, 0xf7, 0x0d, 0x01,
8596  0x09, 0x0e };
8597 
8598  int sz = 0; /* overall size */
8599  int cpSz = 0; /* Challenge Password section size */
8600  int cpSeqSz = 0;
8601  int cpSetSz = 0;
8602  int cpStrSz = 0;
8603  int pwSz = 0;
8604  int erSz = 0; /* Extension Request section size */
8605  int erSeqSz = 0;
8606  int erSetSz = 0;
8607  byte cpSeq[MAX_SEQ_SZ];
8608  byte cpSet[MAX_SET_SZ];
8609  byte cpStr[MAX_PRSTR_SZ];
8610  byte erSeq[MAX_SEQ_SZ];
8611  byte erSet[MAX_SET_SZ];
8612 
8613  output[0] = 0xa0;
8614  sz++;
8615 
8616  if (pw && pw[0]) {
8617  pwSz = (int)XSTRLEN(pw);
8618  cpStrSz = SetUTF8String(pwSz, cpStr);
8619  cpSetSz = SetSet(cpStrSz + pwSz, cpSet);
8620  cpSeqSz = SetSequence(sizeof(cpOid) + cpSetSz + cpStrSz + pwSz, cpSeq);
8621  cpSz = cpSeqSz + sizeof(cpOid) + cpSetSz + cpStrSz + pwSz;
8622  }
8623 
8624  if (extSz) {
8625  erSetSz = SetSet(extSz, erSet);
8626  erSeqSz = SetSequence(erSetSz + sizeof(erOid) + extSz, erSeq);
8627  erSz = extSz + erSetSz + erSeqSz + sizeof(erOid);
8628  }
8629 
8630  /* Put the pieces together. */
8631  sz += SetLength(cpSz + erSz, &output[sz]);
8632 
8633  if (cpSz) {
8634  XMEMCPY(&output[sz], cpSeq, cpSeqSz);
8635  sz += cpSeqSz;
8636  XMEMCPY(&output[sz], cpOid, sizeof(cpOid));
8637  sz += sizeof(cpOid);
8638  XMEMCPY(&output[sz], cpSet, cpSetSz);
8639  sz += cpSetSz;
8640  XMEMCPY(&output[sz], cpStr, cpStrSz);
8641  sz += cpStrSz;
8642  XMEMCPY(&output[sz], pw, pwSz);
8643  sz += pwSz;
8644  }
8645 
8646  if (erSz) {
8647  XMEMCPY(&output[sz], erSeq, erSeqSz);
8648  sz += erSeqSz;
8649  XMEMCPY(&output[sz], erOid, sizeof(erOid));
8650  sz += sizeof(erOid);
8651  XMEMCPY(&output[sz], erSet, erSetSz);
8652  sz += erSetSz;
8653  /* The actual extension data will be tacked onto the output later. */
8654  }
8655 
8656  return sz;
8657 }
8658 
8659 
8660 /* encode info from cert into DER encoded format */
8661 static int EncodeCertReq(Cert* cert, DerCert* der, RsaKey* rsaKey,
8662  ecc_key* eccKey, ed25519_key* ed25519Key)
8663 {
8664  (void)eccKey;
8665  (void)ed25519Key;
8666 
8667  if (cert == NULL || der == NULL)
8668  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
8669 
8670  /* init */
8671  XMEMSET(der, 0, sizeof(DerCert));
8672 
8673  /* version */
8674  der->versionSz = SetMyVersion(cert->version, der->version, FALSE);
8675 
8676  /* subject name */
8677  der->subjectSz = SetName(der->subject, sizeof(der->subject), &cert->subject);
8678  if (der->subjectSz <= 0)
8679  return SUBJECT_E;
8680 
8681  /* public key */
8682  if (cert->keyType == RSA_KEY) {
8683  if (rsaKey == NULL)
8684  return PUBLIC_KEY_E;
8685  der->publicKeySz = SetRsaPublicKey(der->publicKey, rsaKey,
8686  sizeof(der->publicKey), 1);
8687  if (der->publicKeySz <= 0)
8688  return PUBLIC_KEY_E;
8689  }
8690 
8691 #ifdef HAVE_ECC
8692  if (cert->keyType == ECC_KEY) {
8693  if (eccKey == NULL)
8694  return PUBLIC_KEY_E;
8695  der->publicKeySz = SetEccPublicKey(der->publicKey, eccKey, 1);
8696  if (der->publicKeySz <= 0)
8697  return PUBLIC_KEY_E;
8698  }
8699 #endif /* HAVE_ECC */
8700 
8701 #ifdef HAVE_ED25519
8702  if (cert->keyType == ED25519_KEY) {
8703  if (ed25519Key == NULL)
8704  return PUBLIC_KEY_E;
8705  der->publicKeySz = SetEd25519PublicKey(der->publicKey, ed25519Key, 1);
8706  if (der->publicKeySz <= 0)
8707  return PUBLIC_KEY_E;
8708  }
8709 #endif /* HAVE_ED25519 */
8710 
8711  /* set the extensions */
8712  der->extensionsSz = 0;
8713 
8714  /* CA */
8715  if (cert->isCA) {
8716  der->caSz = SetCa(der->ca, sizeof(der->ca));
8717  if (der->caSz <= 0)
8718  return CA_TRUE_E;
8719 
8720  der->extensionsSz += der->caSz;
8721  }
8722  else
8723  der->caSz = 0;
8724 
8725 #ifdef WOLFSSL_CERT_EXT
8726  /* SKID */
8727  if (cert->skidSz) {
8728  /* check the provided SKID size */
8729  if (cert->skidSz > (int)sizeof(der->skid))
8730  return SKID_E;
8731 
8732  der->skidSz = SetSKID(der->skid, sizeof(der->skid),
8733  cert->skid, cert->skidSz);
8734  if (der->skidSz <= 0)
8735  return SKID_E;
8736 
8737  der->extensionsSz += der->skidSz;
8738  }
8739  else
8740  der->skidSz = 0;
8741 
8742  /* Key Usage */
8743  if (cert->keyUsage != 0){
8744  der->keyUsageSz = SetKeyUsage(der->keyUsage, sizeof(der->keyUsage),
8745  cert->keyUsage);
8746  if (der->keyUsageSz <= 0)
8747  return KEYUSAGE_E;
8748 
8749  der->extensionsSz += der->keyUsageSz;
8750  }
8751  else
8752  der->keyUsageSz = 0;
8753 #endif /* WOLFSSL_CERT_EXT */
8754 
8755  /* put extensions */
8756  if (der->extensionsSz > 0) {
8757  int ret;
8758 
8759  /* put the start of sequence (ID, Size) */
8760  der->extensionsSz = SetSequence(der->extensionsSz, der->extensions);
8761  if (der->extensionsSz <= 0)
8762  return EXTENSIONS_E;
8763 
8764  /* put CA */
8765  if (der->caSz) {
8766  ret = SetExtensions(der->extensions, sizeof(der->extensions),
8767  &der->extensionsSz,
8768  der->ca, der->caSz);
8769  if (ret <= 0)
8770  return EXTENSIONS_E;
8771  }
8772 
8773 #ifdef WOLFSSL_CERT_EXT
8774  /* put SKID */
8775  if (der->skidSz) {
8776  ret = SetExtensions(der->extensions, sizeof(der->extensions),
8777  &der->extensionsSz,
8778  der->skid, der->skidSz);
8779  if (ret <= 0)
8780  return EXTENSIONS_E;
8781  }
8782 
8783  /* put AKID */
8784  if (der->akidSz) {
8785  ret = SetExtensions(der->extensions, sizeof(der->extensions),
8786  &der->extensionsSz,
8787  der->akid, der->akidSz);
8788  if (ret <= 0)
8789  return EXTENSIONS_E;
8790  }
8791 
8792  /* put KeyUsage */
8793  if (der->keyUsageSz) {
8794  ret = SetExtensions(der->extensions, sizeof(der->extensions),
8795  &der->extensionsSz,
8796  der->keyUsage, der->keyUsageSz);
8797  if (ret <= 0)
8798  return EXTENSIONS_E;
8799  }
8800 
8801 #endif /* WOLFSSL_CERT_EXT */
8802  }
8803 
8804  der->attribSz = SetReqAttrib(der->attrib,
8805  cert->challengePw, der->extensionsSz);
8806  if (der->attribSz <= 0)
8807  return REQ_ATTRIBUTE_E;
8808 
8809  der->total = der->versionSz + der->subjectSz + der->publicKeySz +
8810  der->extensionsSz + der->attribSz;
8811 
8812  return 0;
8813 }
8814 
8815 
8816 /* write DER encoded cert req to buffer, size already checked */
8817 static int WriteCertReqBody(DerCert* der, byte* buffer)
8818 {
8819  int idx;
8820 
8821  /* signed part header */
8822  idx = SetSequence(der->total, buffer);
8823  /* version */
8824  XMEMCPY(buffer + idx, der->version, der->versionSz);
8825  idx += der->versionSz;
8826  /* subject */
8827  XMEMCPY(buffer + idx, der->subject, der->subjectSz);
8828  idx += der->subjectSz;
8829  /* public key */
8830  XMEMCPY(buffer + idx, der->publicKey, der->publicKeySz);
8831  idx += der->publicKeySz;
8832  /* attributes */
8833  XMEMCPY(buffer + idx, der->attrib, der->attribSz);
8834  idx += der->attribSz;
8835  /* extensions */
8836  if (der->extensionsSz) {
8837  XMEMCPY(buffer + idx, der->extensions, min(der->extensionsSz,
8838  (int)sizeof(der->extensions)));
8839  idx += der->extensionsSz;
8840  }
8841 
8842  return idx;
8843 }
8844

8846 static int MakeCertReq(Cert* cert, byte* derBuffer, word32 derSz,
8847  RsaKey* rsaKey, ecc_key* eccKey, ed25519_key* ed25519Key)
8848 {
8849  int ret;
8850 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
8851  DerCert* der;
8852 #else
8853  DerCert der[1];
8854 #endif
8855 
8856  cert->keyType = eccKey ? ECC_KEY : (ed25519Key ? ED25519_KEY : RSA_KEY);
8857 
8858 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
8859  der = (DerCert*)XMALLOC(sizeof(DerCert), NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
8860  if (der == NULL)
8861  return MEMORY_E;
8862 #endif
8863 
8864  ret = EncodeCertReq(cert, der, rsaKey, eccKey, ed25519Key);
8865 
8866  if (ret == 0) {
8867  if (der->total + MAX_SEQ_SZ * 2 > (int)derSz)
8868  ret = BUFFER_E;
8869  else
8870  ret = cert->bodySz = WriteCertReqBody(der, derBuffer);
8871  }
8872 
8873 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
8874  XFREE(der, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
8875 #endif
8876 
8877  return ret;
8878 }

8904 
8905 static int SignCert(int requestSz, int sType, byte* buffer, word32 buffSz,
8906  RsaKey* rsaKey, ecc_key* eccKey, ed25519_key* ed25519Key,
8907  WC_RNG* rng)
8908 {
8909  int sigSz = 0;
8910  void* heap = NULL;
8911  CertSignCtx* certSignCtx = NULL;
8912 #ifndef WOLFSSL_ASYNC_CRYPT
8913  CertSignCtx certSignCtx_lcl;
8914  certSignCtx = &certSignCtx_lcl;
8915  XMEMSET(certSignCtx, 0, sizeof(CertSignCtx));
8916 #endif
8917 
8918  if (requestSz < 0)
8919  return requestSz;
8920 
8921  /* locate ctx */
8922  if (rsaKey) {
8923  #ifndef NO_RSA
8924  #ifdef WOLFSSL_ASYNC_CRYPT
8925  certSignCtx = &rsaKey->certSignCtx;
8926  #endif
8927  heap = rsaKey->heap;
8928  #else
8929  return NOT_COMPILED_IN;
8930  #endif /* NO_RSA */
8931  }
8932  else if (eccKey) {
8933  #ifdef HAVE_ECC
8934  #ifdef WOLFSSL_ASYNC_CRYPT
8935  certSignCtx = &eccKey->certSignCtx;
8936  #endif
8937  heap = eccKey->heap;
8938  #else
8939  return NOT_COMPILED_IN;
8940  #endif /* HAVE_ECC */
8941  }
8942 
8943 #ifdef WOLFSSL_ASYNC_CRYPT
8944  if (certSignCtx == NULL) {
8945  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
8946  }
8947 #endif
8948 
8949  if (certSignCtx->sig == NULL) {
8950  certSignCtx->sig = (byte*)XMALLOC(MAX_ENCODED_SIG_SZ, heap,
8951  DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
8952  if (certSignCtx->sig == NULL)
8953  return MEMORY_E;
8954  }
8955 
8956  sigSz = MakeSignature(certSignCtx, buffer, requestSz, certSignCtx->sig,
8957  MAX_ENCODED_SIG_SZ, rsaKey, eccKey, ed25519Key, rng, sType, heap);
8958  if (sigSz == WC_PENDING_E)
8959  return sigSz;
8960 
8961  if (sigSz >= 0) {
8962  if (requestSz + MAX_SEQ_SZ * 2 + sigSz > (int)buffSz)
8963  sigSz = BUFFER_E;
8964  else
8965  sigSz = AddSignature(buffer, requestSz, certSignCtx->sig, sigSz, sType);
8966  }
8967 
8968  XFREE(certSignCtx->sig, heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
8969  certSignCtx->sig = NULL;
8970 
8971  return sigSz;
8972 }
8973 
8974 int wc_SignCert_ex(int requestSz, int sType, byte* buffer, word32 buffSz,
8975  int keyType, void* key, WC_RNG* rng)
8976 {
8977  RsaKey* rsaKey = NULL;
8978  ecc_key* eccKey = NULL;
8979  ed25519_key* ed25519Key = NULL;
8980 
8981  if (keyType == RSA_TYPE)
8982  rsaKey = (RsaKey*)key;
8983  else if (keyType == ECC_TYPE)
8984  eccKey = (ecc_key*)key;
8985  else if (keyType == ED25519_TYPE)
8986  ed25519Key = (ed25519_key*)key;
8987 
8988  return SignCert(requestSz, sType, buffer, buffSz, rsaKey, eccKey,
8989  ed25519Key, rng);
8990 }

8992 int wc_SignCert(int requestSz, int sType, byte* buffer, word32 buffSz,
8993  RsaKey* rsaKey, ecc_key* eccKey, WC_RNG* rng)
8994 {
8995  return SignCert(requestSz, sType, buffer, buffSz, rsaKey, eccKey, NULL,
8996  rng);

8999 int wc_MakeSelfCert(Cert* cert, byte* buffer, word32 buffSz,
9000  RsaKey* key, WC_RNG* rng)
9001 {
9002  int ret;
9003 
9004  ret = wc_MakeCert(cert, buffer, buffSz, key, NULL, rng);
9005  if (ret < 0)
9006  return ret;
9007 
9008  return wc_SignCert(cert->bodySz, cert->sigType,
9009  buffer, buffSz, key, NULL, rng);

9012 
9013 #ifdef WOLFSSL_CERT_EXT
9014 
9015 /* Set KID from RSA or ECC public key */
9016 static int SetKeyIdFromPublicKey(Cert *cert, RsaKey *rsakey, ecc_key *eckey,
9017  byte *ntruKey, word16 ntruKeySz,
9018  ed25519_key* ed25519Key, int kid_type)
9019 {
9020  byte *buffer;
9021  int bufferSz, ret;
9022 
9023 #ifndef HAVE_NTRU
9024  (void)ntruKeySz;
9025 #endif
9026 
9027  if (cert == NULL ||
9028  (rsakey == NULL && eckey == NULL && ntruKey == NULL &&
9029  ed25519Key == NULL) ||
9030  (rsakey != NULL && eckey != NULL) ||
9031  (rsakey != NULL && ntruKey != NULL) ||
9032  (ntruKey != NULL && eckey != NULL) ||
9033  (kid_type != SKID_TYPE && kid_type != AKID_TYPE))
9034  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
9035 
9036  buffer = (byte *)XMALLOC(MAX_PUBLIC_KEY_SZ, cert->heap,
9037  DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
9038  if (buffer == NULL)
9039  return MEMORY_E;
9040 
9041  /* RSA public key */
9042  if (rsakey != NULL)
9043  bufferSz = SetRsaPublicKey(buffer, rsakey, MAX_PUBLIC_KEY_SZ, 0);
9044 #ifdef HAVE_ECC
9045  /* ECC public key */
9046  else if (eckey != NULL)
9047  bufferSz = SetEccPublicKey(buffer, eckey, 0);
9048 #endif /* HAVE_ECC */
9049 #ifdef HAVE_NTRU
9050  /* NTRU public key */
9051  else if (ntruKey != NULL) {
9052  bufferSz = MAX_PUBLIC_KEY_SZ;
9053  ret = ntru_crypto_ntru_encrypt_publicKey2SubjectPublicKeyInfo(
9054  ntruKeySz, ntruKey, (word16 *)(&bufferSz), buffer);
9055  if (ret != NTRU_OK)
9056  bufferSz = -1;
9057  }
9058 #endif
9059 #ifdef HAVE_ED25519
9060  /* ED25519 public key */
9061  else if (ed25519Key != NULL)
9062  bufferSz = SetEd25519PublicKey(buffer, ed25519Key, 0);
9063 #endif /* HAVE_ECC */
9064  else
9065  bufferSz = -1;
9066 
9067  if (bufferSz <= 0) {
9068  XFREE(buffer, cert->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
9069  return PUBLIC_KEY_E;
9070  }
9071 
9072  /* Compute SKID by hashing public key */
9073 #ifdef NO_SHA
9074  if (kid_type == SKID_TYPE) {
9075  ret = wc_Sha256Hash(buffer, bufferSz, cert->skid);
9076  cert->skidSz = SHA256_DIGEST_SIZE;
9077  }
9078  else if (kid_type == AKID_TYPE) {
9079  ret = wc_Sha256Hash(buffer, bufferSz, cert->akid);
9080  cert->akidSz = SHA256_DIGEST_SIZE;
9081  }
9082  else
9083  ret = BAD_FUNC_ARG;
9084 #else /* NO_SHA */
9085  if (kid_type == SKID_TYPE) {
9086  ret = wc_ShaHash(buffer, bufferSz, cert->skid);
9087  cert->skidSz = SHA_DIGEST_SIZE;
9088  }
9089  else if (kid_type == AKID_TYPE) {
9090  ret = wc_ShaHash(buffer, bufferSz, cert->akid);
9091  cert->akidSz = SHA_DIGEST_SIZE;
9092  }
9093  else
9094  ret = BAD_FUNC_ARG;
9095 #endif /* NO_SHA */
9096 
9097  XFREE(buffer, cert->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
9098  return ret;
9099 }

9102 {
9103  RsaKey* rsaKey = NULL;
9104  ecc_key* eccKey = NULL;
9105  ed25519_key* ed25519Key = NULL;

9108  rsaKey = (RsaKey*)key;
9109  else if (keyType == ECC_TYPE)
9110  eccKey = (ecc_key*)key;
9111  else if (keyType == ED25519_TYPE)
9112  ed25519Key = (ed25519_key*)key;
9113 
9114  return SetKeyIdFromPublicKey(cert, rsaKey, eccKey, NULL, 0, ed25519Key,
9115  SKID_TYPE);
9116 }

9160 /* Set SKID from public key file in PEM */
9161 int wc_SetSubjectKeyId(Cert *cert, const char* file)
9162 {
9163  int ret, derSz;
9164  byte* der;
9165  word32 idx;
9166  RsaKey *rsakey = NULL;
9167  ecc_key *eckey = NULL;
9168 
9169  if (cert == NULL || file == NULL)
9170  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
9171 
9172  der = (byte*)XMALLOC(MAX_PUBLIC_KEY_SZ, cert->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_CERT);
9173  if (der == NULL) {
9174  WOLFSSL_MSG("wc_SetSubjectKeyId memory Problem");
9175  return MEMORY_E;
9176  }
9177 
9178  derSz = wolfSSL_PemPubKeyToDer(file, der, MAX_PUBLIC_KEY_SZ);
9179  if (derSz <= 0)
9180  {
9181  XFREE(der, cert->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_CERT);
9182  return derSz;
9183  }
9184 
9185  /* Load PubKey in internal structure */
9186  rsakey = (RsaKey*) XMALLOC(sizeof(RsaKey), cert->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_RSA);
9187  if (rsakey == NULL) {
9188  XFREE(der, cert->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_CERT);
9189  return MEMORY_E;
9190  }
9191 
9192  if (wc_InitRsaKey(rsakey, cert->heap) != 0) {
9193  WOLFSSL_MSG("wc_InitRsaKey failure");
9194  XFREE(rsakey, cert->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_RSA);
9195  XFREE(der, cert->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_CERT);
9196  return MEMORY_E;
9197  }
9198 
9199  idx = 0;
9200  ret = wc_RsaPublicKeyDecode(der, &idx, rsakey, derSz);
9201  if (ret != 0) {
9202  WOLFSSL_MSG("wc_RsaPublicKeyDecode failed");
9203  wc_FreeRsaKey(rsakey);
9204  XFREE(rsakey, cert->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_RSA);
9205  rsakey = NULL;
9206 #ifdef HAVE_ECC
9207  /* Check to load ecc public key */
9208  eckey = (ecc_key*) XMALLOC(sizeof(ecc_key), cert->heap,
9209  DYNAMIC_TYPE_ECC);
9210  if (eckey == NULL) {
9211  XFREE(der, cert->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_CERT);
9212  return MEMORY_E;
9213  }
9214 
9215  if (wc_ecc_init(eckey) != 0) {
9216  WOLFSSL_MSG("wc_ecc_init failure");
9217  wc_ecc_free(eckey);
9218  XFREE(eckey, cert->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_ECC);
9219  XFREE(der, cert->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_CERT);
9220  return MEMORY_E;
9221  }
9222 
9223  idx = 0;
9224  ret = wc_EccPublicKeyDecode(der, &idx, eckey, derSz);
9225  if (ret != 0) {
9226  WOLFSSL_MSG("wc_EccPublicKeyDecode failed");
9227  XFREE(der, cert->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_CERT);
9228  wc_ecc_free(eckey);
9229  return PUBLIC_KEY_E;
9230  }
9231 #else
9232  XFREE(der, cert->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_CERT);
9233  return PUBLIC_KEY_E;
9234 #endif /* HAVE_ECC */
9235  }
9236 
9237  XFREE(der, cert->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_CERT);
9238 
9239  ret = wc_SetSubjectKeyIdFromPublicKey(cert, rsakey, eckey);
9240 
9241  wc_FreeRsaKey(rsakey);
9242  XFREE(rsakey, cert->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_RSA);
9243 #ifdef HAVE_ECC
9244  wc_ecc_free(eckey);
9245  XFREE(eckey, cert->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_ECC);
9246 #endif
9247  return ret;
9248 }
9249 
9250 #endif /* NO_FILESYSTEM */
9251 
9252 /* Set AKID from certificate contains in buffer (DER encoded) */
9253 int wc_SetAuthKeyIdFromCert(Cert *cert, const byte *der, int derSz)
9254 {
9255  int ret;
9256 
9257 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
9258  DecodedCert* decoded;
9259 #else
9260  DecodedCert decoded[1];
9261 #endif
9262 
9263  if (cert == NULL || der == NULL || derSz <= 0)
9264  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
9265 
9266 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
9267  decoded = (DecodedCert*)XMALLOC(sizeof(DecodedCert),
9268  NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
9269  if (decoded == NULL)
9270  return MEMORY_E;
9271 #endif
9272 
9273  /* decode certificate and get SKID that will be AKID of current cert */
9274  InitDecodedCert(decoded, (byte*)der, derSz, NULL);
9275  ret = ParseCert(decoded, CERT_TYPE, NO_VERIFY, 0);
9276  if (ret != 0) {
9277  FreeDecodedCert(decoded);
9278  #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
9279  XFREE(decoded, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
9280  #endif
9281  return ret;
9282  }
9283 
9284  /* Subject Key Id not found !! */
9285  if (decoded->extSubjKeyIdSet == 0) {
9286  FreeDecodedCert(decoded);
9287  #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
9288  XFREE(decoded, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
9289  #endif
9290  return ASN_NO_SKID;
9291  }
9292 
9293  /* SKID invalid size */
9294  if (sizeof(cert->akid) < sizeof(decoded->extSubjKeyId)) {
9295  FreeDecodedCert(decoded);
9296  #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
9297  XFREE(decoded, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
9298  #endif
9299  return MEMORY_E;
9300  }
9301 
9302  /* Put the SKID of CA to AKID of certificate */
9303  XMEMCPY(cert->akid, decoded->extSubjKeyId, KEYID_SIZE);
9304  cert->akidSz = KEYID_SIZE;
9305 
9306  FreeDecodedCert(decoded);
9307  #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
9308  XFREE(decoded, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
9309  #endif
9310 
9311  return 0;
9312 }

9315 #ifndef NO_FILESYSTEM

9317 /* Set AKID from certificate file in PEM */
9318 int wc_SetAuthKeyId(Cert *cert, const char* file)
9319 {
9320  int ret;
9321  int derSz;
9322  byte* der;
9323 
9324  if (cert == NULL || file == NULL)
9325  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
9326 
9327  der = (byte*)XMALLOC(EIGHTK_BUF, cert->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_CERT);
9328  if (der == NULL) {
9329  WOLFSSL_MSG("wc_SetAuthKeyId OOF Problem");
9330  return MEMORY_E;
9331  }
9332 
9333  derSz = wolfSSL_PemCertToDer(file, der, EIGHTK_BUF);
9334  if (derSz <= 0)
9335  {
9336  XFREE(der, cert->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_CERT);
9337  return derSz;
9338  }
9339 
9340  ret = wc_SetAuthKeyIdFromCert(cert, der, derSz);
9341  XFREE(der, cert->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_CERT);
9342 
9343  return ret;
9344 }

9348 /* Set KeyUsage from human readable string */
9349 int wc_SetKeyUsage(Cert *cert, const char *value)
9350 {
9351  int ret = 0;
9352  char *token, *str, *ptr;
9353  word32 len;
9354 
9355  if (cert == NULL || value == NULL)
9356  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
9357 
9358  cert->keyUsage = 0;
9359 
9360  str = (char *)XMALLOC(XSTRLEN(value)+1, cert->heap,
9361  DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
9362  if (str == NULL)
9363  return MEMORY_E;
9364 
9365  XMEMSET(str, 0, XSTRLEN(value)+1);
9366  XSTRNCPY(str, value, XSTRLEN(value));
9367 
9368  /* parse value, and set corresponding Key Usage value */
9369  if ((token = XSTRTOK(str, ",", &ptr)) == NULL) {
9370  XFREE(str, cert->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
9371  return KEYUSAGE_E;
9372  }
9373  while (token != NULL)
9374  {
9375  len = (word32)XSTRLEN(token);
9376 
9377  if (!XSTRNCASECMP(token, "digitalSignature", len))
9378  cert->keyUsage |= KEYUSE_DIGITAL_SIG;
9379  else if (!XSTRNCASECMP(token, "nonRepudiation", len) ||
9380  !XSTRNCASECMP(token, "contentCommitment", len))
9381  cert->keyUsage |= KEYUSE_CONTENT_COMMIT;
9382  else if (!XSTRNCASECMP(token, "keyEncipherment", len))
9383  cert->keyUsage |= KEYUSE_KEY_ENCIPHER;
9384  else if (!XSTRNCASECMP(token, "dataEncipherment", len))
9385  cert->keyUsage |= KEYUSE_DATA_ENCIPHER;
9386  else if (!XSTRNCASECMP(token, "keyAgreement", len))
9387  cert->keyUsage |= KEYUSE_KEY_AGREE;
9388  else if (!XSTRNCASECMP(token, "keyCertSign", len))
9389  cert->keyUsage |= KEYUSE_KEY_CERT_SIGN;
9390  else if (!XSTRNCASECMP(token, "cRLSign", len))
9391  cert->keyUsage |= KEYUSE_CRL_SIGN;
9392  else if (!XSTRNCASECMP(token, "encipherOnly", len))
9393  cert->keyUsage |= KEYUSE_ENCIPHER_ONLY;
9394  else if (!XSTRNCASECMP(token, "decipherOnly", len))
9395  cert->keyUsage |= KEYUSE_DECIPHER_ONLY;
9396  else {
9397  ret = KEYUSAGE_E;
9398  break;
9399  }
9400 
9401  token = XSTRTOK(NULL, ",", &ptr);
9402  }
9403 
9404  XFREE(str, cert->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
9405  return ret;
9406 }
9407 #endif /* WOLFSSL_CERT_EXT */

9411 
9412 /* Set Alt Names from der cert, return 0 on success */
9413 static int SetAltNamesFromCert(Cert* cert, const byte* der, int derSz)
9414 {
9415  int ret;
9416 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
9417  DecodedCert* decoded;
9418 #else
9419  DecodedCert decoded[1];
9420 #endif
9421 
9422  if (derSz < 0)
9423  return derSz;
9424 
9425 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
9426  decoded = (DecodedCert*)XMALLOC(sizeof(DecodedCert), NULL,
9427  DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
9428  if (decoded == NULL)
9429  return MEMORY_E;
9430 #endif
9431 
9432  InitDecodedCert(decoded, (byte*)der, derSz, NULL);
9433  ret = ParseCertRelative(decoded, CA_TYPE, NO_VERIFY, 0);
9434 
9435  if (ret < 0) {
9436  WOLFSSL_MSG("ParseCertRelative error");
9437  }
9438  else if (decoded->extensions) {
9439  byte b;
9440  int length;
9441  word32 maxExtensionsIdx;
9442 
9443  decoded->srcIdx = decoded->extensionsIdx;
9444  b = decoded->source[decoded->srcIdx++];
9445 
9446  if (b != ASN_EXTENSIONS) {
9447  ret = ASN_PARSE_E;
9448  }
9449  else if (GetLength(decoded->source, &decoded->srcIdx, &length,
9450  decoded->maxIdx) < 0) {
9451  ret = ASN_PARSE_E;
9452  }
9453  else if (GetSequence(decoded->source, &decoded->srcIdx, &length,
9454  decoded->maxIdx) < 0) {
9455  ret = ASN_PARSE_E;
9456  }
9457  else {
9458  maxExtensionsIdx = decoded->srcIdx + length;
9459 
9460  while (decoded->srcIdx < maxExtensionsIdx) {
9461  word32 oid;
9462  word32 startIdx = decoded->srcIdx;
9463  word32 tmpIdx;
9464 
9465  if (GetSequence(decoded->source, &decoded->srcIdx, &length,
9466  decoded->maxIdx) < 0) {
9467  ret = ASN_PARSE_E;
9468  break;
9469  }
9470 
9471  tmpIdx = decoded->srcIdx;
9472  decoded->srcIdx = startIdx;
9473 
9474  if (GetAlgoId(decoded->source, &decoded->srcIdx, &oid,
9475  oidCertExtType, decoded->maxIdx) < 0) {
9476  ret = ASN_PARSE_E;
9477  break;
9478  }
9479 
9480  if (oid == ALT_NAMES_OID) {
9481  cert->altNamesSz = length + (tmpIdx - startIdx);
9482 
9483  if (cert->altNamesSz < (int)sizeof(cert->altNames))
9484  XMEMCPY(cert->altNames, &decoded->source[startIdx],
9485  cert->altNamesSz);
9486  else {
9487  cert->altNamesSz = 0;
9488  WOLFSSL_MSG("AltNames extensions too big");
9489  ret = ALT_NAME_E;
9490  break;
9491  }
9492  }
9493  decoded->srcIdx = tmpIdx + length;
9494  }
9495  }
9496  }
9497 
9498  FreeDecodedCert(decoded);
9499 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
9500  XFREE(decoded, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
9501 #endif
9502 
9503  return ret < 0 ? ret : 0;
9504 }
9505

9507 /* Set Dates from der cert, return 0 on success */
9508 static int SetDatesFromCert(Cert* cert, const byte* der, int derSz)
9509 {
9510  int ret;
9511 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
9512  DecodedCert* decoded;
9513 #else
9514  DecodedCert decoded[1];
9515 #endif
9516 
9517  WOLFSSL_ENTER("SetDatesFromCert");
9518  if (derSz < 0)
9519  return derSz;
9520 
9521 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
9522  decoded = (DecodedCert*)XMALLOC(sizeof(DecodedCert), NULL,
9523  DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
9524  if (decoded == NULL)
9525  return MEMORY_E;
9526 #endif
9527 
9528  InitDecodedCert(decoded, (byte*)der, derSz, NULL);
9529  ret = ParseCertRelative(decoded, CA_TYPE, NO_VERIFY, 0);
9530 
9531  if (ret < 0) {
9532  WOLFSSL_MSG("ParseCertRelative error");
9533  }
9534  else if (decoded->beforeDate == NULL || decoded->afterDate == NULL) {
9535  WOLFSSL_MSG("Couldn't extract dates");
9536  ret = -1;
9537  }
9538  else if (decoded->beforeDateLen > MAX_DATE_SIZE ||
9539  decoded->afterDateLen > MAX_DATE_SIZE) {
9540  WOLFSSL_MSG("Bad date size");
9541  ret = -1;
9542  }
9543  else {
9544  XMEMCPY(cert->beforeDate, decoded->beforeDate, decoded->beforeDateLen);
9545  XMEMCPY(cert->afterDate, decoded->afterDate, decoded->afterDateLen);
9546 
9547  cert->beforeDateSz = decoded->beforeDateLen;
9548  cert->afterDateSz = decoded->afterDateLen;
9549  }
9550 
9551  FreeDecodedCert(decoded);
9552 
9553 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
9554  XFREE(decoded, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
9555 #endif
9556 
9557  return ret < 0 ? ret : 0;
9558 }

9564 /* Set cn name from der buffer, return 0 on success */
9565 static int SetNameFromCert(CertName* cn, const byte* der, int derSz)
9566 {
9567  int ret, sz;
9568 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
9569  DecodedCert* decoded;
9570 #else
9571  DecodedCert decoded[1];
9572 #endif
9573 
9574  if (derSz < 0)
9575  return derSz;
9576 
9577 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
9578  decoded = (DecodedCert*)XMALLOC(sizeof(DecodedCert), NULL,
9579  DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
9580  if (decoded == NULL)
9581  return MEMORY_E;
9582 #endif
9583 
9584  InitDecodedCert(decoded, (byte*)der, derSz, NULL);
9585  ret = ParseCertRelative(decoded, CA_TYPE, NO_VERIFY, 0);
9586 
9587  if (ret < 0) {
9588  WOLFSSL_MSG("ParseCertRelative error");
9589  }
9590  else {
9591  if (decoded->subjectCN) {
9592  sz = (decoded->subjectCNLen < CTC_NAME_SIZE) ? decoded->subjectCNLen
9593  : CTC_NAME_SIZE - 1;
9594  XSTRNCPY(cn->commonName, decoded->subjectCN, CTC_NAME_SIZE);
9595  cn->commonName[sz] = 0;
9596  cn->commonNameEnc = decoded->subjectCNEnc;
9597  }
9598  if (decoded->subjectC) {
9599  sz = (decoded->subjectCLen < CTC_NAME_SIZE) ? decoded->subjectCLen
9600  : CTC_NAME_SIZE - 1;
9601  XSTRNCPY(cn->country, decoded->subjectC, CTC_NAME_SIZE);
9602  cn->country[sz] = 0;
9603  cn->countryEnc = decoded->subjectCEnc;
9604  }
9605  if (decoded->subjectST) {
9606  sz = (decoded->subjectSTLen < CTC_NAME_SIZE) ? decoded->subjectSTLen
9607  : CTC_NAME_SIZE - 1;
9608  XSTRNCPY(cn->state, decoded->subjectST, CTC_NAME_SIZE);
9609  cn->state[sz] = 0;
9610  cn->stateEnc = decoded->subjectSTEnc;
9611  }
9612  if (decoded->subjectL) {
9613  sz = (decoded->subjectLLen < CTC_NAME_SIZE) ? decoded->subjectLLen
9614  : CTC_NAME_SIZE - 1;
9615  XSTRNCPY(cn->locality, decoded->subjectL, CTC_NAME_SIZE);
9616  cn->locality[sz] = 0;
9617  cn->localityEnc = decoded->subjectLEnc;
9618  }
9619  if (decoded->subjectO) {
9620  sz = (decoded->subjectOLen < CTC_NAME_SIZE) ? decoded->subjectOLen
9621  : CTC_NAME_SIZE - 1;
9622  XSTRNCPY(cn->org, decoded->subjectO, CTC_NAME_SIZE);
9623  cn->org[sz] = 0;
9624  cn->orgEnc = decoded->subjectOEnc;
9625  }
9626  if (decoded->subjectOU) {
9627  sz = (decoded->subjectOULen < CTC_NAME_SIZE) ? decoded->subjectOULen
9628  : CTC_NAME_SIZE - 1;
9629  XSTRNCPY(cn->unit, decoded->subjectOU, CTC_NAME_SIZE);
9630  cn->unit[sz] = 0;
9631  cn->unitEnc = decoded->subjectOUEnc;
9632  }
9633  if (decoded->subjectSN) {
9634  sz = (decoded->subjectSNLen < CTC_NAME_SIZE) ? decoded->subjectSNLen
9635  : CTC_NAME_SIZE - 1;
9636  XSTRNCPY(cn->sur, decoded->subjectSN, CTC_NAME_SIZE);
9637  cn->sur[sz] = 0;
9638  cn->surEnc = decoded->subjectSNEnc;
9639  }
9640  if (decoded->subjectEmail) {
9641  sz = (decoded->subjectEmailLen < CTC_NAME_SIZE)
9642  ? decoded->subjectEmailLen : CTC_NAME_SIZE - 1;
9643  XSTRNCPY(cn->email, decoded->subjectEmail, CTC_NAME_SIZE);
9644  cn->email[sz] = 0;
9645  }
9646  }
9647 
9648  FreeDecodedCert(decoded);
9649 
9650 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
9651  XFREE(decoded, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
9652 #endif
9653 
9654  return ret < 0 ? ret : 0;
9655 }

9660 /* Set cert issuer from issuerFile in PEM */

9675

9757 #ifdef HAVE_ECC
9758 
9759 /* Der Encode r & s ints into out, outLen is (in/out) size */
9760 int StoreECC_DSA_Sig(byte* out, word32* outLen, mp_int* r, mp_int* s)
9761 {
9762  word32 idx = 0;
9763  int rSz; /* encoding size */
9764  int sSz;
9765  word32 headerSz = 4; /* 2*ASN_TAG + 2*LEN(ENUM) */
9766 
9767  /* If the leading bit on the INTEGER is a 1, add a leading zero */
9768  int rLeadingZero = mp_leading_bit(r);
9769  int sLeadingZero = mp_leading_bit(s);
9770  int rLen = mp_unsigned_bin_size(r); /* big int size */
9771  int sLen = mp_unsigned_bin_size(s);
9772 
9773  if (*outLen < (rLen + rLeadingZero + sLen + sLeadingZero +
9774  headerSz + 2)) /* SEQ_TAG + LEN(ENUM) */
9775  return BUFFER_E;
9776 
9777  idx = SetSequence(rLen + rLeadingZero + sLen+sLeadingZero + headerSz, out);
9778 
9779  /* store r */
9780  rSz = SetASNIntMP(r, -1, &out[idx]);
9781  if (rSz < 0)
9782  return rSz;
9783  idx += rSz;
9784 
9785  /* store s */
9786  sSz = SetASNIntMP(s, -1, &out[idx]);
9787  if (sSz < 0)
9788  return sSz;
9789  idx += sSz;
9790 
9791  *outLen = idx;
9792 
9793  return 0;
9794 }
9795 
9796 
9797 /* Der Decode ECC-DSA Signature, r & s stored as big ints */
9798 int DecodeECC_DSA_Sig(const byte* sig, word32 sigLen, mp_int* r, mp_int* s)
9799 {
9800  word32 idx = 0;
9801  int len = 0;
9802 
9803  if (GetSequence(sig, &idx, &len, sigLen) < 0) {
9804  return ASN_ECC_KEY_E;
9805  }
9806 
9807  if ((word32)len > (sigLen - idx)) {
9808  return ASN_ECC_KEY_E;
9809  }
9810 
9811  if (GetInt(r, sig, &idx, sigLen) < 0) {
9812  return ASN_ECC_KEY_E;
9813  }
9814 
9815  if (GetInt(s, sig, &idx, sigLen) < 0) {
9816  return ASN_ECC_KEY_E;
9817  }
9818 
9819  return 0;
9820 }

9822 
9823 int wc_EccPrivateKeyDecode(const byte* input, word32* inOutIdx, ecc_key* key,
9824  word32 inSz)
9825 {
9826  word32 oidSum;
9827  int version, length;
9828  int privSz, pubSz = 0;
9829  byte b;
9830  int ret = 0;
9831  int curve_id = ECC_CURVE_DEF;
9832 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
9833  byte* priv;
9834  byte* pub;
9835 #else
9836  byte priv[ECC_MAXSIZE+1];
9837  byte pub[2*(ECC_MAXSIZE+1)]; /* public key has two parts plus header */
9838 #endif
9839  byte* pubData = NULL;
9840 
9841  if (input == NULL || inOutIdx == NULL || key == NULL || inSz == 0)
9842  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
9843 
9844  if (GetSequence(input, inOutIdx, &length, inSz) < 0)
9845  return ASN_PARSE_E;
9846 
9847  if (GetMyVersion(input, inOutIdx, &version, inSz) < 0)
9848  return ASN_PARSE_E;
9849 
9850  b = input[*inOutIdx];
9851  *inOutIdx += 1;
9852 
9853  /* priv type */
9854  if (b != 4 && b != 6 && b != 7)
9855  return ASN_PARSE_E;
9856 
9857  if (GetLength(input, inOutIdx, &length, inSz) < 0)
9858  return ASN_PARSE_E;
9859 
9860  if (length > ECC_MAXSIZE)
9861  return BUFFER_E;
9862 
9863 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
9864  priv = (byte*)XMALLOC(ECC_MAXSIZE+1, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
9865  if (priv == NULL)
9866  return MEMORY_E;
9867 
9868  pub = (byte*)XMALLOC(2*(ECC_MAXSIZE+1), NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
9869  if (pub == NULL) {
9870  XFREE(priv, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
9871  return MEMORY_E;
9872  }
9873 #endif
9874 
9875  /* priv key */
9876  privSz = length;
9877  XMEMCPY(priv, &input[*inOutIdx], privSz);
9878  *inOutIdx += length;
9879 
9880  if (ret == 0 && (*inOutIdx + 1) < inSz) {
9881  /* prefix 0, may have */
9882  b = input[*inOutIdx];
9883  if (b == ECC_PREFIX_0) {
9884  *inOutIdx += 1;
9885 
9886  if (GetLength(input, inOutIdx, &length, inSz) <= 0)
9887  ret = ASN_PARSE_E;
9888  else {
9889  ret = GetObjectId(input, inOutIdx, &oidSum, oidIgnoreType,
9890  inSz);
9891  if (ret == 0) {
9892  if ((ret = CheckCurve(oidSum)) < 0)
9893  ret = ECC_CURVE_OID_E;
9894  else {
9895  curve_id = ret;
9896  ret = 0;
9897  }
9898  }
9899  }
9900  }
9901  }
9902 
9903  if (ret == 0 && (*inOutIdx + 1) < inSz) {
9904  /* prefix 1 */
9905  b = input[*inOutIdx];
9906  *inOutIdx += 1;
9907 
9908  if (b != ECC_PREFIX_1) {
9909  ret = ASN_ECC_KEY_E;
9910  }
9911  else if (GetLength(input, inOutIdx, &length, inSz) <= 0) {
9912  ret = ASN_PARSE_E;
9913  }
9914  else {
9915  /* key header */
9916  ret = CheckBitString(input, inOutIdx, &length, inSz, 0, NULL);
9917  if (ret == 0) {
9918  /* pub key */
9919  pubSz = length;
9920  if (pubSz < 2*(ECC_MAXSIZE+1)) {
9921  XMEMCPY(pub, &input[*inOutIdx], pubSz);
9922  *inOutIdx += length;
9923  pubData = pub;
9924  }
9925  else
9926  ret = BUFFER_E;
9927  }
9928  }
9929  }
9930 
9931  if (ret == 0) {
9932  ret = wc_ecc_import_private_key_ex(priv, privSz, pubData, pubSz, key,
9933  curve_id);
9934  }
9935 
9936 #ifdef WOLFSSL_SMALL_STACK
9937  XFREE(priv, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
9938  XFREE(pub, NULL, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
9939 #endif
9940 
9941  return ret;
9942 }
9943 
9944 
9945 int wc_EccPublicKeyDecode(const byte* input, word32* inOutIdx,
9946  ecc_key* key, word32 inSz)
9947 {
9948  int length;
9949  int ret;
9950 #ifdef ECC_CHECK_PUBLIC_KEY_OID
9951  word32 oidSum;
9952 #endif
9953 
9954  if (input == NULL || inOutIdx == NULL || key == NULL || inSz == 0)
9955  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
9956 
9957  if (GetSequence(input, inOutIdx, &length, inSz) < 0)
9958  return ASN_PARSE_E;
9959 
9960  if (GetSequence(input, inOutIdx, &length, inSz) < 0)
9961  return ASN_PARSE_E;
9962 
9963  ret = SkipObjectId(input, inOutIdx, inSz);
9964  if (ret != 0)
9965  return ret;
9966 
9967  /* ecc params information */
9968 #ifdef ECC_CHECK_PUBLIC_KEY_OID
9969  ret = GetObjectId(input, inOutIdx, &oidSum, oidIgnoreType, inSz);
9970  if (ret != 0)
9971  return ret;
9972  if (CheckCurve(oidSum) < 0)
9973  return ECC_CURVE_OID_E;
9974 #else
9975  ret = SkipObjectId(input, inOutIdx, inSz);
9976  if (ret != 0)
9977  return ret;
9978 #endif
9979 
9980  /* key header */
9981  ret = CheckBitString(input, inOutIdx, NULL, inSz, 1, NULL);
9982  if (ret != 0)
9983  return ret;
9984 
9985  /* This is the raw point data compressed or uncompressed. */
9986  if (wc_ecc_import_x963(input + *inOutIdx, inSz - *inOutIdx, key) != 0)
9987  return ASN_ECC_KEY_E;
9988 
9989  return 0;
9990 }
