9993 #ifdef WOLFSSL_KEY_GEN
9994 
9995 /* build DER formatted ECC key, include optional public key if requested,
9996  * return length on success, negative on error */
9997 static int wc_BuildEccKeyDer(ecc_key* key, byte* output, word32 inLen,
9998  int pubIn)
9999 {
10000  byte curve[MAX_ALGO_SZ+2];
10001  byte ver[MAX_VERSION_SZ];
10002  byte seq[MAX_SEQ_SZ];
10003  byte *prv = NULL, *pub = NULL;
10004  int ret, totalSz, curveSz, verSz;
10005  int privHdrSz = ASN_ECC_HEADER_SZ;
10006  int pubHdrSz = ASN_ECC_CONTEXT_SZ + ASN_ECC_HEADER_SZ;
10007 
10008  word32 idx = 0, prvidx = 0, pubidx = 0, curveidx = 0;
10009  word32 seqSz, privSz, pubSz = ECC_BUFSIZE;
10010 
10011  if (key == NULL || output == NULL || inLen == 0)
10012  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
10013 
10014  /* curve */
10015  curve[curveidx++] = ECC_PREFIX_0;
10016  curveidx++ /* to put the size after computation */;
10017  curveSz = SetCurve(key, curve+curveidx);
10018  if (curveSz < 0)
10019  return curveSz;
10020  /* set computed size */
10021  curve[1] = (byte)curveSz;
10022  curveidx += curveSz;
10023 
10024  /* private */
10025  privSz = key->dp->size;
10026  prv = (byte*)XMALLOC(privSz + privHdrSz + MAX_SEQ_SZ,
10027  key->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
10028  if (prv == NULL) {
10029  return MEMORY_E;
10030  }
10031  prvidx += SetOctetString8Bit(key->dp->size, &prv[prvidx]);
10032  ret = wc_ecc_export_private_only(key, prv + prvidx, &privSz);
10033  if (ret < 0) {
10034  XFREE(prv, key->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
10035  return ret;
10036  }
10037  prvidx += privSz;
10038 
10039  /* pubIn */
10040  if (pubIn) {
10041  ret = wc_ecc_export_x963(key, NULL, &pubSz);
10042  if (ret != LENGTH_ONLY_E) {
10043  XFREE(prv, key->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
10044  return ret;
10045  }
10046 
10047  pub = (byte*)XMALLOC(pubSz + pubHdrSz + MAX_SEQ_SZ,
10048  key->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
10049  if (pub == NULL) {
10050  XFREE(prv, key->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
10051  return MEMORY_E;
10052  }
10053 
10054  pub[pubidx++] = ECC_PREFIX_1;
10055  if (pubSz > 128) /* leading zero + extra size byte */
10056  pubidx += SetLength(pubSz + ASN_ECC_CONTEXT_SZ + 2, pub+pubidx);
10057  else /* leading zero */
10058  pubidx += SetLength(pubSz + ASN_ECC_CONTEXT_SZ + 1, pub+pubidx);
10059 
10060  /* SetBitString adds leading zero */
10061  pubidx += SetBitString(pubSz, 0, pub + pubidx);
10062  ret = wc_ecc_export_x963(key, pub + pubidx, &pubSz);
10063  if (ret != 0) {
10064  XFREE(prv, key->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
10065  XFREE(pub, key->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
10066  return ret;
10067  }
10068  pubidx += pubSz;
10069  }
10070 
10071  /* make headers */
10072  verSz = SetMyVersion(1, ver, FALSE);
10073  seqSz = SetSequence(verSz + prvidx + pubidx + curveidx, seq);
10074 
10075  totalSz = prvidx + pubidx + curveidx + verSz + seqSz;
10076  if (totalSz > (int)inLen) {
10077  XFREE(prv, key->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
10078  if (pubIn) {
10079  XFREE(pub, key->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
10080  }
10081  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
10082  }
10083 
10084  /* write out */
10085  /* seq */
10086  XMEMCPY(output + idx, seq, seqSz);
10087  idx = seqSz;
10088 
10089  /* ver */
10090  XMEMCPY(output + idx, ver, verSz);
10091  idx += verSz;
10092 
10093  /* private */
10094  XMEMCPY(output + idx, prv, prvidx);
10095  idx += prvidx;
10096  XFREE(prv, key->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
10097 
10098  /* curve */
10099  XMEMCPY(output + idx, curve, curveidx);
10100  idx += curveidx;
10101 
10102  /* pubIn */
10103  if (pubIn) {
10104  XMEMCPY(output + idx, pub, pubidx);
10105  /* idx += pubidx; not used after write, if more data remove comment */
10106  XFREE(pub, key->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_TMP_BUFFER);
10107  }
10108 
10109  return totalSz;
10110 }

10113 /* Write a Private ecc key, including public to DER format,
10114  * length on success else < 0 */
10115 int wc_EccKeyToDer(ecc_key* key, byte* output, word32 inLen)
10116 {
10117  return wc_BuildEccKeyDer(key, output, inLen, 1);

10123 int wc_EccPrivateKeyToDer(ecc_key* key, byte* output, word32 inLen)

10134 
10135 int wc_Ed25519PrivateKeyDecode(const byte* input, word32* inOutIdx,
10136  ed25519_key* key, word32 inSz)
10137 {
10138  word32 oid;
10139  int ret, version, length, endKeyIdx, privSz, pubSz;
10140  const byte* priv;
10141  const byte* pub;
10142 
10143  if (input == NULL || inOutIdx == NULL || key == NULL || inSz == 0)
10144  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
10145 
10146  if (GetSequence(input, inOutIdx, &length, inSz) < 0)
10147  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10148  endKeyIdx = *inOutIdx + length;
10149 
10150  if (GetMyVersion(input, inOutIdx, &version, inSz) < 0)
10151  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10152  if (version != 0) {
10153  WOLFSSL_MSG("Unrecognized version of ED25519 private key");
10154  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10155  }
10156 
10157  if (GetAlgoId(input, inOutIdx, &oid, oidKeyType, inSz) < 0)
10158  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10159  if (oid != ED25519k)
10160  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10161 
10162  if (GetOctetString(input, inOutIdx, &length, inSz) < 0)
10163  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10164 
10165  if (GetOctetString(input, inOutIdx, &privSz, inSz) < 0)
10166  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10167  priv = input + *inOutIdx;
10168  *inOutIdx += privSz;
10169 
10170  if (endKeyIdx == (int)*inOutIdx) {
10171  ret = wc_ed25519_import_private_only(priv, privSz, key);
10172  }
10173  else {
10174  if (GetASNHeader(input, ASN_CONTEXT_SPECIFIC | ASN_CONSTRUCTED | 1,
10175  inOutIdx, &length, inSz) < 0) {
10176  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10177  }
10178  if (GetOctetString(input, inOutIdx, &pubSz, inSz) < 0)
10179  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10180  pub = input + *inOutIdx;
10181  *inOutIdx += pubSz;
10182 
10183  ret = wc_ed25519_import_private_key(priv, privSz, pub, pubSz, key);
10184  }
10185  if (ret == 0 && endKeyIdx != (int)*inOutIdx)
10186  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10187 
10188  return ret;
10189 }
10190 
10191 
10192 int wc_Ed25519PublicKeyDecode(const byte* input, word32* inOutIdx,
10193  ed25519_key* key, word32 inSz)
10194 {
10195  int length;
10196  int ret;
10197 #ifdef ECC_CHECK_PUBLIC_KEY_OID
10198  word32 oidSum;
10199 #endif
10200 
10201  if (input == NULL || inOutIdx == NULL || key == NULL || inSz == 0)
10202  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
10203 
10204  if (GetSequence(input, inOutIdx, &length, inSz) < 0)
10205  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10206 
10207  if (GetSequence(input, inOutIdx, &length, inSz) < 0)
10208  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10209 
10210  ret = SkipObjectId(input, inOutIdx, inSz);
10211  if (ret != 0)
10212  return ret;
10213 
10214  /* key header */
10215  ret = CheckBitString(input, inOutIdx, NULL, inSz, 1, NULL);
10216  if (ret != 0)
10217  return ret;
10218 
10219  /* This is the raw point data compressed or uncompressed. */
10220  if (wc_ed25519_import_public(input + *inOutIdx, inSz - *inOutIdx, key) != 0)
10221  return ASN_ECC_KEY_E;
10222 
10223  return 0;
10224 }

10226 
10227 #ifdef WOLFSSL_KEY_GEN
10228 
10229 /* build DER formatted ED25519 key,
10230  * return length on success, negative on error */
10231 static int wc_BuildEd25519KeyDer(ed25519_key* key, byte* output, word32 inLen,
10232  int pubOut)
10233 {
10234  byte algoArray[MAX_ALGO_SZ];
10235  byte ver[MAX_VERSION_SZ];
10236  byte seq[MAX_SEQ_SZ];
10237  int ret;
10238  word32 idx = 0, seqSz, verSz, algoSz, privSz, pubSz = 0;
10239 
10240  if (key == NULL || output == NULL || inLen == 0)
10241  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
10242 
10243  if (pubOut)
10244  pubSz = 2 + 2 + ED25519_PUB_KEY_SIZE;
10245  privSz = 2 + 2 + ED25519_KEY_SIZE;
10246  algoSz = SetAlgoID(ED25519k, algoArray, oidKeyType, 0);
10247  verSz = SetMyVersion(0, ver, FALSE);
10248  seqSz = SetSequence(verSz + algoSz + privSz + pubSz, seq);
10249 
10250  if (seqSz + verSz + algoSz + privSz + pubSz > inLen)
10251  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
10252 
10253  /* write out */
10254  /* seq */
10255  XMEMCPY(output + idx, seq, seqSz);
10256  idx = seqSz;
10257  /* ver */
10258  XMEMCPY(output + idx, ver, verSz);
10259  idx += verSz;
10260  /* algo */
10261  XMEMCPY(output + idx, algoArray, algoSz);
10262  idx += algoSz;
10263  /* privKey */
10264  idx += SetOctetString(2 + ED25519_KEY_SIZE, output + idx);
10265  idx += SetOctetString(ED25519_KEY_SIZE, output + idx);
10266  ret = wc_ed25519_export_private_only(key, output + idx, &privSz);
10267  if (ret != 0)
10268  return ret;
10269  idx += privSz;
10270  /* pubKey */
10271  if (pubOut) {
10272  idx += SetExplicit(1, 2 + ED25519_PUB_KEY_SIZE, output + idx);
10273  idx += SetOctetString(ED25519_KEY_SIZE, output + idx);
10274  ret = wc_ed25519_export_public(key, output + idx, &pubSz);
10275  if (ret != 0)
10276  return ret;
10277  idx += pubSz;
10278  }
10279 
10280  return idx;
10281 }

10283 /* Write a Private ecc key, including public to DER format,

10305 
10306 /* Get raw Date only, no processing, 0 on success */
10307 static int GetBasicDate(const byte* source, word32* idx, byte* date,
10308  byte* format, int maxIdx)
10309 {
10310  int length;
10311 
10312  WOLFSSL_ENTER("GetBasicDate");
10313 
10314  *format = source[*idx];
10315  *idx += 1;
10316  if (*format != ASN_UTC_TIME && *format != ASN_GENERALIZED_TIME)
10317  return ASN_TIME_E;
10318 
10319  if (GetLength(source, idx, &length, maxIdx) < 0)
10320  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10321 
10322  if (length > MAX_DATE_SIZE || length < MIN_DATE_SIZE)
10323  return ASN_DATE_SZ_E;
10324 
10325  XMEMCPY(date, &source[*idx], length);
10326  *idx += length;
10327 
10328  return 0;
10329 }
10330 
10331 #endif
10332

10334 #ifdef HAVE_OCSP
10335 
10336 static int GetEnumerated(const byte* input, word32* inOutIdx, int *value)
10337 {
10338  word32 idx = *inOutIdx;
10339  word32 len;
10340 
10341  WOLFSSL_ENTER("GetEnumerated");
10342 
10343  *value = 0;
10344 
10345  if (input[idx++] != ASN_ENUMERATED)
10346  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10347 
10348  len = input[idx++];
10349  if (len > 4)
10350  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10351 
10352  while (len--) {
10353  *value = *value << 8 | input[idx++];
10354  }
10355 
10356  *inOutIdx = idx;
10357 
10358  return *value;
10359 }
10360 
10361 
10362 static int DecodeSingleResponse(byte* source,
10363  word32* ioIndex, OcspResponse* resp, word32 size)
10364 {
10365  word32 idx = *ioIndex, prevIndex, oid;
10366  int length, wrapperSz;
10367  CertStatus* cs = resp->status;
10368  int ret;
10369 
10370  WOLFSSL_ENTER("DecodeSingleResponse");
10371 
10372  /* Outer wrapper of the SEQUENCE OF Single Responses. */
10373  if (GetSequence(source, &idx, &wrapperSz, size) < 0)
10374  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10375 
10376  prevIndex = idx;
10377 
10378  /* When making a request, we only request one status on one certificate
10379  * at a time. There should only be one SingleResponse */
10380 
10381  /* Wrapper around the Single Response */
10382  if (GetSequence(source, &idx, &length, size) < 0)
10383  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10384 
10385  /* Wrapper around the CertID */
10386  if (GetSequence(source, &idx, &length, size) < 0)
10387  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10388  /* Skip the hash algorithm */
10389  if (GetAlgoId(source, &idx, &oid, oidIgnoreType, size) < 0)
10390  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10391  /* Save reference to the hash of CN */
10392  ret = GetOctetString(source, &idx, &length, size);
10393  if (ret < 0)
10394  return ret;
10395  resp->issuerHash = source + idx;
10396  idx += length;
10397  /* Save reference to the hash of the issuer public key */
10398  ret = GetOctetString(source, &idx, &length, size);
10399  if (ret < 0)
10400  return ret;
10401  resp->issuerKeyHash = source + idx;
10402  idx += length;
10403 
10404  /* Get serial number */
10405  if (GetSerialNumber(source, &idx, cs->serial, &cs->serialSz, size) < 0)
10406  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10407 
10408  /* CertStatus */
10409  switch (source[idx++])
10410  {
10411  case (ASN_CONTEXT_SPECIFIC | CERT_GOOD):
10412  cs->status = CERT_GOOD;
10413  idx++;
10414  break;
10415  case (ASN_CONTEXT_SPECIFIC | ASN_CONSTRUCTED | CERT_REVOKED):
10416  cs->status = CERT_REVOKED;
10417  if (GetLength(source, &idx, &length, size) < 0)
10418  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10419  idx += length;
10420  break;
10421  case (ASN_CONTEXT_SPECIFIC | CERT_UNKNOWN):
10422  cs->status = CERT_UNKNOWN;
10423  idx++;
10424  break;
10425  default:
10426  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10427  }
10428 
10429 #if defined(WOLFSSL_NGINX) || defined(WOLFSSL_HAPROXY)
10430  cs->thisDateAsn = source + idx;
10431 #endif
10432  if (GetBasicDate(source, &idx, cs->thisDate,
10433  &cs->thisDateFormat, size) < 0)
10434  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10435 
10436 #ifndef NO_ASN_TIME
10437  if (!XVALIDATE_DATE(cs->thisDate, cs->thisDateFormat, BEFORE))
10438  return ASN_BEFORE_DATE_E;
10439 #endif
10440 
10441  /* The following items are optional. Only check for them if there is more
10442  * unprocessed data in the singleResponse wrapper. */
10443 
10444  if (((int)(idx - prevIndex) < wrapperSz) &&
10445  (source[idx] == (ASN_CONSTRUCTED | ASN_CONTEXT_SPECIFIC | 0)))
10446  {
10447  idx++;
10448  if (GetLength(source, &idx, &length, size) < 0)
10449  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10450 #if defined(WOLFSSL_NGINX) || defined(WOLFSSL_HAPROXY)
10451  cs->nextDateAsn = source + idx;
10452 #endif
10453  if (GetBasicDate(source, &idx, cs->nextDate,
10454  &cs->nextDateFormat, size) < 0)
10455  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10456 
10457 #ifndef NO_ASN_TIME
10458  if (!XVALIDATE_DATE(cs->nextDate, cs->nextDateFormat, AFTER))
10459  return ASN_AFTER_DATE_E;
10460 #endif
10461  }
10462  if (((int)(idx - prevIndex) < wrapperSz) &&
10463  (source[idx] == (ASN_CONSTRUCTED | ASN_CONTEXT_SPECIFIC | 1)))
10464  {
10465  idx++;
10466  if (GetLength(source, &idx, &length, size) < 0)
10467  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10468  idx += length;
10469  }
10470 
10471  *ioIndex = idx;
10472 
10473  return 0;
10474 }
10475 
10476 static int DecodeOcspRespExtensions(byte* source,
10477  word32* ioIndex, OcspResponse* resp, word32 sz)
10478 {
10479  word32 idx = *ioIndex;
10480  int length;
10481  int ext_bound; /* boundary index for the sequence of extensions */
10482  word32 oid;
10483  int ret;
10484 
10485  WOLFSSL_ENTER("DecodeOcspRespExtensions");
10486 
10487  if ((idx + 1) > sz)
10488  return BUFFER_E;
10489 
10490  if (source[idx++] != (ASN_CONSTRUCTED | ASN_CONTEXT_SPECIFIC | 1))
10491  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10492 
10493  if (GetLength(source, &idx, &length, sz) < 0)
10494  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10495 
10496  if (GetSequence(source, &idx, &length, sz) < 0)
10497  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10498 
10499  ext_bound = idx + length;
10500 
10501  while (idx < (word32)ext_bound) {
10502  if (GetSequence(source, &idx, &length, sz) < 0) {
10503  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tfail: should be a SEQUENCE");
10504  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10505  }
10506 
10507  oid = 0;
10508  if (GetObjectId(source, &idx, &oid, oidOcspType, sz) < 0) {
10509  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tfail: OBJECT ID");
10510  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10511  }
10512 
10513  /* check for critical flag */
10514  if (source[idx] == ASN_BOOLEAN) {
10515  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tfound optional critical flag, moving past");
10516  ret = GetBoolean(source, &idx, sz);
10517  if (ret < 0)
10518  return ret;
10519  }
10520 
10521  ret = GetOctetString(source, &idx, &length, sz);
10522  if (ret < 0)
10523  return ret;
10524 
10525  if (oid == OCSP_NONCE_OID) {
10526  /* get data inside extra OCTET_STRING */
10527  ret = GetOctetString(source, &idx, &length, sz);
10528  if (ret < 0)
10529  return ret;
10530 
10531  resp->nonce = source + idx;
10532  resp->nonceSz = length;
10533  }
10534 
10535  idx += length;
10536  }
10537 
10538  *ioIndex = idx;
10539  return 0;
10540 }
10541 
10542 
10543 static int DecodeResponseData(byte* source,
10544  word32* ioIndex, OcspResponse* resp, word32 size)
10545 {
10546  word32 idx = *ioIndex, prev_idx;
10547  int length;
10548  int version;
10549  word32 responderId = 0;
10550 
10551  WOLFSSL_ENTER("DecodeResponseData");
10552 
10553  resp->response = source + idx;
10554  prev_idx = idx;
10555  if (GetSequence(source, &idx, &length, size) < 0)
10556  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10557  resp->responseSz = length + idx - prev_idx;
10558 
10559  /* Get version. It is an EXPLICIT[0] DEFAULT(0) value. If this
10560  * item isn't an EXPLICIT[0], then set version to zero and move
10561  * onto the next item.
10562  */
10563  if (source[idx] == (ASN_CONTEXT_SPECIFIC | ASN_CONSTRUCTED))
10564  {
10565  idx += 2; /* Eat the value and length */
10566  if (GetMyVersion(source, &idx, &version, size) < 0)
10567  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10568  } else
10569  version = 0;
10570 
10571  responderId = source[idx++];
10572  if ((responderId == (ASN_CONTEXT_SPECIFIC | ASN_CONSTRUCTED | 1)) ||
10573  (responderId == (ASN_CONTEXT_SPECIFIC | ASN_CONSTRUCTED | 2)))
10574  {
10575  if (GetLength(source, &idx, &length, size) < 0)
10576  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10577  idx += length;
10578  }
10579  else
10580  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10581 
10582  /* save pointer to the producedAt time */
10583  if (GetBasicDate(source, &idx, resp->producedDate,
10584  &resp->producedDateFormat, size) < 0)
10585  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10586 
10587  if (DecodeSingleResponse(source, &idx, resp, size) < 0)
10588  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10589 
10590  /*
10591  * Check the length of the ResponseData against the current index to
10592  * see if there are extensions, they are optional.
10593  */
10594  if (idx - prev_idx < resp->responseSz)
10595  if (DecodeOcspRespExtensions(source, &idx, resp, size) < 0)
10596  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10597 
10598  *ioIndex = idx;
10599  return 0;
10600 }
10601 
10602 
10603 #ifndef WOLFSSL_NO_OCSP_OPTIONAL_CERTS
10604 
10605 static int DecodeCerts(byte* source,
10606  word32* ioIndex, OcspResponse* resp, word32 size)
10607 {
10608  word32 idx = *ioIndex;
10609 
10610  WOLFSSL_ENTER("DecodeCerts");
10611 
10612  if (source[idx++] == (ASN_CONSTRUCTED | ASN_CONTEXT_SPECIFIC))
10613  {
10614  int length;
10615 
10616  if (GetLength(source, &idx, &length, size) < 0)
10617  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10618 
10619  if (GetSequence(source, &idx, &length, size) < 0)
10620  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10621 
10622  resp->cert = source + idx;
10623  resp->certSz = length;
10624 
10625  idx += length;
10626  }
10627  *ioIndex = idx;
10628  return 0;
10629 }
10630 
10631 #endif /* WOLFSSL_NO_OCSP_OPTIONAL_CERTS */
10632 
10633 
10634 static int DecodeBasicOcspResponse(byte* source, word32* ioIndex,
10635  OcspResponse* resp, word32 size, void* cm, void* heap, int noVerify)
10636 {
10637  int length;
10638  word32 idx = *ioIndex;
10639  word32 end_index;
10640  int ret;
10641  int sigLength;
10642 
10643  WOLFSSL_ENTER("DecodeBasicOcspResponse");
10644  (void)heap;
10645 
10646  if (GetSequence(source, &idx, &length, size) < 0)
10647  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10648 
10649  if (idx + length > size)
10650  return ASN_INPUT_E;
10651  end_index = idx + length;
10652 
10653  if (DecodeResponseData(source, &idx, resp, size) < 0)
10654  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10655 
10656  /* Get the signature algorithm */
10657  if (GetAlgoId(source, &idx, &resp->sigOID, oidSigType, size) < 0)
10658  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10659 
10660  ret = CheckBitString(source, &idx, &sigLength, size, 1, NULL);
10661  if (ret != 0)
10662  return ret;
10663 
10664  resp->sigSz = sigLength;
10665  resp->sig = source + idx;
10666  idx += sigLength;
10667 
10668  /*
10669  * Check the length of the BasicOcspResponse against the current index to
10670  * see if there are certificates, they are optional.
10671  */
10672 #ifndef WOLFSSL_NO_OCSP_OPTIONAL_CERTS
10673  if (idx < end_index)
10674  {
10675  DecodedCert cert;
10676 
10677  if (DecodeCerts(source, &idx, resp, size) < 0)
10678  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10679 
10680  InitDecodedCert(&cert, resp->cert, resp->certSz, heap);
10681 
10682  /* Don't verify if we don't have access to Cert Manager. */
10683  ret = ParseCertRelative(&cert, CERT_TYPE,
10684  noVerify ? NO_VERIFY : VERIFY_OCSP, cm);
10685  if (ret < 0) {
10686  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tOCSP Responder certificate parsing failed");
10687  FreeDecodedCert(&cert);
10688  return ret;
10689  }
10690 
10691 #ifndef WOLFSSL_NO_OCSP_ISSUER_CHECK
10692  if ((cert.extExtKeyUsage & EXTKEYUSE_OCSP_SIGN) == 0) {
10693  if (XMEMCMP(cert.subjectHash,
10694  resp->issuerHash, KEYID_SIZE) == 0) {
10695  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tOCSP Response signed by issuer");
10696  }
10697  else {
10698  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tOCSP Responder key usage check failed");
10699 
10700  FreeDecodedCert(&cert);
10701  return BAD_OCSP_RESPONDER;
10702  }
10703  }
10704 #endif
10705 
10706  /* ConfirmSignature is blocking here */
10707  ret = ConfirmSignature(&cert.sigCtx,
10708  resp->response, resp->responseSz,
10709  cert.publicKey, cert.pubKeySize, cert.keyOID,
10710  resp->sig, resp->sigSz, resp->sigOID);
10711  FreeDecodedCert(&cert);
10712 
10713  if (ret != 0) {
10714  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tOCSP Confirm signature failed");
10715  return ASN_OCSP_CONFIRM_E;
10716  }
10717  }
10718  else
10719 #endif /* WOLFSSL_NO_OCSP_OPTIONAL_CERTS */
10720  {
10721  Signer* ca = NULL;
10722  int sigValid = -1;
10723 
10724  #ifndef NO_SKID
10725  ca = GetCA(cm, resp->issuerKeyHash);
10726  #else
10727  ca = GetCA(cm, resp->issuerHash);
10728  #endif
10729 
10730  if (ca) {
10731  SignatureCtx sigCtx;
10732  InitSignatureCtx(&sigCtx, heap, INVALID_DEVID);
10733 
10734  /* ConfirmSignature is blocking here */
10735  sigValid = ConfirmSignature(&sigCtx, resp->response,
10736  resp->responseSz, ca->publicKey, ca->pubKeySize, ca->keyOID,
10737  resp->sig, resp->sigSz, resp->sigOID);
10738  }
10739  if (ca == NULL || sigValid != 0) {
10740  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tOCSP Confirm signature failed");
10741  return ASN_OCSP_CONFIRM_E;
10742  }
10743 
10744  (void)noVerify;
10745  }
10746 
10747  *ioIndex = idx;
10748  return 0;
10749 }
10750 
10751 
10752 void InitOcspResponse(OcspResponse* resp, CertStatus* status,
10753  byte* source, word32 inSz)
10754 {
10755  WOLFSSL_ENTER("InitOcspResponse");
10756 
10757  XMEMSET(status, 0, sizeof(CertStatus));
10758  XMEMSET(resp, 0, sizeof(OcspResponse));
10759 
10760  resp->responseStatus = -1;
10761  resp->status = status;
10762  resp->source = source;
10763  resp->maxIdx = inSz;
10764 }
10765 
10766 
10767 int OcspResponseDecode(OcspResponse* resp, void* cm, void* heap, int noVerify)
10768 {
10769  int ret;
10770  int length = 0;
10771  word32 idx = 0;
10772  byte* source = resp->source;
10773  word32 size = resp->maxIdx;
10774  word32 oid;
10775 
10776  WOLFSSL_ENTER("OcspResponseDecode");
10777 
10778  /* peel the outer SEQUENCE wrapper */
10779  if (GetSequence(source, &idx, &length, size) < 0)
10780  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10781 
10782  /* First get the responseStatus, an ENUMERATED */
10783  if (GetEnumerated(source, &idx, &resp->responseStatus) < 0)
10784  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10785 
10786  if (resp->responseStatus != OCSP_SUCCESSFUL)
10787  return 0;
10788 
10789  /* Next is an EXPLICIT record called ResponseBytes, OPTIONAL */
10790  if (idx >= size)
10791  return ASN_INPUT_E;
10792  if (source[idx++] != (ASN_CONSTRUCTED | ASN_CONTEXT_SPECIFIC))
10793  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10794  if (GetLength(source, &idx, &length, size) < 0)
10795  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10796 
10797  /* Get the responseBytes SEQUENCE */
10798  if (GetSequence(source, &idx, &length, size) < 0)
10799  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10800 
10801  /* Check ObjectID for the resposeBytes */
10802  if (GetObjectId(source, &idx, &oid, oidOcspType, size) < 0)
10803  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10804  if (oid != OCSP_BASIC_OID)
10805  return ASN_PARSE_E;
10806  ret = GetOctetString(source, &idx, &length, size);
10807  if (ret < 0)
10808  return ret;
10809 
10810  ret = DecodeBasicOcspResponse(source, &idx, resp, size, cm, heap, noVerify);
10811  if (ret < 0)
10812  return ret;
10813 
10814  return 0;
10815 }
10816 
10817 
10818 word32 EncodeOcspRequestExtensions(OcspRequest* req, byte* output, word32 size)
10819 {
10820  static const byte NonceObjId[] = { 0x2b, 0x06, 0x01, 0x05, 0x05, 0x07,
10821  0x30, 0x01, 0x02 };
10822  byte seqArray[5][MAX_SEQ_SZ];
10823  word32 seqSz[5], totalSz = (word32)sizeof(NonceObjId);
10824 
10825  WOLFSSL_ENTER("SetOcspReqExtensions");
10826 
10827  if (!req || !output || !req->nonceSz)
10828  return 0;
10829 
10830  totalSz += req->nonceSz;
10831  totalSz += seqSz[0] = SetOctetString(req->nonceSz, seqArray[0]);
10832  totalSz += seqSz[1] = SetOctetString(req->nonceSz + seqSz[0], seqArray[1]);
10833  totalSz += seqSz[2] = SetObjectId(sizeof(NonceObjId), seqArray[2]);
10834  totalSz += seqSz[3] = SetSequence(totalSz, seqArray[3]);
10835  totalSz += seqSz[4] = SetSequence(totalSz, seqArray[4]);
10836 
10837  if (totalSz > size)
10838  return 0;
10839 
10840  totalSz = 0;
10841 
10842  XMEMCPY(output + totalSz, seqArray[4], seqSz[4]);
10843  totalSz += seqSz[4];
10844 
10845  XMEMCPY(output + totalSz, seqArray[3], seqSz[3]);
10846  totalSz += seqSz[3];
10847 
10848  XMEMCPY(output + totalSz, seqArray[2], seqSz[2]);
10849  totalSz += seqSz[2];
10850 
10851  XMEMCPY(output + totalSz, NonceObjId, sizeof(NonceObjId));
10852  totalSz += (word32)sizeof(NonceObjId);
10853 
10854  XMEMCPY(output + totalSz, seqArray[1], seqSz[1]);
10855  totalSz += seqSz[1];
10856 
10857  XMEMCPY(output + totalSz, seqArray[0], seqSz[0]);
10858  totalSz += seqSz[0];
10859 
10860  XMEMCPY(output + totalSz, req->nonce, req->nonceSz);
10861  totalSz += req->nonceSz;
10862 
10863  return totalSz;
10864 }
10865 
10866 
10867 int EncodeOcspRequest(OcspRequest* req, byte* output, word32 size)
10868 {
10869  byte seqArray[5][MAX_SEQ_SZ];
10870  /* The ASN.1 of the OCSP Request is an onion of sequences */
10871  byte algoArray[MAX_ALGO_SZ];
10872  byte issuerArray[MAX_ENCODED_DIG_SZ];
10873  byte issuerKeyArray[MAX_ENCODED_DIG_SZ];
10874  byte snArray[MAX_SN_SZ];
10875  byte extArray[MAX_OCSP_EXT_SZ];
10876  word32 seqSz[5], algoSz, issuerSz, issuerKeySz, snSz, extSz, totalSz;
10877  int i;
10878 
10879  WOLFSSL_ENTER("EncodeOcspRequest");
10880 
10881 #ifdef NO_SHA
10882  algoSz = SetAlgoID(SHA256h, algoArray, oidHashType, 0);
10883 #else
10884  algoSz = SetAlgoID(SHAh, algoArray, oidHashType, 0);
10885 #endif
10886 
10887  issuerSz = SetDigest(req->issuerHash, KEYID_SIZE, issuerArray);
10888  issuerKeySz = SetDigest(req->issuerKeyHash, KEYID_SIZE, issuerKeyArray);
10889  snSz = SetSerialNumber(req->serial, req->serialSz, snArray);
10890  extSz = 0;
10891 
10892  if (req->nonceSz) {
10893  /* TLS Extensions use this function too - put extensions after
10894  * ASN.1: Context Specific [2].
10895  */
10896  extSz = EncodeOcspRequestExtensions(req, extArray + 2,
10897  OCSP_NONCE_EXT_SZ);
10898  extSz += SetExplicit(2, extSz, extArray);
10899  }
10900 
10901  totalSz = algoSz + issuerSz + issuerKeySz + snSz;
10902  for (i = 4; i >= 0; i--) {
10903  seqSz[i] = SetSequence(totalSz, seqArray[i]);
10904  totalSz += seqSz[i];
10905  if (i == 2) totalSz += extSz;
10906  }
10907 
10908  if (output == NULL)
10909  return totalSz;
10910  if (totalSz > size)
10911  return BUFFER_E;
10912 
10913  totalSz = 0;
10914  for (i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
10915  XMEMCPY(output + totalSz, seqArray[i], seqSz[i]);
10916  totalSz += seqSz[i];
10917  }
10918 
10919  XMEMCPY(output + totalSz, algoArray, algoSz);
10920  totalSz += algoSz;
10921 
10922  XMEMCPY(output + totalSz, issuerArray, issuerSz);
10923  totalSz += issuerSz;
10924 
10925  XMEMCPY(output + totalSz, issuerKeyArray, issuerKeySz);
10926  totalSz += issuerKeySz;
10927 
10928  XMEMCPY(output + totalSz, snArray, snSz);
10929  totalSz += snSz;
10930 
10931  if (extSz != 0) {
10932  XMEMCPY(output + totalSz, extArray, extSz);
10933  totalSz += extSz;
10934  }
10935 
10936  return totalSz;
10937 }
10938 
10939 
10940 int InitOcspRequest(OcspRequest* req, DecodedCert* cert, byte useNonce,
10941  void* heap)
10942 {
10943  int ret;
10944 
10945  WOLFSSL_ENTER("InitOcspRequest");
10946 
10947  if (req == NULL)
10948  return BAD_FUNC_ARG;
10949 
10950  ForceZero(req, sizeof(OcspRequest));
10951  req->heap = heap;
10952 
10953  if (cert) {
10954  XMEMCPY(req->issuerHash, cert->issuerHash, KEYID_SIZE);
10955  XMEMCPY(req->issuerKeyHash, cert->issuerKeyHash, KEYID_SIZE);
10956 
10957  req->serial = (byte*)XMALLOC(cert->serialSz, req->heap,
10958  DYNAMIC_TYPE_OCSP_REQUEST);
10959  if (req->serial == NULL)
10960  return MEMORY_E;
10961 
10962  XMEMCPY(req->serial, cert->serial, cert->serialSz);
10963  req->serialSz = cert->serialSz;
10964 
10965  if (cert->extAuthInfoSz != 0 && cert->extAuthInfo != NULL) {
10966  req->url = (byte*)XMALLOC(cert->extAuthInfoSz, req->heap,
10967  DYNAMIC_TYPE_OCSP_REQUEST);
10968  if (req->url == NULL) {
10969  XFREE(req->serial, req->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_OCSP);
10970  return MEMORY_E;
10971  }
10972 
10973  XMEMCPY(req->url, cert->extAuthInfo, cert->extAuthInfoSz);
10974  req->urlSz = cert->extAuthInfoSz;
10975  }
10976  }
10977 
10978  if (useNonce) {
10979  WC_RNG rng;
10980 
10981  #ifndef HAVE_FIPS
10982  ret = wc_InitRng_ex(&rng, req->heap, INVALID_DEVID);
10983  #else
10984  ret = wc_InitRng(&rng);
10985  #endif
10986  if (ret != 0) {
10987  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tCannot initialize RNG. Skipping the OSCP Nonce.");
10988  } else {
10989  if (wc_RNG_GenerateBlock(&rng, req->nonce, MAX_OCSP_NONCE_SZ) != 0)
10990  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tCannot run RNG. Skipping the OSCP Nonce.");
10991  else
10992  req->nonceSz = MAX_OCSP_NONCE_SZ;
10993 
10994  wc_FreeRng(&rng);
10995  }
10996  }
10997 
10998  return 0;
10999 }
11000 
11001 void FreeOcspRequest(OcspRequest* req)
11002 {
11003  WOLFSSL_ENTER("FreeOcspRequest");
11004 
11005  if (req) {
11006  if (req->serial)
11007  XFREE(req->serial, req->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_OCSP_REQUEST);
11008 
11009  if (req->url)
11010  XFREE(req->url, req->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_OCSP_REQUEST);
11011  }
11012 }

11014 
11015 int CompareOcspReqResp(OcspRequest* req, OcspResponse* resp)
11016 {
11017  int cmp;
11018 
11019  WOLFSSL_ENTER("CompareOcspReqResp");
11020 
11021  if (req == NULL)
11022  {
11023  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tReq missing");
11024  return -1;
11025  }
11026 
11027  if (resp == NULL)
11028  {
11029  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tResp missing");
11030  return 1;
11031  }
11032 
11033  /* Nonces are not critical. The responder may not necessarily add
11034  * the nonce to the response. */
11035  if (resp->nonceSz != 0) {
11036  cmp = req->nonceSz - resp->nonceSz;
11037  if (cmp != 0)
11038  {
11039  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tnonceSz mismatch");
11040  return cmp;
11041  }
11042 
11043  cmp = XMEMCMP(req->nonce, resp->nonce, req->nonceSz);
11044  if (cmp != 0)
11045  {
11046  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tnonce mismatch");
11047  return cmp;
11048  }
11049  }
11050 
11051  cmp = XMEMCMP(req->issuerHash, resp->issuerHash, KEYID_SIZE);
11052  if (cmp != 0)
11053  {
11054  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tissuerHash mismatch");
11055  return cmp;
11056  }
11057 
11058  cmp = XMEMCMP(req->issuerKeyHash, resp->issuerKeyHash, KEYID_SIZE);
11059  if (cmp != 0)
11060  {
11061  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tissuerKeyHash mismatch");
11062  return cmp;
11063  }
11064 
11065  cmp = req->serialSz - resp->status->serialSz;
11066  if (cmp != 0)
11067  {
11068  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tserialSz mismatch");
11069  return cmp;
11070  }
11071 
11072  cmp = XMEMCMP(req->serial, resp->status->serial, req->serialSz);
11073  if (cmp != 0)
11074  {
11075  WOLFSSL_MSG("\tserial mismatch");
11076  return cmp;
11077  }
11078 
11079  return 0;
11080 }
11081 
11082 #endif
11083 
11084 
11085 /* store SHA hash of NAME */
11086 WOLFSSL_LOCAL int GetNameHash(const byte* source, word32* idx, byte* hash,
11087  int maxIdx)
11088 {
11089  int length; /* length of all distinguished names */
11090  int ret;
11091  word32 dummy;
11092 
11093  WOLFSSL_ENTER("GetNameHash");
11094 
11095  if (source[*idx] == ASN_OBJECT_ID) {
11096  WOLFSSL_MSG("Trying optional prefix...");
11097 
11098  if (GetLength(source, idx, &length, maxIdx) < 0)
11099  return ASN_PARSE_E;
11100 
11101  *idx += length;
11102  WOLFSSL_MSG("Got optional prefix");
11103  }
11104 
11105  /* For OCSP, RFC2560 section 4.1.1 states the issuer hash should be
11106  * calculated over the entire DER encoding of the Name field, including
11107  * the tag and length. */
11108  dummy = *idx;
11109  if (GetSequence(source, idx, &length, maxIdx) < 0)
11110  return ASN_PARSE_E;
11111 
11112 #ifdef NO_SHA
11113  ret = wc_Sha256Hash(source + dummy, length + *idx - dummy, hash);
11114 #else
11115  ret = wc_ShaHash(source + dummy, length + *idx - dummy, hash);
11116 #endif
11117 
11118  *idx += length;
11119 
11120  return ret;
11121 }

11126 /* initialize decoded CRL */
11127 void InitDecodedCRL(DecodedCRL* dcrl, void* heap)

11131  dcrl->certBegin = 0;
11132  dcrl->sigIndex = 0;
11133  dcrl->sigLength = 0;
11134  dcrl->signatureOID = 0;

11136  dcrl->totalCerts = 0;
11137  dcrl->heap = heap;

11139  dcrl->heap = (void*)WOLFSSL_HEAP_TEST;
11140  #endif
11141 }

11144 /* free decoded CRL resources */
11145 void FreeDecodedCRL(DecodedCRL* dcrl)
11146 {
11147  RevokedCert* tmp = dcrl->certs;
11148 
11149  WOLFSSL_MSG("FreeDecodedCRL");
11150 
11151  while(tmp) {
11152  RevokedCert* next = tmp->next;
11153  XFREE(tmp, dcrl->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_REVOKED);
11154  tmp = next;
11155  }
11156 }
11157 
11158 
11159 /* Get Revoked Cert list, 0 on success */
11160 static int GetRevoked(const byte* buff, word32* idx, DecodedCRL* dcrl,
11161  int maxIdx)
11162 {
11163  int len;
11164  word32 end;
11165  byte b;
11166  RevokedCert* rc;
11167 
11168  WOLFSSL_ENTER("GetRevoked");
11169 
11170  if (GetSequence(buff, idx, &len, maxIdx) < 0)
11171  return ASN_PARSE_E;
11172 
11173  end = *idx + len;
11174 
11175  rc = (RevokedCert*)XMALLOC(sizeof(RevokedCert), dcrl->heap,
11176  DYNAMIC_TYPE_REVOKED);
11177  if (rc == NULL) {
11178  WOLFSSL_MSG("Alloc Revoked Cert failed");
11179  return MEMORY_E;
11180  }
11181 
11182  if (GetSerialNumber(buff, idx, rc->serialNumber, &rc->serialSz,
11183  maxIdx) < 0) {
11184  XFREE(rc, dcrl->heap, DYNAMIC_TYPE_REVOKED);
11185  return ASN_PARSE_E;
11186  }
11187 
11188  /* add to list */
11189  rc->next = dcrl->certs;
11190  dcrl->certs = rc;
11191  dcrl->totalCerts++;
11192 
11193 
11194  /* get date */
11195  b = buff[*idx];
11196  *idx += 1;
11197 
11198  if (b != ASN_UTC_TIME && b != ASN_GENERALIZED_TIME) {
11199  WOLFSSL_MSG("Expecting Date");
11200  return ASN_PARSE_E;
11201  }
11202 
11203  if (GetLength(buff, idx, &len, maxIdx) < 0)
11204  return ASN_PARSE_E;
11205 
11206  /* skip for now */
11207  *idx += len;
11208 
11209  if (*idx != end) /* skip extensions */
11210  *idx = end;
11211 
11212  return 0;
11213 }
11214 
11215 
11216 /* Get CRL Signature, 0 on success */
11217 static int GetCRL_Signature(const byte* source, word32* idx, DecodedCRL* dcrl,
11218  int maxIdx)
11219 {
11220  int length;
11221  int ret;
11222 
11223  WOLFSSL_ENTER("GetCRL_Signature");
11224 
11225  ret = CheckBitString(source, idx, &length, maxIdx, 1, NULL);
11226  if (ret != 0)
11227  return ret;
11228  dcrl->sigLength = length;
11229 
11230  dcrl->signature = (byte*)&source[*idx];
11231  *idx += dcrl->sigLength;
11232 
11233  return 0;
11234 }
11235 
11236 int VerifyCRL_Signature(SignatureCtx* sigCtx, const byte* toBeSigned,
11237  word32 tbsSz, const byte* signature, word32 sigSz,
11238  word32 signatureOID, Signer *ca, void* heap)
11239 {
11240  /* try to confirm/verify signature */
11241 #ifndef IGNORE_KEY_EXTENSIONS
11242  if ((ca->keyUsage & KEYUSE_CRL_SIGN) == 0) {
11243  WOLFSSL_MSG("CA cannot sign CRLs");
11244  return ASN_CRL_NO_SIGNER_E;
11245  }
11246 #endif /* IGNORE_KEY_EXTENSIONS */
11247 
11248  InitSignatureCtx(sigCtx, heap, INVALID_DEVID);
11249  if (ConfirmSignature(sigCtx, toBeSigned, tbsSz, ca->publicKey,
11250  ca->pubKeySize, ca->keyOID, signature, sigSz,
11251  signatureOID) != 0) {
11252  WOLFSSL_MSG("CRL Confirm signature failed");
11253  return ASN_CRL_CONFIRM_E;
11254  }
11255 
11256  return 0;
11257 }
11258 
11259 /* prase crl buffer into decoded state, 0 on success */
11260 int ParseCRL(DecodedCRL* dcrl, const byte* buff, word32 sz, void* cm)
11261 {
11262  int version, len, doNextDate = 1;
11263  word32 oid, idx = 0, dateIdx;
11264  Signer* ca = NULL;
11265  SignatureCtx sigCtx;
11266 
11267  WOLFSSL_MSG("ParseCRL");
11268 
11269  /* raw crl hash */
11270  /* hash here if needed for optimized comparisons
11271  * Sha sha;
11272  * wc_InitSha(&sha);
11273  * wc_ShaUpdate(&sha, buff, sz);
11274  * wc_ShaFinal(&sha, dcrl->crlHash); */
11275 
11276  if (GetSequence(buff, &idx, &len, sz) < 0)
11277  return ASN_PARSE_E;
11278 
11279  dcrl->certBegin = idx;
11280 
11281  if (GetSequence(buff, &idx, &len, sz) < 0)
11282  return ASN_PARSE_E;
11283  dcrl->sigIndex = len + idx;
11284 
11285  /* may have version */
11286  if (buff[idx] == ASN_INTEGER) {
11287  if (GetMyVersion(buff, &idx, &version, sz) < 0)
11288  return ASN_PARSE_E;
11289  }
11290 
11291  if (GetAlgoId(buff, &idx, &oid, oidIgnoreType, sz) < 0)
11292  return ASN_PARSE_E;
11293 
11294  if (GetNameHash(buff, &idx, dcrl->issuerHash, sz) < 0)
11295  return ASN_PARSE_E;
11296 
11297  if (GetBasicDate(buff, &idx, dcrl->lastDate, &dcrl->lastDateFormat, sz) < 0)
11298  return ASN_PARSE_E;
11299 
11300  dateIdx = idx;
11301 
11302  if (GetBasicDate(buff, &idx, dcrl->nextDate, &dcrl->nextDateFormat, sz) < 0)
11303  {
11304 #ifndef WOLFSSL_NO_CRL_NEXT_DATE
11305  (void)dateIdx;
11306  return ASN_PARSE_E;
11307 #else
11308  dcrl->nextDateFormat = ASN_OTHER_TYPE; /* skip flag */
11309  doNextDate = 0;
11310  idx = dateIdx;
11311 #endif
11312  }
11313 
11314  if (doNextDate) {
11315 #ifndef NO_ASN_TIME
11316  if (!XVALIDATE_DATE(dcrl->nextDate, dcrl->nextDateFormat, AFTER)) {
11317  WOLFSSL_MSG("CRL after date is no longer valid");
11318  return ASN_AFTER_DATE_E;
11319  }
11320 #endif
11321  }
11322 
11323  if (idx != dcrl->sigIndex && buff[idx] != CRL_EXTENSIONS) {
11324  if (GetSequence(buff, &idx, &len, sz) < 0)
11325  return ASN_PARSE_E;
11326 
11327  len += idx;
11328 
11329  while (idx < (word32)len) {
11330  if (GetRevoked(buff, &idx, dcrl, sz) < 0)
11331  return ASN_PARSE_E;
11332  }
11333  }
11334 
11335  if (idx != dcrl->sigIndex)
11336  idx = dcrl->sigIndex; /* skip extensions */
11337 
11338  if (GetAlgoId(buff, &idx, &dcrl->signatureOID, oidSigType, sz) < 0)
11339  return ASN_PARSE_E;
11340 
11341  if (GetCRL_Signature(buff, &idx, dcrl, sz) < 0)
11342  return ASN_PARSE_E;
11343 
11344  /* openssl doesn't add skid by default for CRLs cause firefox chokes
11345  we're not assuming it's available yet */
11346 #if !defined(NO_SKID) && defined(CRL_SKID_READY)
11347  if (dcrl->extAuthKeyIdSet)
11348  ca = GetCA(cm, dcrl->extAuthKeyId);
11349  if (ca == NULL)
11350  ca = GetCAByName(cm, dcrl->issuerHash);
11351 #else
11352  ca = GetCA(cm, dcrl->issuerHash);
11353 #endif /* !NO_SKID && CRL_SKID_READY */
11354  WOLFSSL_MSG("About to verify CRL signature");
11355 
11356  if (ca == NULL) {
11357  WOLFSSL_MSG("Did NOT find CRL issuer CA");
11358  return ASN_CRL_NO_SIGNER_E;
11359  }
11360 
11361  WOLFSSL_MSG("Found CRL issuer CA");
11362  return VerifyCRL_Signature(&sigCtx, buff + dcrl->certBegin,
11363  dcrl->sigIndex - dcrl->certBegin, dcrl->signature, dcrl->sigLength,
11364  dcrl->signatureOID, ca, dcrl->heap);
11365 }
11366 
11367 #endif /* HAVE_CRL */
11368 
11369 #undef ERROR_OUT
11370 
11371 #endif /* !NO_ASN */
11372

11374 
11375 
11376 #endif /* WOLFSSL_SEP */
